notes: A few oddities about our home: The front door is a bit odd, turn it about a quarter turn past what you think you need to turn it. The key is to the front gate. If you close the gate it will automatically lock and you will need the key to get back in, so always keep your keys on you.

interaction: We are social and friendly. We love to share beer when we have some, and occasionally some wine. Though we are fine doing our own thing if you want to do yours.

name: CANYON BEDROOM SURROUNDED BY TREES
summary: Close to naval bases/harbors & downtown, great for relaxing, long-term stays. The house was dreamt & built by a great sea captain & muralist. Above a quiet canyon hawks fly in the day, coyotes sing at night - bedroom stays cool on hot sunny days!
space: High above our beautiful San Diego experience this panorama of beauty in our urban oasis/artist/sculpture/loft.  I love the silence and diversity of the neighborhood. 10 minutes from Balboa Park & downtown. It is perfect for visiting artists, vacationers, weekenders, or if you are in San Diego on an extended work trip.  The three- level sunny loft was inspired by the sea captain's voyages & his love for sci-fi imagery.  The upper entrance was inspired by the Tardis" - a time machine in "Dr. Who". This becomes the pivotal concept of this architectural wonder -  An arced bridge acts as a threshold between two worlds;  linking the street to an eight-foot-square entrance tower or "time machine" that transports the individual from one world to another.  Once inside
description: a new realm unfolds.  The space opens dramatically to reveal a volume sculpted by the three levels below -  An ocean view on a clear day from the dining room table or outside upper deck provides vistas of one of  The Coronado I"

notes: We are in one of the most diverse part of San Diego - a true melting pot.  Neighbors from all over the world.  We are on a quiet street above a canyon.  Although 10 minutes from downtown, it feels rural here - some neighbors have goats, ducks, and chickens.  I truly love my neighborhood!  I like to walk in my neighborhood and see the great views of Coronado Island, Point Loma, the Catalina Islands of Mexico, the surrounding mountains, and the Pacific Ocean.
transit: We live in a canyon, although close to the city we are surrounded by nature and its givings. Coyotes, hawks, raccoons, ants, hummingbirds, doves and other wildlife abound.  If you love & respect nature, you will be happy here, if not, you might be happier in another fabulous place in our wonderful city. :) We're also nurturing the long tradition of providing space for long-term visiting naval personnel, civil service workers, and artists of all stripes. We look forward to longer visits from people who are here on business, or looking to get away from their regular lives but also to begin, work on or finish their dream projects. No access to lower patio off yoga floor, or use of 8 foot sliding door, nor tardis entrance over bridge, nor upstairs private bathroom, nor other bedrooms in house.

host_about: San Diego, California, United States
host_response_time: Hi! I am a musician (piano & slide guitar), writer, teacher, animal lover, art enthusiast, foodie, & perpetual tourist--even in my own city :)! I love meeting new people, spending time with family and friends, practicing gratitude, having adventures and enjoying all the great things San Diego has to offer :) I've lived half my life in the U.S., and the other half in Europe (born and raised there), Africa  & many other places mostly in the northern hemisphere. I worked on a sailboat for three years in the Red Sea, Med, and South China Seas & use to manage “The Last Refuge” restaurant in the Sinai.  Tragically--haven't traveled much lately, so really enjoy when travelers bring that wonderful travel essence here! I’m a community volunteer – I teach songwriting to children as a means of increasing literacy.   My favorite day trip in San Diego is to ride my bike from Ocean Beach, then along Mission Bay to Pacific Beach, then up along the coast to La Jolla, do yoga in La Jolla, swim in La Jolla Cove, and ride my bike back south again. I love the water!!! My favorite travel destinations are around latitude 30 degrees north – San Diego, Baja, the Sonoran Desert, Sinai, Katmandu.  This home is dedicated to resting and recharging, loving the earth and all the creatures that inhabit it, and is a retreat and sanctuary for myself, my cat Ms. Lady Pirate,  and YOU :)! Namaste, y'all!

notes: The room is in front of the house and all other bedrooms are on the second floor. You will not be heard and you won't hear others. Semi-Private entry meaning you won't see anyone unless someone is entering/exiting at the same time. The entrance is almost like a hotel lobby.
transit: Unfortunately public transport is not excellent in San Diego. The Bus stop is roughly a one mile walk from our home, we recommend renting a car while enjoying your stay in San Diego although it is possible to commute via bus if you want to visit downtown San Diego please realize public transport will take about an hour.  Uber and Lyft are phone apps for the phone and cheaper taxi services. An Uber from the airport is $26-$30.

neighborhood_overview: Ocean Beach California is a small beach community of San Diego and is one of the most relaxed places in all of Southern California. If you want to experience the way California was in the 50's and 60's visit Ocean Beach. It is one cool and hip place. At Ocean Beach you can enjoy shops, restaurants, bars, antique stores, or just sit back and watch the surfers catch waves at the OB Pier. Stroll down to Sunset Cliffs and enjoy enchanting views where you might even be lucky enough to see passing Whales!
notes: The Bedroom is Extremely Comfortable with a quality mattresse, Down alternative mattress bed topper. Wonderful High Quality Linens and blankets. Every Detail has been seen too from Linens to Decor to make your stay the most enjoyable possible… You'll feel like your in an actual home rather than a sparse rental! Custom tile bathroom that will make you feel like you are in an underwater Grotto! The bathroom has a beautiful, deep claw foot bath tub to take a relaxing bath in after a fun day of exploring. The shower is the ultimate in relaxation with a Large Rain head shower head and an on demand water heater so you'll never run out of hot water!! Ask us about our Concierge Services! The $3 ticket price allows riders on and off privileges for the entire day.  SAN DIEGO TROLLY: The San Diego Trolley provides convenient services from key locations downtown, including the Santa Fe Depot and the San Diego Convention Center, crisscrossing through downtown and out to various locations like Old Town and Mission Valley. neighborhood_overview: Pacific Beach (PB) is one of the most popular beach areas of San Diego. It is not surprising when you see what it has to offer! You can spend the day relaxing on this beautiful beach, soaking in the sun; or if you are feeling adventurous, hit the waves for some of the best surf in SoCal. Other water sports include paddle boarding, Jet Skiing, boating and the famous water jet pack that lets you hover over the ocean. Pacific Beach has numerous bars and restaurants, all with a lively atmospheres. It is the ideal location for a relaxing day and a buzzing night. If you're looking for a more laid back experience, no problem - North PB is a 5 minute walk that provides quiet cafes and restaurants for a top notch dining experience. If you want a bit more hustle, be sure to walk down the boardwalk that goes all the way to South Mission Beach. Here's where you will find Belmont Park, home to the Big Dipper, a historic wooden roller coaster right along the boardwalk, souvenir shops and lots of nig
notes: Please check out the welcome notebook inside the condo for useful tips, and have a great time-- PB was made for it!

We are 10 minutes driving from the zoo, downtown, Balboa park, Safeco Field, Qualcomm Stadium, Old Town, Little Italy and many other tourist destinations.  Mission Hills is one of San Diego’s premier communities, where you can stroll the neighborhood, enjoy our parks (Lewis Street Park, Pioneer Park, Presidio Park), dine at local eateries (we are 2 blocks from The Patio, one of San Diego's 2014 Best Restaurant award winners), sample wine and beer, take in a movie in Hillcrest, or shop at one of our local grocery stores...all within walking distance.

notes: Pacific Beach is a fun and young vibrant beach neighborhood of San Diego.  While there is always a party somewhere in bustling bars of Pacific Beach (or as we say, PB), North PB has distinguished itself as being quieter and more refined with a relaxed beachy environment.  There is truly something for everyone here.  Every day out feels like a vacation even for those who live here!
transit: Pro-tip for San Diego: book for 31 days or more to avoid the Short Term Occupancy Tax of 10% and get a significant monthly discount.  Also FYI for new bookers - Airbnb typically adds a 12% fee on top of the advertised rate. Donation based yoga classes overlooking the ocean is available on weekends just two blocks away.  There's also a great wine bar that has live music twice a day just two blocks away.
access: The bus is only a block away and can take you through up to La Jolla to UCSD and UTC or down through PB and MB to the central transit hub of Old Town.   Street parking is always available nearby.
interaction: You'll have access to the entire place with exception of the master bedroom, where I'll be sleeping.  Full size bed can accommodate up to two people.  Queen size or twin air mattress available for one or two additional people.
house_rules: I enjoy hosting and showing people the sites and experiences San Diego has to offer so feel free to ask about my availability to be your guide during your stay.  Guests staying a month or longer are ideal for me and you get a good discount if you book for 31 days or longer!

There are some really great breakfast joints like Leilani's Hawaiian and Konos.  Oscar's original location is a must for authentic Baja fish tacos.  We are not far from Tourmaline Surf Park, a great beginner's surf break.  Mt. Soledad and Kate Sessions park are two sights that offer spectacular views of the area. notes: The apartment is non-smoking.  We are close to the beach we kindly ask our guests to clean off any sand before coming back from beach yoga or an epic surf sesh!

host_about: Hi thanks for checking out my listing!   I moved to San Diego about a decade ago from New York for graduate school and the sunshine and surf kept me out here. name: La Jolla Shores Studio Guest House
summary: Only 3 Blocks to the beach and located in prestigious La Jolla Shores is this eclectic surf studio guest house.  After a day spent at beautiful La Jolla Shores beach (just 3 blocks away) the backyard feels like an oasis. If you need to plug into the tech world of “Sonos” or “Alexa”, or if you need “over the top” luxury please look elsewhere. There’s wi-fi and one TV with cable—that’s about it.
space: This 400 sq ft “studio” guest house, only two blocks to the beach and restaurants, general store and many other retail stores. It features a main area with queen size bed, small seating area, kitchenette with refrigerator, sink, microwave and coffee pot (no stove/oven), wifi smart tv, lots of natural light, views of the gardens and so much more. The location in the Shores has accurately been described as perfect. You’re close to the beach but away from the crowds and noise. I’ve provided beach towels, umbrellas, beach chairs. La Jolla Shores is probably the best family friendly beach on the west coast—maybe in the country.

neighborhood_overview: Great central location in San Diego.  Quiet, and great freeway access to all parts of town! Look at my other listing for the main house to see people’s reviews of the location.  5 minutes to north park and south park  10 minutes downtown and mission valley, Zoo, and balboa park 15 minutes to beaches/sea world. The neighborhood itself is purely residential.  There are a couple of small restaurants and quick food places as well as a 7-11 within walking distance, and there is a nice neighborhood park with a playground and basketball court within a 5 minute walk.  Otherwise you’ll need to drive to explore San Diego.
notes: This is a cool little studio the I have recently built out of the garage.  I am living in it myself, and just renting it out while I’m out of town.  It’s totally comfortable but there are still some signs it’s a garage.  Mainly, the floor is concrete with a rug over it, and the one wall is still a garage door, however I have covered it with insulated moving pads as well as an aesthetic curtain, so it’s hard to even tell there’s a garage door there.   The private entrance is through the side yard of the house, and I keep some tools/and various yard supplies over there, so the outside looks a little messy, but the the patio area in the back will look nice and be a great place to relax.   If all this sounds good, then shoot me a message!
transit: You’ll need a vehicle to get around San Diego from this location.  Uber/Lift are options also, but public transit is not a realistic option in San Diego in general :-)
access: The whole studio with its own private entrance, and private backyard space.
interaction: I will be gone, this will be a private unit.  There are two women who live in the main house who prefer no interaction with the Airbnb guests.
host_about:
I've lived in San Diego for 7 years and have been hosting Airbnb guests here at my little house for about 3 years now.  It has been great meeting people from around the world and introducing them to my amazing city.  Originally from Northern California, I've lived in San Francisco, Los Angeles, Washington DC, New York, and finally here in San Diego.  I've yet to live abroad, and really hope I get the chance to sometime in the future.  My work schedule is pretty flexible and allows me the freedom to travel and explore often. I like to think I'm a good balance between outdoorsy/city dweller.  Love camping, skiing, hiking, sleeping on the beach, backpacking, as well as night life, bars, restaurants, historic sites, museums, etc.

I have made friends from all over the world through Airbnb, which is probably my favorite thing about being a host.  I've had guests from all corners of the globe, and its amazing to hear all of their unique stories.  I'm happy to give restaurant, or neighborhood recommendations, and even on occasion taking my guests out on a little tour.  I want my guests to have the best possible time during their visit to San Diego.

neighborhood_overview: Very quiet neighborhood. Our house is located in a very unique area at the edge of Mira Mesa and Rancho Peñasquitos. It overlooks the Los Peñasquitos Canyon Preserve. There is a trail down the Canyon where you can hike or bike. This trail has some of the better scenery in San Diego. The scenery of the canyon includes: a waterfall cascading through volcanic rock; a streamside forest of giant California live oaks; groves of majestic sycamore trees; a year-round stream populated by pacific tree frogs, crayfish and largemouth bass; a fresh water marsh hosting a variety of aquatic birds including great blue herons, egrets, mallard ducks; and mule deer, bobcat, coyote, and raccoon are just a few of the mammals than can be observed throughout the Preserve.
notes: Not kid friendly, ages 0 - 12
transit: Public transportation is available - 21 mins walk to bus station and 13 mins drive to train station.
access: Master suite, kitchen, space in the refrigerator, living room area, backyard/patio, washer & dryer, wireless, TV, community pool (heated)...and ample free parking. No cooking after 9:00 pm. host_about:
I grew up at the beach and spent most of my early adulthood living in various beach communities.  I love to surf  but like many San Diegans, in my adult years I moved 'up on the hill'.  

I feel very fortunate to have found a nice cottage in University Heights.  I work at home and really enjoy living in a quiet historical neighborhood on a stunning canyon.  The folks I work with have gotten used to the sound of birds singing when I join conference calls.  :-)

I've always loved to travel, especially meeting people.  With AirBnB, I'm looking forward to meeting people on their travels and helping them enjoy America's Finest City.  I know the city very well so if you want any tips on where to go or what to do, don't hesitate to ask.

I'm a frequent volunteer in the community.  I like to play cards, love food and craft beer.  I prefer flip flops to power suits.  I love animals, especially well behaved dogs.

This home is Located in the downtown neighborhood of Cortez Hill.  A $5 Lyft ride to Comic-con or a 15 minute walk.   It comes with an amazing WHOLE HOME sound system. Large LED Samsung TVs.  laundry facilities.  Subzero fridge, Wolf Range, Zoned AC, BBQ, Free high speed wifi, & more.
space: This is a stand alone house, which is super unique for a downtown environment.   Enjoy the convenience of being close to the action for easy access, but far enough away to get a peaceful nights rest.    We are about a quarter mile from the flight path so if you are sensitive to airplane noise, you wouldn't be happy here.  You would have your own bedroom that will have air mattress and couch, and you will have your own private bath.   You can have access to the kitchen but no heavy meal prep nor food storage.  The rental fee is for 2 people.  If you have an extra person or two let me know, it's possible we could accomodate more.  There is also another house on the same property that may be available.  This second house can handle 5 people (4 people comfortably) and is a stand alone home you can have to yourself if a private space is what you seek. name: 4 blocks away form the beach !
summary: My husband and I are going on a 1 month vacation from Sep 17th till Oct 17th, and are looking for someone who's interested in renting the apartment while we're away. Must be someone responsible who'll take good care of our apartment and return it as received. The apartment is 680 sq ft big, and has a nice size living room, kitchen, bedroom and bathroom (including a bathtub). Located in N Pacific Beach, 4 blocks away from the beach and a walking distance from Garner Ave, Mission Blvd and more.

name: Spend Comic Con Week in a Modern Style Bungalow!
summary: Completely renovated, modern, 1-Bedroom private home in the historic Logan Heights neighborhood of San Diego. **Could be noisy. This home is situated within walking / Uber distance from many popular vacation destinations! Super close to Downtown, the Convention Center, Petco Park, Gaslamp District, Balboa Park, zoo, + a handful of beer breweries. Walk to Comic-Con or a quick Uber over the bridge to Coronado island will get you to one of the top 10 beaches in the USA. Car rental not required!
space: My girlfriend + I own this property.  We are both architects + as such we were planning to purchase a property then begin an extensive renovation.   This home was originally built in 1925, likely as a worker's bungalow.  In 2016 we purchased the home (which had since been converted to a duplex).  So far we have updated pretty much every single component of the structure, w/ our initial focus on this unit (Unit A).   The home is renovated to be in the modern / minimalist style, but special attention has been taken to display the structure's historic nature (notice the exposed ceiling beams).   Today the home functions as both a green home + as a smart home.

neighborhood_overview: Logan Heights is a historical neighborhood in San Diego.  It's considered up-and-coming but is still a little rough around the edges.   **All of our neighbors are friendly, but some are not as courteous as we'd prefer.  In this neighborhood it is common for loud music to play through the night or for dogs to bark unattended to.  Most of the time there is peace + quiet @ our property, but on occurrence you may hear muted bass music or random dogs barking.  If this is something that may bother you, we apologize but this may not be the right neighborhood for your trip.   We recommend staying west of 32nd Street + taking an uber after dark.

transit: If you like to walk, this location is going to be great for you (we walk to work during the weekdays)!  You can usually use the electric scooters that are available on the sidewalk downtown or an uber to get back home.   Chicano Park:  0.5 mile walk Petco Park:  1.5 mile walk The Convention Center:  2 mile walk If you don't like to walk or would like to explore a little further a quick drive or a cheap uber will get you to some of the nations best vacation destinations.   Balboa Park:  5min Convention Center:  10min Coronado island beach:  10min Downtown San Diego:  10min North Park:  10min Mission Beach:  15min Ocean Beach:  15min Pacific Beach:  15min Point Loma:  20min Torry Pines Golf Course:  25min La Jolla:  25min
access: Guests will be able to cook in our Kitchen (cooktop, oven, microwave, sink, dishwasher).  We'll leave some information about the cookware / tableware.  You may also use our refrigerator, although we may have some personal items in there.   You may use our projector / entertainment system.  There is an apple tv w/ access to netflix, amazon prime, + youtube.  You can play your music through the apple tv airplay or the 1/8 headphone input.  There is also a 2nd tv w/ another apple tv in the Bedroom."
interaction: We may be able to meet you when you check in, depending on our schedule.  We'd be happy to meet you!
house_rules: - 420 friendly!  You may smoke marijuana indoors (glass pieces / vape only). - No shoes in the house please. - Quiet hours from 10pm - 9am.
host_about: Hi!  I'm the property owner.  I own + operate a small modern residential architecture firm in San Diego.  I like art, music, + obviously architecture.  Logan Heights is one of my favorite neighborhoods in San Diego b/c it has so much character + quick access to some of this cities hidden gems.  I purchased this duplex w/ my girlfriend (who is also an architect) b/c we believe this neighborhood will become on of the most popular in San Diego over the next few years.

name: Light, Bright, and Breezy Home near Downtown
summary: Light bright and breezy. Come enjoy San Diego's amazing weather in the penthouse suite at Casa De Georgia. This 1 bedroom unit is located upstairs with no shared walls. Plenty of windows let in sunlight and San Diego breezes. If it gets too hot, turn on the AC- but we bet you won't need it in this breezy unit. Fully equipped kitchen with everything you need. Long or short term stays are welcome.

Plenty of windows let in sunlight and San Diego breezes. If it gets too hot, turn on the AC- but we bet you won't need it in this breezy unit. Fully equipped kitchen with everything you need. Long or short term stays are welcome. You will have access to the entire private apartment. You will also have access to a shared yard and shared laundry. This neighborhood is very walkable. There are a number of great restaurants, coffee shops, bars, and a grocery store just a short walk away. Downtown, Balboa Park, and the Zoo are a quick Uber away. The beach is about 20 minutes away. We are close to public transportation. Parking is on the street only. We suggest you plan to use public transportation during your stay so you don't have to search for parking. Parking all over San Diego is limited, this neighborhood is no different

name: Studio with beautiful natural light by Gaslamp!
summary: Charming 2nd floor studio apartment located in historic building in downtown San Diego. Walking distance (three blocks) to the Gaslamp Quarter, Convention Center, and Petco Park! This  studio is bright, boasts hardwood floors, a full kitchen, great downtown views, access to rooftop lounge and beautiful garden, walk-in closet, and a claw foot bathtub. There is artwork throughout the building and amazing greenery in the community spaces. Perfect for those looking to stay near the Gaslamp District.
space: 500 square foot studio apt on second floor in historic building on 9th ave downtown. Fantastic rooftop garden and lounge with tables/chairs to enjoy morning coffee or a late afternoon beer. This is the second of two studios we manage in the building so we are very experienced in hosting in this area and have plenty of recommendations for your stay. Washer/dryer facilities on site. Small gym on site. There are for-pay parking lots around the block. This is a major downtown district so, like many cities, there is no parking lot on site and there is possibility of outside noise, which is foreseeable. It is important our guests understand ahead of time that the city is busy, is under construction in certain places, and that noise/commotion is typical on this block just like any block downtown. Understand that we cannot control or change these issues in any way.

name: The Coziest Retreat in N. PB
summary: The Cozy Retreat... This completely remodeled and furnished (Nov. 2014) Large Open Detached studio in North Pacific Beach. Stroll 4 blocks to the beach or less than one block to many restaurants, wine bars, coffee, shopping and nightlife.

neighborhood_overview: Pacific Beach in San Diego is a young beach town with the attraction of the surf and sand by day and the lure of bars and restaurants by night. Located south of La Jolla and north of Mission Beach, this San Diego beach has a popular nightlife scene from dancing to drinking craft beers, which attracts a college-aged and young professionals crowd.  San Diego Pacific Beach is also the ideal spot to catch some waves on your surfboard or bodyboard, while children splash around in the water and build sand castles on the beach. San Diego Pacific Beach visitors are encouraged to try other water sports popular at the beach such as kayaking, sailing and paddle boarding. As for some physical activity on dry land, Pacific Beach has the Ocean Front Walk, which is a boardwalk that stretches parallel to the Pacific Ocean. The boardwalk is lined with shops and restaurants, and it is always filled with beach cruisers, joggers and skateboarders zooming along the strip. Garnet Avenue is another attractio
transit: There is plenty of street parking or you can park in the gated driveway if you are traveling by car. Most everything is walking distance, there is bus transportation nearby and you can Uber/Lyft pretty much anywhere in PB for about $5-10. Getting Around Electric Scooters (BIRD/LIME) and Bicycles (Jump/Uber): Electric scooters and bicycles are everywhere for you to use. They are an easy, fun, convenient way to get around town and best of all you don't have to worry about parking! Just download the app, find a scooter, scan the QR code and go!  Bus Route: Route 9 can be picked up at Ingraham and Garnet. It can take you down Garnet to the beach or in the other direction to SeaWorld and Old Town. Adult $2.50 Trolley: From Old Tow great, inexpensive way of getting around town. Best of all you don't have to find parking!n you can take the trolley into the Seaport Village/Gaslamp Quarter downtown or into Fashion/Mission Valley. I love sharing this wonderful area, and look forward to sending you to a few of my favorite local places.

The 5 things I must have:
1. The love of my husband and family.
2. Everyday is a good day to laugh, be positive and listen.
3. Health - tennis, yoga, walk, hike play golf, sup, kayak,  and  sailing.
 San Diego, is the perfect play land for all the activities we love.
4. Spirituality- path of the inner mind, soul  and always evolving to a more positive being.
5. Adventures of entering  new doors of travels.

Our guest at Airbnb is welcome to our beach home and  our extended family of travelers
from a 4 day stay to a 90 day stay.

 We truly love the interior of the property. We decided to hand select most of the furniture from Living Spaces, because of the quality of the furniture and the design elements for ourselves and guest.  The Peacock and Parrot Sculptures remind us our travels and our famous San Diego Zoo.
We also offer our guest for a separate fee; Raja Yoga and Guided Meditation. We can custom tailor your # YogaRetreatinSanDiego.
Our style of traveling is anything along the water. My  husband and I love sailing, stand up paddle Boards (SUP) snorkeling and he is also a certified padi diver. Now a kite boarder; anything in or above the water. We have travelled to Manzanillo and as far as Switzerland of course many, upon many other countries as well.  

Life is either a daring adventure or nothing." - Helen Keller

Easily accessible lines include: - the 201/202 Super Loop that serve UCSD and the whole UTC area in clockwise and counter-clockwise loops -the 150 Express that serves UCSD and Downtown and connects to the airport bus -the 101 that serves Torrey Pines Golf Course and Reserve and heads to the train station in Solana Beach Car Interstate 5 and State Route 52 are readily accessible in a few minutes' drive, from where you can get to other freeways and just about anywhere in San Diego in about 10-20 minutes without traffic.

name: Organic Garden >> Bohemian California Surf Vibes
summary: BEACH LOCATION! Walk 3 tiny blocks to pristine beaches; soak in salty fresh air + the sun. Wake up to waves and birds softly chirping. Sip coffee or a glass of wine in our organic garden of flowers, fresh herbs & veggies. We have cool bikes and plenty surfboards for rent, free yoga mats + sun shine. Walk to candlelit dining then sleep in our comfy soft bed.  Work out or hygge, we have filtered water, high flow vitamin-C shower and all the amenities you need. 20 minutes to downtown, airport, zoo.
space: Newly refurbished upstairs 1-bedroom apartment in a 4-plex.  This is a quiet North Pacific Beach neighborhood just 3 tiny blocks from the ocean. Beaches are pristine with direct beach access + surf spots!  Our neighbors are quiet and considerate. Apartment is top floor overlooking the garden + private guest parking accessed from the back alley.  Bedroom has comfortable queen bed and wifi. We provide fresh linens, towels, beach towels, shampoo, conditioner, soaps, etc. Forgot sunscreen? We have plenty!  The bathroom tub is newly refinished and sparkly white! We’ve installed a high flow Japanese Vitamin-C filter in the shower with a removable Spa shower head which makes the shower 6’ 5” tall. (No ducking in this shower!)   Living room has A/C, large imported Scandinavian couches and a 50” flat screen with HBO Now, Hulu & Netflix.   Kitchen is well stocked with a Kitchenaide, ice cream makers, pizza stone, herbs, pots, pans, dishes, filtered water, coffees, French press, expresso percolat

neighborhood_overview: North Pacific Beach / Bird Rock is its own charming little beach town nestled between downtown Pacific Beach + La Jolla.  Home to world famous Oscar's (cheap fish tacos* + killer ceviche!) and Tourmaline Surf Park. It's quiet, residential streets holds quaint coffee shops, small bars + restaurants. Each morning, entrepreneurs disguised as beach bums will be typing away on laptops in the open-air cafes while locals walk by with surf boards tucked under their arms.  Grab an acai bowl, smoothie, or fish taco for lunch.  Stroll the boardwalk and stop for a cold craft beer or froze' at one of the endless ocean front bars. The PB boardwalk continues directly into Mission Beach + Bay boardwalk for miles and miles of oceanfront pathways for walkers, runners, bikes and skateboards.  Free volleyball courts and inexpensive catamaran rentals are on the bay as is the world famous Belmont Park (a beach front amusement park with rides, an arcade and a small roller coaster that packs a punch!) Weekend
notes: We aim to be your ultimate San Diego stay!  If it's not listed, please inquire.  We can obtain anything for a fee. This is not a party pad, quiet time is 10PM.  There is a gym, local coffee /sandwich shop, 7-11 and laundry mat steps away on the corner. Early check in or late check out can be arranged for a fee when possible. Just ask us when you book, and we'll do what we can to make your trip awesome!
transit: Public buses run from the airport to Pacific Beach + further up the coast to North County.  The nearest Coaster stops are Ocean Beach or Sorrento Valley.  Uber or Lyft to downtown or San Diego Zoo!  Ubers are plentiful and inexpensive all over San Diego.
access: The entire apartment is yours (with exception of the extra bedroom - our bedroom, that is locked while we are away); the garden access is shared with 3 neighbors.
interaction: We will be available and responsive via phone or Airbnb mail / App for any questions during your stay or recommendations.  We are not on property or available in person.
house_rules: We are happy to invite you into our home, and trust you will treat it as your own during your San Diego holiday.  Being located in a beautiful and peaceful neighbourhood, please keep the noise down after 10 pm, respect our neighbours and their visitors and let´s all have a good time here.  Check in time is after 5 pm, and earlier check in can be arranged if agreed upon prior to arrival.  Check out time is 11 am.  Unfortunately we can not allow any pets here - sorry.   Smoking is not allowed inside the apartment - but feel free to smoke in the garden while of course respecting neighbors and other tenants :-)   The bedroom is set up for a max. of two people, but extra sleeping area can be set up in living room with a queen size air mattress and a large coach if booked accordingly.
host_about:
Easy going, surfers, world travelers, organic gardeners with a joy for life.

We love Airbnb as a gateway for experiences and meeting interesting people.

name: Modern Pacific Beach Flat
summary: This recently-renovated one-bedroom condo is a short walk to the beautiful beaches, food and nightlife of downtown Pacific Beach. Perfect for a couple wanting a quiet haven to relax in comfort after days of surfing, sunbathing, shopping and dining. The condo includes all new appliances and very comfortable furnishings. Only 20 minutes to downtown San Diego.
space: If you're looking for comfort and modern amenities in a great location then this is the place for you! Sleep comfortably on the queen-sized Temperpedic memory foam mattress--if you haven't tried memory foam, you'll be amazed how deeply you'll sleep!  When you're not eating out in the great neighborhood restaurants, cook in our fully-equipped kitchen, with efficient and eco-friendly induction stovetop, dishwasher,  and convection oven. We recommend produce from the various neighborhood farmers markets (Sunday mornings in La Jolla, Tuesday evenings in Pacific Beach)! Relax on the sofa after a long day and watch a movie on the giant flat-screen TV with surround sound. Wifi internet is included.  Enjoy the ocean breezes on our balcony. We're so close to the beach that you can smell the salt air.

neighborhood_overview: Perfect location in a quiet neighborhood near the heart of Pacific Beach just 2 blocks from the ocean and 2 blocks from the hip restaurants and cafes on Cass St. It's a great launching point for surfing, sunbathing, dining and shopping in PB but quiet enough to feel like a retreat. Within 4 blocks from home you can: • Do sunrise yoga overlooking the ocean in Palisades Park  • Eat amazing tacos at Oscar's • Get a fantastic morning coffee or smoothie...or enjoy an evening cocktail in the cafes on Cass St.  • Surf, swim, stroll or sunbathe at the beach
notes: We've made our home a place of comfort for ourselves, and we want you to enjoy it too. If you like to cook, help yourself to our collection of spices and condiments. We have lots of great books and some musical instruments for you to respectfully enjoy.
transit: You could stay in Pacific Beach and enjoy all the great beaches, restaurants and shopping in walking distance from our flat (which is quite a lot!). Local bike rentals are a popular way to explore Pacific Beach! There is a bus stop on our block that connects to the city's public transportation system. It's 30 minutes by bus from our door to the Old Town Transit Station, which has further connections all over the city. To explore San Diego's other neighborhoods and attractions a car is recommended but not required. We have one available off-street parking spot and there is plentiful street parking. Adjacent neighborhoods and attractions include: • Elegant shopping, dining, art museums, and seal and sea lion viewing in La Jolla • Cute coffee shops and lunch spots in hidden gem Bird Rock neighborhood • Unparalleled sunset hiking in Sunset Cliffs and Torrey Pines parks • Bohemian beach-side shops and retro Amusement Park in Mission Beach (a lovely 1-hour beach stroll from our flat)
access: Coin operated washer and dryer in building.  Wifi and television with AppleTV, Netflix, Hulu Plus, Amazon Prime, and HBO Now.    Nearby bike and surfboard rental.
interaction: We'll make arrangements by phone and the flat will be ready for you when you arrive. You'll have it all to yourselves, but can reach us by email or text if issues arise. The doors have key-code electric locks that we control remotely, so you never have to worry about losing your key or getting locked out!
house_rules: This is a residential building with families so we ask that guests keep noise to a minimum late at night. The space is suitable for one or two small dogs, but the building prohibits large dogs (>20lbs) in this condo unit. Dogs must be on a leash whenever they are inside the building.

summary: For business or pleasure, this Southern California coastline spot offers beautiful beaches, plenty of art, and outdoor adventure! Our garden view suite is located walking distance to several beaches, Seal Rock, and a variety of cultural activities, including the San Diego Museum of Contemporary Art. Take a peaceful stroll down Coast Blvd. for an ocean view or move closer into town for quaint cafes, restaurants, and shops. • Living area with comfy King bed • Kitchenette with cookware + dishware • Gas fireplace for the cool nights • FREE high-speed Wi-Fi • Access to a lovely Outdoor Pool • Daily housekeeping service included • 5-minute walk to the beach, scenic walk down Coastal Blvd • Reserve for Sunday brunch at the onsite NINE-TEN Restaurant and Bar • 24-hour convenient check-in desk

The onsite NINE-TEN restaurant offers a variety of food choices with a focus on California cuisine. Dine indoors or alfresco on NINE-TEN’s sidewalk patio or outdoor terrace offering glimpses of the ocean. Our elegant and bright 385 to 390 sq. ft  LIVING AREA features 1 King bed. Just a short drive away from this stunning destination, world-class attractions like the San Diego Zoo and SeaWorld guarantee unforgettable vacation memories.
notes: • You will love the garden courtyard view and the 5-minute walk to the beach • Housekeeping 2 times/day keeps your room fresh and tidy • Enjoy the calm of the ocean waves, take in beautiful seaside views at Point La Jolla on the way to Goldfish Point Cafe • While there is no fitness centre on-site, enjoy access to a neighbouring gym for a fee • Guest rooms, suites and bathrooms will undergo renovations, starting in November 2019 and completed in March 2019 • There is no on-site self-parking, though valet parking is available for $30/night/car • Upon your arrival, you'll be asked for a $100 USD/night damage deposit for incidentals
house_rules: • Check-in is available after 4pm. You will pick up your keys from the onsite guest service team upon arrival. • Check-out time is before 12pm. You will be asked to provide photo identification upon check-in. Any reservation made under false pretenses will forfeit all payments, and guests will be escorted from the property.

Make the world your home & Leavetown with us!

We look forward to hearing from you!

Your Leavetown Team

neighborhood_overview: Banker’s Hill is a beautiful, quiet and elegant old neighborhood, great for leisurely strolls (just a three-block walk to a food mart and cafe), and centrally located near downtown, the Gaslamp District and  Convention Center, San Diego International Airport, Balboa Park with its museums, theaters, outdoor activities and world-famous zoo, as well as the many clubs and restaurants of the Hillcrest District, Little Italy and historic Old Town.
notes: Suitable for one or two persons. No pets, no smoking, no maid service provided, no parties over 6 persons, no loud music. Check-in time is 3 pm and check-out time is 11am. Street parking only.
transit: You are just one block from a bus route that will take you to all parts of the city, connecting with trolley lines, one of which will take you to the U.S. border should you want to spend the afternoon in Mexico (don't forget your passport). And Uber and Lyft are inexpensive ways to take advantage of San Diego's main tourism sites.
access: After entering the main gate, you will have access to the entire guesthouse and adjoining patio and gardens. There are no stairs and only one half-step to enter.
interaction: A husband and wife have owned the main property (built in 1926) for over 45 years. He is a retired philosophy professor and antiques dealer and she is an artist and retired docent at the San Diego Museum of Art. Their friend and Airbnb manager, Shirley, will be your contact. She will check with you beforehand to determine if you have any special requests, will greet you on arrival, will always be available by phone, text or email to address any concerns you may have, and will make sure your stay will be an unforgettably delightful experience.

neighborhood_overview: I love how quiet our neighborhood is! not so easy to find in SD, as there are numerous airports and freeways everywhere. Parking is free and easy- you never have to 'hunt' for a spot. Neighborhood is quiet and diverse- a lot of Vietnamese and Mexican families here. Less crime here than in La Jolla, according to SDPD website. We often walk at night, and have never been disturbed or harassed while doing so. Our neighborhood is perched on the edge of Tecolote Canyon, the mouth of which is right at Mission Bay; as a result, the prevailing westerly breeze comes off the ocean, across Mission Bay, into Tecolote Canyon and filters thru the neighborhood, which is why most houses here do not have A/C.
notes: If you're looking to walk to bars, restaurants, and nightlife, this may not be the spot for you; however, if you want a clean, quiet, affordable space with easy parking and don't mind short drives to attractions, this is the best.
transit: Close to all SD attractions without the big price tag and attendant hassles (noise/congestion/parking issues). We're close to the (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) freeways, but can't hear any of them.
access: Shared laundry facilities (9am-9pm), WIFI Network,  large backyard with fruit trees, outdoor grill.
interaction: I like a nice chat, but am busy and will most likely leave you alone unless you'd like to chat with me.
house_rules: No smoking inside apartment, no loud noise after 9 pm (we're working people here), no pets, extra guests, drugs or excessive drinking. Shoes off inside house.
host_about: i'm quiet, respectful, and will chat with you but more than likely will leave you alone. i'm a mixed race person (asian and american). i live in the house with Serbian gal pal (she speaks Serbian and English). We're quiet non smokers and light drinkers.

Whether your idea of the perfect vacation is tanning on the beach, surfing, sailing, water skiing, shopping, bar hopping or sight seeing, San Diego is an ideal destination. Mission Bay is the center of water activities in San Diego and from your vacation rental you can easily arrange to rent anything from kayaks to speed boats for your adventuring needs. Mission Beach offers surfing year round with larger waves in the winter, but cleaner conditions and warmer water in the summer. Be sure to check timetables and schedules, and plan your routes in advance. For bus schedules and information, visit Metropolitan Transit System. summary: This lovely east-facing bedroom comes with an en suite bathroom.
description: This lovely east-facing bedroom comes with an en suite bathroom. The Kitchen: We welcome you into our kitchen for food preparation and eating during meal times, and can provide cookware and table settings. We can provide limited refrigerator room for you too, as well as full use of cooktop, oven, and microwave. As you can appreciate, because we are a working family with potentially other guests staying, the shared kitchen space is not for guest parties with non-resident family members and friends without prior permission. The same can be said for our backyard patio sitting area and fire pit. We enjoy meeting new people and learning about their lives. This is our home, so you'll see a lot of us if you like! Our home is in a safe family neighborhood one block from the walking/biking trails and peacefulness of  Los Penasquitos Canyon Preserve. Our home is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and big groups. (Please consider the practicality and saf
neighborhood_overview: Our home is in a safe family neighborhood one block from the walking/biking trails and peacefulness of  Los Penasquitos Canyon Preserve. Our home is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and big groups. (Please consider the practicality and safety of younger children around our large dogs and swimming pool.) We are approximately 15-30 minutes from several beautiful beaches.
notes: Resident Furry Pets: Our two dogs and cat live downstairs. Apollo is an older black lab, and Willow is a younger rescued lab mix. They are large and 'affectionately gregarious', but part of our family and enjoy interactions with guests. Please consider this, as not everyone is comfortable in close proximity to large active dogs that are potentially excitable and jumpy. They will frequently be in the kitchen and family room areas. Our quiet cat 'Jackie O' resides mostly in the garage. We also keep a couple of laying hens that stay in a backyard coop. They enjoy our compostable food scraps! We appreciate you respecting our home, and look forward to helping you enjoy your stay in lovely San Diego any way we can!
transit: There is not access to public transportation in our neighborhood. Rental car/Uber/Lyft is recommended for guests, as we are approximately a 20 minute drive to downtown San Diego.

neighborhood_overview: University Heights is a neighborhood in Central San Diego, California centered on Park Boulevard and Adams Avenue, a great and peaceful neighborhood located between Hillcrest and North Park. It has its own personality with a mix of Craftsman bungalows and houses and laid-back eateries and hip bars for food. Its small retail area is at the north end of Park Boulevard where it turns into Adams Avenue. The name University" (both for the neighborhood and nearby University Avenue) comes from a plan in the 1880s to build a university in the area. It came to be the State Normal School
notes: which evolved into what is now San Diego State University. That's why the word "university" is prevalent in this part of town
transit: even though there is no university around.  It has some interesting history. On the far northern edge of the neighborhood
access: at the scenic rim of Mission Valley

name: King Palms (Private Room)
summary: Find your Funk & Groove in Ocean Beach! Laid back beach to hang out like a local. This small beach town is a favorite among locals who spend their days surfing, sun bathing around the pier, hanging out in their vintage VW vans, and strolling through the many surf shops, taco stands and antique malls. Ocean Beach offers the pitch perfect throw-back groovy vibe of vintage SoCal, coupled with friendly locals, great dining, and a vibrant night life scene.
space: Influences from Spain, Italy and other Mediterranean countries combined with a compassion for the ocean has given birth to this beautiful home. Finished with high-end appliances and marine grade hardwood floors, this home away from home provides you with an unforgettable experience that is one block to the Pacific Ocean. Rooftop deck with ocean views and Jacuzzi (Great for catching the Seaworld fireworks every night in the summer). Gourmet kitchen to indulge in or hit a local hotspot. neighborhood_overview: Find your Funk & Groove in Ocean Beach If you’re looking for a laid back beach to hang out like a local, look no further than Ocean Beach. This small beach town is a favorite among locals who spend their days surfing, sun bathing around the pier, hanging out in their vintage VW vans, and strolling through the many surf shops, taco stands and antique malls. Ocean Beach offers the pitch perfect throw-back groovy vibe of vintage SoCal, coupled with friendly locals, great dining, and a vibrant night life scene. Nestled between the San Diego River and the hills of Point Loma, Ocean Beach is perfect for surfers to enjoy the waves created by jetties. The beach is also friendly for swimmers, sun bathers, even dogs too!
notes: Sorry, no pets inside the house unless really small and quite ones, but a decent sized gated back yard will accommodate most animals. Important: This is a private bedroom with shared bathroom of a 3 bedroom / 3 bathroom home. Other booking options include individual rooms or the entire home. Please check other listings to confirm prices and availability.
transit: The easiest option is to rent a car, so you can roam freely through the vast and various San Diego regions. But if you’re looking to save a buck or be eco-friendly, plan to make the most of San Diego’s convenient and easy public transport options. There are plenty of lines and routes that are serviced throughout San Diego. Be sure to check timetables and schedules, and plan your routes in advance. For bus schedules and information, visit Metropolitan Transit System. For bus schedules and information for San Diego's North County, visit Breeze.
access: Access to all of the common areas
interaction: Let me know your dates of arrival and I'll try to show you around
host_about: I like adventure and richly varying experiences! Keeps the mind kickin' in overdrive.... Kitesurfed in the Canary Islands...Canyon Swung in the Swiss Alps (Interlaken)... Cocooned by mother nature in Iceland...Toured through war torn Bosnia, Serbia, and the Baltic States...Scuba dived in Cozumel...Shark cage diving in South Africa with great whites...Dirt biked up the Greek island of Corfu to see the clouds push over Albania...Bought a condo in Jaco, Coasta Rico...Experienced the Hammams in Istanbul...last but not least, partied in Ibiza till dawn.

name: Downtown, Spacious and Bright with Balcony!
summary: Parc Suites San Diego is a Victorian Manor, lovingly restored into what is now one of the most unique and comfortable lodging facilities within one minute of downtown San Diego's exciting Gaslamp District. We offer value pricing and specialize in Extended Stay housing. Parc Suites maintains full time staff to insure units and grounds are in top condition. Each unit is designed to host 1-2 guests maximum to insure that our tranquil environment is always intact. Super Quiet, Super Central.
space: Parc Suites San Diego is a Victorian Manor, lovingly restored into what is now one of the most unique and comfortable lodging facilities within one minute of downtown San Diego's exciting Gaslamp District.  Parc Suites is located in San Diego’s largest Historic District.  It is the former home and health retreat of one of San Diego’s most prominent citizens, Dr. J.M. Peebles.  Dr. Peebles traveled the globe back in the late 1800’s but always returned home to what is now Parc Suites San Diego.  While staying at Parc Suites San Diego, you will be a 5-minute drive from Coronado Island's white sand beaches, world famous Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, Sea World, San Diego’s championship golf courses, San Diego International Airport, and much more.     The home and surrounding grounds have been converted into ten individual apartment suites.  Each suite features fully equipped kitchens, private entrances and separate seating areas. notes: or Sherman's Heights". He purchased the land in June 1867
transit: a month after Alonzo Horton (Horton Plaza) purchased land for New Town San Diego (now downtown). Sherman Heights is the largest historic district in San Diego and features outstanding Victorian Architecture including the Villa Montezuma which is only a few blocks away from Parc Suites San Diego."
access: Guests staying at Parc Suites San Diego are sure to have a great nights sleep as we invest in the finest bedding and linens. Parc Suites San Diego is an extremely quiet complex as we have strict limits on the number of guests that we allow in each private apartment. We never overload our suites as we do not want to compromise the tranquil environment that we have worked hard to achieve since we opened in 2007.
interaction: Great access to all freeways, less than 2 minute drive and you will be on most major freeways! Great location for Public Transportation. Bus Stop within 3 blocks and Trolley stop within 5 blocks. Walmart Neighborhood Grocery market is located only 3 blocks away. Perfect location for bicycling or trail jogging/running. Balboa Park off road Mountain Bike trails accessible by bicycle within a 10-15 minute bike ride.
house_rules: All guests at Parc Suites San Diego enjoy a full, private apartment suite. Nice shaded garden areas with seating and a guaranteed, gated parking space. Guest interaction Parc Suites San Diego offers a 24 hour service line. We, also, maintain a full time maintenance staff to insure that all units and common areas are kept in perfect condition.

name: Fantastic Location!  Spacious and Elegant!
summary: Parc Suites San Diego is a Victorian Manor, lovingly restored into what is now one of the most unique and comfortable lodging facilities within one minute of downtown San Diego's exciting Gaslamp District. We offer value pricing and specialize in Extended Stay housing. Parc Suites maintains full time staff to insure units and grounds are in top condition. Each unit is designed to host 1-2 guests maximum to insure that our tranquil environment is always intact. Super Quiet, Super Central.
space: Parc Suites San Diego is a Victorian Manor, lovingly restored into what is now one of the most unique and comfortable lodging facilities within one minute of downtown San Diego's exciting Gaslamp District. Parc Suites is located in San Diego’s largest Historic District. It is the former home and health retreat of one of San Diego’s most prominent citizens, Dr. J.M. Peebles. Dr. Peebles traveled the globe back in the late 1800’s but always returned home to what is now Parc Suites San Diego. While staying at Parc Suites San Diego, you will be a 5-minute drive from Coronado Island's white sand beaches, world famous Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, Sea World, San Diego’s championship golf courses, San Diego International Airport, and much more. The home and surrounding grounds have been converted into ten individual apartment suites. Each suite features fully equipped kitchens, private entrances and separate seating areas. The ample outdoor space provides lots of outdoor seating and relaxation

There is a large shopping center nearby with parking available. Uber and Lyft drivers are usually waiting in the shopping center and always arrive within less than 5 minutes. At the beach there are lots of bike rental places. Mission Bay and the beach boardwalk are great places to bike ride and these places are only 15 minutes away. Buses are available nearby. host_about: I am proud to be a Superhost. I have a beautiful home in a very central location of San Diego that I like to share with other travelers. I am a world traveler and am fortunate that I can travel a lot. I have been a traveler all of my life and I love to visit other countries, see fascinating places, meet the people and learn about their cultures. I am fortunate to live in such a beautiful place as San Diego and be close to the beach, mountains and desert and all that Southern California has to offer. My home is only about 15 minutes away from all the major attractions in San Diego. I take pride in providing a very comfortable and clean place for my guests as you can see from my reviews. As a traveling guest I treat your home as I would my own, with utmost respect.

name: Ocean Haven- Luxurious Studio  AC, Spa, Zen Garden
summary: Ocean Haven is a luxury studio hideaway for two located in North Pacific Beach. We are located just a 5 minute stroll from the beach as well as within walking distance of restaurants, shopping and markets. As the guest quarters for our private residence, this 500 sq.  ft. retreat features a queen size bed, AC, spa-style bathroom with jetted tub. The exotic Asian inspired designed studio opens onto a beautifully landscaped private Zen Garden. Outdoor living...furnished for dining and relaxing.
space: This unique North Pacific Beach neighborhood (at the southern border of La Jolla) is close to all yet quietly removed from the hubs of activity.  It's the perfect sanctuary to rejuvenate one's mind, body and spirit. Rinse off after a day at the beach in the outdoor shower area. Barbecue at home & dine al fresco or take a boardwalk stroll at sunset to one of our many nearby restaurants.

notes: Sorry but no pets allowed. This is a 100% non-smoking house. PLEASE NOTE: Ocean Haven does NOT HAVE A KITCHEN. However, we've provided a mini refrigerator, microwave, coffee maker, tea kettle, toaster and dining dishes and utensils.
transit: A car is not really necessary as Uber and Lyft are readily available. You can also rent bicycles or scooters by signing up with the various companies providing those services. There is also a bus stop located 1/2 block away.

interaction: Although Ocean Haven is just next-door to our private residence, we respect your privacy completely but will be available if needed for questions or advice. Please note that this is a quiet neighborhood and parties or loud gatherings are NOT permitted, (think AHHHH, you'll get a restful night's sleep too)! There are times when we will be traveling ourselves & unavailable. In those instances, my local Co-host, Cori, will always be a helpful call or text away.
host_about:
Most of my adult life I spent dreaming about living by the Ocean. After 32 years living in the deserts of Phoenix my dream came true. For 18 years now, I've enjoyed living and working in the vacation paradise of Pacific Beach. Now I share my beautiful space with other like-minded dreamers.  Having lived in Thailand and the Philippines as a child, I have a penchant for things Asian. After 20 years as an interior designer I retired from the profession and became the owner of a local business. It's been my pleasure to design Ocean Haven which reflects my love of exotic beauty. Here's hoping you enjoy my artistic vision and wishing you a taste of the tranquility and rejuvenating effect that comes from living your dream!
Liz

There is a bus stop one block from the condo, and ride sharing services are affordable and convenient to downtown, Sea World, Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, Ocean Beach, La Jolla and other locations central in San Diego (a typical Uber fair to the beach or Sea World would be about 5$, about 10-15$ to downtown (airport), La Jolla, Ocean Beach, Zoo, etc). Car to Go also has many vehicles available in the area.  La Jolla features dynamic shoreline, a marine sanctuary seals, and sometimes whale sitings from shore! Downtown San Diego offers some unique neighborhoods, such a Little Italy and the Gaslamp, museums and art galleries, night clubs, a great selection of restaurants, and unique a sea port. Balboa park is also nearby, home to 15 museums, the zoo, restaurants and plenty of sites to see!

notes: Off Street covered parking for one car is included in the rental rate.  It is good for a compact car. With the use of fans, it keeps the condo cool most of the year.  It can still get hot during a heat wave. FYI... Only about 1% of the properties in Pacific Beach have central Air Conditioning if they have any Air Conditioning at all. A pack & play can be delivered for a $25 fee.   A pack & plan and high chair can be delivered for $35.

name: Modern Moroccan Beach Cottage
summary: Welcome to the Moroccan Beach Cottage -- where contemporary interior design meets Morocco by the beach. One bedroom suite has a Moroccan salon that can double as a second bedroom with two additional sleeping spaces. Located in a quintessential Southern California beach community: a short five blocks to the beach and three blocks to a gourmet organic market, coffee shop, wine bar, and craft brewery.  This is a stylish, romantic oasis. We're here to help you have an extraordinary stay!
space: Light-filled, one bedroom suite features a Moroccan salon/living room that can double as a second bedroom with two additional sleeping spaces.  The bedroom features a designer Crate & Barrel bed with new Sealy Beautyrest mattress and desk space.  The cottage is decorated with new and vintage Moroccan design elements throughout.   Outdoors, there are two seating areas to enjoy the ocean breeze and eat or drink coffee or check email while sitting under mature avocado trees.  Cook al fresco California style with the outdoor kitchen, complete with sink, burners and a grill.   In the kitchenette indoors, there is also a microwave, small refrigerator and electric kettle.  We, of course, supply ample cooking utensils, dishes, pots, etc.  And we are always happy to handle special requests!

name: Cozy Cottages by the Cove
summary: This cozy one bedroom beach cottage is in the perfect quiet location, minutes from the ocean and close to restaurants and galleries on Prospect St.  There is laundry on site, wireless internet connection, and cable TV.
space: The location is ideal for swimming, snorkeling, diving, surfing, walking along the coast, viewing seals, golfing, kayaking, tennis, whale watching, and biking. There are grocery stores within walking distance. A 20 minute commute from the San Diego airport. A bus stops one block away which can take you to the UTC shopping mall and UCSD. Other nearby attractions include the Birch Aquarium, the San Diego Zoo, Sea World, the Wild Animal Park, and the museums of Balboa Park. La Jolla has the perfect mild climate all year round. The Cove is a wonderful spot for swimmers and there are different facing beaches for surfers. The village is attractive with its wonderful restaurants, galleries and shops.

name: Cozy Room Blocks From Beach & Bay
summary: If you are looking for the perfect San Diego getaway blocks from the ocean and Mission Bay, look no further. We are offering a relaxing vacation with a private room, clean full bathroom, and walking distance to many shops and restaurants.
space: We are offering space, comfort and privacy within walking distance of one of the best beaches and bays of San Diego. We love the Pacific Beach lifestyle: walking along the beach, cruising main street, and enjoying all the delicious food that PB has to offer. The area is quiet and safe, making you feel like home. We love meeting new people and look forward to your stay with us.
description: If you are looking for the perfect San Diego getaway blocks from the ocean and Mission Bay, look no further. We are offering a relaxing vacation with a private room, clean full bathroom, and walking distance to many shops and restaurants. We are offering space, comfort and privacy within walking distance of one of the best beaches and bays of San Diego. We love the Pacific Beach lifestyle: walking along the beach, cruising main street, and enjoying all the delicious food that PB has to offer. The area is quiet and safe, making you feel like home. We love meeting new people and look forward to your stay with us. You will have access to your own private bathroom and cozy bedroom. We are happy to share the common areas including the living room, dining room, and fully equipped kitchen. We ask that you be respectful and clean up after yourself- treating our home as your own. We both have regular jobs and tend to be fairly busy during the week and weekend but we can be reached by phone. We
neighborhood_overview: You will find the house to be ideally located, within 10 minute walk to the bay and 15 to the beach. There are a lot of shops and restaurants within walking distance and we will gladly share our favorite places. Ralphs, Sprouts, Vons and Trader Joes are all walking distance. It's a great place for a healthy lifestyle and you will see a lot of people surfing, running on the beach, biking, hiking and just enjoying the SD lifestyle and weather. Sea World is a 10 minute drive from our place. You are also within walking distance of the Pacific Beach nightlife (Garnet avenue is a few blocks away and the beach front is 1 mile away).
notes: We would like to make sure that you have all the information you need before you make a reservation so please feel free to reach out to us with any questions you may have.
transit: Street parking in PB is hit or miss. Plenty of spaces during the day on weekdays, but in the evening and much of the time on weekends nearby parking can be very difficult though not impossible. We do have a single off-street spot we rent out for a modest charge. Other methods of transportation: There are several bus stops within a couple of blocks (exact change of $2.25 one way), including the 30, which will take you downtown or to La Jolla in about 30 minutes.  There are several bike rental shops all walking distance. They usually cost 15-20 for the whole day.  Uber Black Car, Uber XL and UberX, and Lyft are super common in the Pacific Beach area. They will typically be able to pick you up from the house with less than 5 minutes notice.
access: You will have access to your own private bathroom and cozy bedroom. We are happy to share the common areas including the living room, dining room, and fully equipped kitchen. We ask that you be respectful and clean up after yourself- treating our home as your own.
interaction: We both have regular jobs and tend to be fairly busy during the week and weekend but we can be reached by phone. We will be happy to share our recommendations and tips, helping make your stay a memorable one! On weekends, we will most likely be around the house, running errands and relaxing.
house_rules: - No guests or visits - Please remove shoes when inside house and brush off any sand before entering -  - Check-in is after 3PM - Check out is before 11am - On weekdays: Please be mindful that we work and wake up early -  - We have a few requirements for the convenience of future guests: -  - We love to accommodate early check-ins and late check-outs when we can. If you feel you need more time please make a request at least 24 hrs in advance and we will check our schedule to see if it is possible. If it is not possible, please honor the check-in time of 3:00 p.m. and the check-out time of 11:00 am. This give us time to make the suite nice, clean and attractive for the next guest. -  - Thank you :)

host_about: Hi there, thanks for checking out my place!  Man, Airbnb is the best, huh?  Hosting to the people (fist pump)!  I've stayed in my share of hostels, bed n breakfasts and hotels/motels.  While I don't serve up any vegemite, I'm loving having a li'l BnB of my own.  Like you, probably, I love to travel. When I'm at home, I do home stuff like work, spend time with friends and generally enjoy all the amazingness that is San Diego.  I moved here in 2009 from Salt Lake City basically on a whim - no job or anything - with my dog and a full U-Haul truck, and it all worked out!  Also, as it turns out, Bernie (pictured) is a total sun worshipper, SD is this dog's natural habitat!  Have a great day!  :)

host_has_profile_pic: Molly's Rentals is a short term vacation rental company that provides a personalized customer experience to both our guests and owners. One of our team members is always available should you have any questions or issues during your stay. Our properties are well maintained and we always take our clients suggestions to heart.  Molly McCrackin grew up in San Diego and has been managing short term vacation rentals in the beach area since 2008. The company has grown over the years, but the service and attention to detail has stayed the same. We look forward to having you stay!
host_identity_verified: PLEASE NOTE BEFORE BOOKING: NO SMOKING - All of our properties are non-smoking (this includes marijuana) -  If you smoke, you will need to go to the street.   A $50 fine will be assessed to those that smoke ON the property.  A minimum of a $400 fine will be assessed for those that smoke INSIDE the house. This rental agreement includes a Zero Tolerance Policy for noise disturbances, over occupancy, or house parties. name: Downtown Artist's Loft in Little Italy
summary: Located in the charming neighborhood of Little Italy, the artist's loft is an architectural gem that features:  +Free welcome drink   +Free locally roasted coffee  +Free Wifi  +Malin + Goetz bath products  +Parachute linens + towels  +Tuft & Needle mattress  +Walking distance to the city’s best restaurants +Parking spot available - $10/day
space: The loft is a welcoming space located in the heart of San Diego’s beloved Little Italy neighborhood. Housed on the third floor in a design-focused building by a local architect, the apartment is extremely unique with 20-ft ceilings, massive vintage windows, and industrial touches. There is a compact kitchenette area with a mini fridge with a complimentary welcome drink, reverse-osmosis drinking water, Fellow electric kettle, Chemex coffee maker, and complimentary local coffee. There are not cooking capabilities, but we do have serving ware and silverware for enjoying snacks you pick up from the local farmers market. A few important notes:  — As expected with city living, street noises are often heard in this unit. There are a couple of restaurants and bars across the street which tend to play loud music into the night. Please keep this in mind if you're a light sleeper, and we are also happy to provide earplugs. — The space is accessed via a three-story flight stairs, and there is no e

Housed on the third floor in a design-focused building by a local architect, the apartment is extremely unique with 20-ft ceilings, massive vintage windows, and industrial touches. neighborhood_overview: Little Italy is one of San Diego’s most charming neighborhoods. It’s known to locals at the epicenter of the best culinary hot spots, so if you like to eat - you’re in the right place. We work in the restaurant and hospitality industry, and we are more than happy to give our guests recommendations for the best San Diego has to offer for every palate. Little Italy is extremely centrally located and will be a breeze to get around to other neighborhoods and attractions. It’s a 5-minute drive from the airport, an easy walk/drive to the Convention Center, and is 5-15 minutes away from popular destinations like Balboa Park, Gaslamp, North Park, Hillcrest, Sea World, Coronado, & Pacific Beach.
transit: The loft is conveniently located in the heart of San Diego’s Little Italy neighborhood. The area is extremely walkable (and bikeable) — and you’ll be just a few blocks away from the some of the best restaurants in the city & a few blocks away from the gorgeous San Diego bay front. Parking in Little Italy can be a bit tricky/expensive (as with any city), but we have one parking spot available to reserve for a minimal daily fee ($10 per day). The spots are shared between all of our units and priority is given to whoever reserves first - just inquire if you have any questions on this. If you don’t have a car, you can easily get around by bike, Uber or taxi as well as the trolley (the nearest station is just a few blocks away).
interaction: We live next door, and are available anytime during your stay. Our goal is to make sure you have a wonderful San Diego trip.
host_about: Colorado native living in sunny San Diego. Love to travel, hike, & eat!

name: Featured on the Tiny House Hunters Show!
summary: Featured as the “International House” on the show Tiny House Hunters, The Carriage House has touched hundreds of people with its charm and amazing energy. It was hand selected by the TV show producers as one of the most unforgettable vacation homes in San Diego. It showcases mahogany floors and gorgeous tall wood beam ceilings and is located in the affluent Mission Hill District of San Diego. It is within 0.5 miles to the top restaurants, the beach is a 10 min drive, and downtown is 4 miles.
space: We’ve had tons of great reviews, but the one comment that keeps coming up is how our attention to detail reflects our love for the place. The Carriage House is not just your run of the mill place, but is an actual part of the vacation experience itself. See for yourself in the Tiny House Hunters advertisement (URL HIDDEN) It has always been our goal to create a unique space for travelers and to utilize a portion of the proceeds to help unwanted horses. We’re going on five years now, and have helped many horses including eight wild mustangs that were taken from their native land. Because of guest like you, those 8 horses now roam thousands of acres in Idaho. Formerly a home for the horse groom's family, The Carriage House, was recently remodeled by a local architect who transformed this gem into a spacious one bedroom/one bath that is now perfect for anyone who appreciates modern comfort and artistic design.  Features include a king sized signature Heavenly Bed with amazing pillows and

neighborhood_overview: Mission Hills is the oldest and most centrally located neighborhood in San Diego. The Carriage House is surrounded by 100 year old trees and multi-million dollar homes that making walking around the neighborhood a real treat.
notes: Luckily we have a very talented Interior Designer in the family. Our goal with the design was modern comfort, history, and to create a worldly feel so everyone feels welcome. We'd love to hear your feedback :)
transit: Coffee shops, a small market, and a yoga studio is right around the corner. Within a half mile are some of the best restaurants in all of San Diego. To catch the trolley, head down the hill to Old Town (less than 2 miles). Whole Foods and Trader Joe's is about 5 minutes away.
access: This is your own stand alone house. The owners do not live on the property.
interaction: We speak with our guests on the phone and love meeting them if they are available.
house_rules: There is a kind size (amazingly comfortable) bed and we provide a camping cot with linens or a pack and play for a child. We can accommodate, at most, one couple traveling with one child. No candles allowed but we have provided numerous flameless candles.
host_about: We are an energy executive and a former race horse jockey and we both love horses. We have always dreamed of owning a home like this and sharing it with others as a way to fund horse rescues. 10% of the proceeds go to horse rescues and the remaining profit gets put back into the business to create more opportunities for saving horses. With the talented hands of a designer we have brought to you a home that is a true work of art. The energy as soon as you walk in the door is overwhelming. And your money is going for something greater than us. The survival of horses.....we hope you love The Carriage House.

name: Oceanfront Oasis with view of SEA
summary: View the ocean from your bed!  My family and I would absolutely love to have you as our guest. Ocean Front, remodeled, beautiful beach front studio.  Parking included. Walking distance to all boutiques and restaurants!  Surfboard & bike rentals steps away.  This unit is for 2 adults, possibly with a small child.  The 2nd bed is actually the large sectional couch shown in the pictures.
space: My parents built this beautiful complex here on Spray Street in the 1940's. The old beach charm is still alive here with original wood rafters, flooring, and built ins. I have however completely remodeled all the kitchens and bathrooms. We've upgraded everything with super fast wifi. You'll be able to stream movies for your kids, check in with the office or play video games. Truly a flashback to the era of muscle cars, classy women, and beach glamour. Enjoy.

neighborhood_overview: Ocean Beach is very bohemian.  Once you arrive you will not need a car as everything is within walking distance.  Be sure to visit the O.B People's food store, the farmer's market on Wednesday, and tide pools under the pier.  There are multiple shops, restaurants and breweries nearby.
notes: Please know that this is all one room.  There is a full kitchen and full bathroom.  But everybody sleeps in the same room.  There is a queen bed and a couch.  The couch does not pull out but has plenty of sleeping room.
transit: Free parking.  Bikes for rent across the street.  15 dollar cab ride to downtown san diego.  Bike riding distance to Sea World.  Ocean front.  Can't beat it.
access: We have free parking directly below your unit in the garage.  Please note:  if you  have a large SUV it probably won't fit and at point you will be parking on the street.  We have upgraded our wifi so that it is very fast.  We use Apple T.V and have smart T.V. s  which you may access with your private codes and/or subscriptions.  The downstairs patio area is available to all guests on site.  There is a propane grill, comfortable seating and lighting.  We have beach chairs, umbrellas,  boogie boards and sand toys available.  There is also a washer and dryer on site free for you to use.  Surf lessons, bike rentals and volley ball courts are right across the street.
interaction: I check in via phone/text a few times before the projected arrival date. I also guide guest through the parking and security locks on the unit.  This ensures safe/fast entry into our unit.  We use a keyless system.  The code changes with each guest.   You must use the air bnb app to contact me.  It is the only way for me to make sure you are the person who actually booked the unit.  Please be aware, the code will not be given out without the app.
house_rules: No smoking tobacco inside the unit.  No smoking pot on property.  No extra guests.  These units are not meant for a ton of people. Quiet hours from 10 pm till 9 am. No Parties!!!!  Anyone throwing a party will be evicted immediately. Sorry, no pets or animals of any kind.  We have pet friendly units available.  Look under Oceanfront Dog Mahal and Moondoggies Beach Retreat.
host_about: I was born and raised in Ocean Beach. I lived at Spray Street until I was married.  Both my husband and I went to Point Loma High School which is just over the hill from this property.  We want to share this beautiful place with you and hope that you will treat it as you would your own home.  We consider it our home and hope to retire there someday.  In the meantime please enjoy the magic of Ocean Beach.
