name: La Jolla Gem w/ Pool+Gym UCSD Beach
summary: Location! Location! Location! Welcome to this cozy and elegant La Jolla condo within walking distance to plenty of shops including multiple grocery stores (Whole Foods, Ralphs and Trader Joe's) and an AMC Movie Theater. The condo is only 2 miles to the the beach (La Jolla Shores) and is only 1.5 miles to the newly renovated UTC mall which has a variety of fancy and causal restaurants.
space: Enjoy this inviting and cozy condo as if you've never left home! The large comfy couch will be ideal after a day of exploring this beautiful city! A full kitchen is available with all the necessary pots and pans you need for cooking. There is also a decent size patio with a sliding door. The complex is also very quite and well maintained.  This is a bottom floor unit so there are no stairs.

neighborhood_overview: Del Cerro is an up and coming neighborhood.  There is a a nice gastropub with an excellent beer selection just a mile down the road next to an amazing local grocery store full of inexpensive produce and a variety of healthy snacks and nutrition products.  San Diego State University is just close enough to enjoy a lot of nearby fast food restaurants but far away enough to avoid the noise and traffic.  Only 10 miles away from some of the most beautiful beaches anywhere, enjoy San Diego's amazing weather and gorgeous sunsets whenever you like. The beach offers a smorgasbord of activities with dedicated bike trails, kayaking, paddle boarding, parasailing, and of course sun bathing! My favorite part of our neighborhood is our proximity to the Mission Trails Regional Park(2.2mi).  Over 6800 acres of rugged terrain and a multitude of trails perfect for hiking, mountain biking, and mountain climbing for all skill levels.  The park boasts of San Diego's highest peak Cowles Mountain (1594') offe
notes: Lots of free parking! No parking restrictions either. Netflix Amazon Prime Roku Lots of free apps Jacuzzi operational hours are on the weekends by request
transit: By car, we are next to the 8 freeway, off the College Avenue exit.  Less than 5 minutes drive from popular destinations like Mission Valley, Fashion Valley, Balboa Park and 10 minutes to Downtown and 15 min to the beaches. Public Transit Uber or Lyft is definitely preferable when travelling in any party more than one especially if you are new to the app($50 free credit). Public transit is easily accessible from the house, simply walk out the front door and take a left down Camino Rico and then across College Avenue for the bus stop for the 115 bus line that will take you to SDSU's Transit center (6 mins).  From there take San Diego's Trolley to the beaches, Sea World, the malls, downtown San Diego, or even Mexico!  A 30 minute ride on the 215 bus line will take you to Balboa Park and the world famous zoo!

Use of all common areas in house & 2 shared bathrooms High e
neighborhood_overview: Del Cerro is a quiet neighborhood.  There is a a nice gastropub with an excellent beer selection just a mile down the road next to an amazing local grocery store full of inexpensive produce and a variety of healthy snacks and nutrition products.  San Diego State University is just close enough to enjoy a lot of nearby quick food eateries but far away from the noise and traffic.  Only 10 miles away from some of the most beautiful beaches. Enjoy San Diego's amazing weather and gorgeous sunsets whenever you like. The beach offers a smorgasbord of activities with dedicated bike trails, kayaking, paddle boarding, parasailing, and of course sun bathing! My favorite part of our neighborhood is our proximity to the Mission Trails Regional Park(2.2mi).  Over 6800 acres of rugged terrain and a multitude of trails perfect for hiking, mountain biking, and mountain climbing.  The park boasts of San Diego's highest peak Cowles Mountain (1594') offering a 360° look at all San Diego has to offer.  Don
notes: Lots of free parking! No parking restrictions either.
transit: By car, we are next to the 8 freeway, off the College Avenue exit.  Less than 5 minutes drive from popular destinations like Mission Valley, Fashion Valley, Balboa Park and 10 minutes to Downtown and 15 min to the beaches. Public Transit Uber or Lyft is definitely preferable when travelling in any party more than one especially if you are new to the app($50 free credit). Public transit is easily accessible from the house, simply walk out the front door and take a left down Camino Rico and then across College Avenue for the bus stop for the 115 bus line that will take you to SDSU's Transit center (6 mins).  From there take San Diego's Trolley to the beaches, Sea World, the malls, downtown San Diego, or even Mexico!  A 30 minute ride on the 215 bus line will take you to Balboa Park and the world famous zoo!

name: Island Guest Suite: Shipping Container Home
summary: Enjoy a stay at the Island Guest Suite. It's a private studio that's attached to the first shipping container home in San Diego.  From the property you have a view of the downtown skyline and Coronado bridge.  This comfortable and clean studio offers all the amenities of a luxury hotel suite for a fraction of the cost.  Feel like a local and enjoy all that San Diego has to offer. The airport and central SD's hottest neighborhoods/ sightseeing are less than 10 mins away.
space: The Island Guest Suite is located in Grant Hill, an up and coming area for San Diego. It’s only minutes away from downtown, marina, Little Italy, Balboa Park, conference center and airport.  The Guest Suite/Studio is approximately 500+ square feet and is a SEPARATE unit that’s on the first floor of San Diego’s first shipping container home.    The floor plan is a large singular space with a Queen bed, seating area, and ¾ bathroom. Guests rave about the comfort of the Queen size bed! There are ceiling fans throughout to keep the space comfortably cool. Lots of windows and sliding glass doors that overlook the Coronado bridge and downtown skyline.  The Island suite offers hotel suite amenities such as: mini refrigerator, Keurig, snacks, WiFi, Roku Smart TV with Amazon Video, Netflix streaming and DVD player, armoire/closet and more.  There is no kitchen. The private entrance for guests includes a keyless entry so you can arrive and depart with ease.

neighborhood_overview: Grant Hill area is located just south of the 94 freeway and east of Golden Hill. It has the best panoramic views of the Coronado Bay Bridge, the San Diego Bay, Petco Park and the Downtown areas.  Grant Hill, just like Golden Hill, attracts people because it's a diverse, chill neighborhood with amazing food, historic homes, and a welcoming locals vibe. It is an up and coming area for San Diego that's continuing to evolve with some of the highest locals rated coffee, bistros and taco shops.  For more specifics on what's close by, check out the Tracy's Guidebook link above the map below....for restaurant, bar and sightseeing recommendations.
notes: This is a smoke free property. This means no smoking on property, please.  Street parking only. The neighborhood is not metered so you can easily find parking around the house.
transit: All central San Diego hotspots: Gaslamp, Downtown, Marina, Little Italy, Balboa Park, Coronado Beach, North Park and more...are within 10 - 15 minutes via car, Uber or Lyft. Street parking is unmetered and easy to find in Grant Hill.

name: Fay Cottage
summary: In the heart of the village.   The back 1 bedroom cottage of a 1920's bungalow in downtown La Jolla.  Restaurants, cafes, movie theater, and more are all within a couple blocks walk.   Walk 10 minutes to the ocean.  Schools are located on either side of the property,  so there are sounds of playing children until the afternoon but peaceful evenings.  Bus stop for the 30 line on the corner, that runs to LJ Shores beach, UCSD and Pacific Beach.  Off-street parking.  Owner lives in front bungalow.

neighborhood_overview: Downtown La Jolla is totally safe for walking around and is it's only nearly self-contained community.  LOTs of restaurants, but also services.  Very walkable.   The ocean can be reached walking in 3 different directions.  I usually do a sunset loop, watching the sunset over the ocean and checking surf spots.
notes: The cottage is really in an amazing location.  Just about everything you need is within a couple blocks - grocery, dry cleaner, good coffee, 3 thai restauraunts, indian, tacos, bank.  Locals' pocket beaches and surfing spots are a 10-15 min walk.    It's possible to do so much without a car, but the bus line is right on the corner for trips to other beaches.  You do hear school children when it's in session but at night it's pretty quiet and there are no neighboring houses with a second story staring into the property.
transit: #30 bus has stop on the corner near the cottage.  Dedicated parking spot for guests.

name: Gaslamp European-Style Boutique - Studio
summary: Describe your place to guests: Situated in San Diego's historic Gaslamp Quarter, Gaslamp Plaza Suites is within several blocks of myriad shops, restaurants, and nightclubs. The San Diego Convention Center is 8 blocks away. Built in 1913, this European-style boutique hotel retains many original architectural elements. Modern conveniences include hotel-wide free WiFi and valet parking for a nightly fee. A free continental breakfast is served on an outdoor rooftop deck.
space: The Melting Pot-A Fondue Restaurant is located in the Gaslamp Plaza Suites, where guests can select from a variety of fondues for a different type of dinner. The hotel bar, Vin de Syrah, serves a selection of spirits, beers, and wines by the glass. Gaslamp Plaza Suites provides discounted access to a health club located 4 blocks away.

neighborhood_overview: Ocean Beach is famous for its bohemian, laid-back fee and enthusiastic embrace of beach life. Catch the sunset with a bucket of cold beers at Wonderland Ocean Pub (Website hidden by Airbnb) one block away at the end of Santa Monica Avenue. Grab some world-famous fish tacos at South Beach Bar & Grille (Website hidden by Airbnb) just one and half blocks from your beach house. Or walk the historic OB pier (Website hidden by Airbnb) the longest concrete pier on the West Coast. Everything in Ocean Beach is steps away from your vacation getaway.
notes: PARKING: No parking on property.  Street parking only and sometimes can be hard to find a spot. Daytime is fairly chill but at night is tough, expect to circle 15-20min. Watch signs for street cleaning restrictions. There is a CVS across the street that has paid parking.
transit: Uber and Lyft are readily available in OB. You can also walk a block over to Newport Avenue and catch the 923 bus for a half hour ride to downtown ($2.25). If you're in a car, there is street parking outside the house and a pay parking lot across the street.

host_about:
Hi there! 

We are Gabriela & Daniel and we work at Air Concierge, Inc. We are a dynamic vacation home rental services company serving vacation homeowners throughout California including San Diego, San Francisco (and Marin), Los Angeles, Palm Springs, Lake Tahoe and Orange County (coastal). The goal of our company and team is to ensure our guests experience first class service while staying in our homes, whether it's a 5 bedroom beachfront home or a bungalow in the city.  These homes are owned by some wonderful, hard-working folks who have opened their homes and spaces to us and thus to you. 

Since 2012, we have established ourselves as the first-of-its-kind vacation rental and short term property management service in San Diego. We have since expanded to those cities noted above, and increased our services to include home cleaning, maintenance, key exchanges and online listing management for sites like Airbnb. 

You might receive communications from me or Daniel, also from Air Concierge.

We look forward to hosting you!

summary: We are at the ocean if you are looking for a place that is clean and spacious our house is for you. 630 Loring St.  Not Suitable for toddlers,  infants, children & pets. space: Before each guest checks in the house is professionally cleaned by a housekeeping service. We do not retain any of the cleaning fees.  This detached house was built in 1950. It was used as a summer home by the previous owners. We restored it respecting the architecture and Beach House spirit.  It's perfect for couples or close friends. Our secluded back yard is very relaxing and private. Unfortunately, the house is not set up to accommodate children of any age....The house is located on a dead end. You will see beautiful sunsets from the cliffs.  Surfing, swimming and sunbathing are just across the street. There are 2 access points to the beach.  At 1000 sq ft the house more than comfortably fits two adults. ABOUT THE HOUSE: Fully Furnished with new beds and couch. Bathroom remodeled with new fixtures. name: Bohemian Beach House
summary: Tucked away and hidden by a lush garden entrance is your spacious and serine loft studio waiting to relieve you from the hustle and bustle of todays fast-paced life! Your Bohemian Beach House Loft awaits- where you are invited to unwind and relax in a uniquely designed open loft space in the heart of sunny Mission Beach.
space: High vaulted ceilings with a fresh and open space vibe, you’ll feel cozy and at home yet transported and free in the spacious Bohemian Beach House. Filled with unique and eclectic pieces collected during world travels, the Bohemian Loft is a rare find in the Mission Beach neighborhood. An airy and bright loft, you are able to use a full kitchen with stainless steel appliances stocked with all the cooking utensils needed to whip up a delicious feast! Find some peaceful rest in your upper loft area with a queen size memory foam mattress, desk, and rocking chair; and watch tv in bed or opt for the couch and flat screen tv in the downstairs living space. neighborhood_overview: Located in the center of Mission Beach you are quite literally steps away from being on both the beach and the bay and are surrounded by a variety of neighborhood locally owned businesses and shops! In less than a minute you will find yourself on the sandy shores with your toes in the water. Enjoy them with your complimentary beach gear: beach chairs, boogie boards, and traditional Turkish towels. We have two new beach cruiser bikes available to rent for $10/day each. 3 Miles of boardwalks shielded from the street run along the beach and the bay and provide you plenty of roaming room. Walk, run, skate, and bike friendly you can choose to walk or ride along them. Restaurants, ocean view bars, coffee and cold pressed juice shops line the streets and are also in less and 1-5 minutes walk of stepping outside your door. Grab your coffee and breakfast at the neighborhood favorite Olive Cafe just a couple doors down, or start your day with a local cold pressed organic juice a couple doors in
notes: Our boutique, Kahve, is in front of the Bohemian Beach House on the same property but completely separated from your private space.
transit: There is street parking right in front (15min-2hr spots along the street) as well as a couple parking lots close by with long term spots (2-3 minutes walk). There is a bus stop less than one block away and getting a Lyft, Uber, or cab is highly accessible. Plus there are boardwalks along the beach and bay where you can walk, run, skate, or bike along the water to where you need to go in the area!
access: The unit is located through a gated garden entrance that is shared between you and our downstairs guests + us when we are on the property. The unit door and garden entrance are private from the general public. Detailed instructions regarding check-in will be provided prior to your visit so that you know exactly how to find us and enter without issue.
interaction: During your stay we are available as often as needed or not at all. We are often in the area or working up front in our boutique, Kahve. We are there if you need us and mind our own business if you don't! :) We are always available by phone or text should you need anything, and are always happy to offer recommendations or answer any locals questions!

I just like to be transparent so you aren't surprised! - While I won't be at the property, I'll notify my leasing office that you will be staying so you can contact them with any concerns. I will be available, but in the event of a maintenance issue, I'll also have their information available to you. - Lastly, but almost most importantly, please note this is my personal living space, not a side property. As such, I have my work/school/life :) materials all in this space. I will do all that I can to make your stay welcoming and enjoyable. Please be considerate of my space and belongings, and treat it as if it were your own.
host_about:
I'm an east coast transplant, living in CA for a little while! I love to travel and last year I finally got to go to Europe. I explored Barcelona, Paris and studied in Rome for a little while. It was such an incredible experience and can't wait to go back. 

While I'm living in beautiful Southern California, I'm taking full advantage of all that this area has to offer. Whether that means a Saturday morning bike ride, a weekend ski trip up north, or a quick run on a weeknight, there is so much to see and do in CA!

I look forward to welcoming others and introducing them to the beauty of SoCal. When staying in my apartment, I won't be there, but I will be easily accessible should you have questions. I can provide guidance as to how to best travel the city and key places to check out. Hope to see you soon!

name: Cute Condo 1 Block from Beach, PB
summary: This condo is located in the heart of Pacific Beach, San Diego and is one block from the vibrant beach and four blocks from the calm, relaxing bay. It's a cute, comfortable condo with all the main amenities and is one of the best places to be in SD! (And has parking and AC...both hard to come by here!)
space: Enjoy a cute, comfortable, well-decorated one-bedroom condo in the heart of Pacific Beach! You'll find almost no other location that is as close to the beach, bay, and main street of PB. Spend time strolling around the beach town, laying out at the beach, biking along the boardwalk, and enjoying the local restaurants. The bedroom is a decent size with a comfy queen bed, and a great bathroom. As I do live here regularly, there is not a lot of closet space.  You will have a comfortable living room with a large flat screen TV and wireless internet service. Make use of the full-size kitchen equipped with stainless steel appliances, a dishwasher, microwave, toaster, and a counter top grill. If you love to cook, I have almost every cooking tool needed. I also have a Nespresso and a fresh press for you coffee fiends :)  There is in-unit washer/dryer and a parking spot! (Parking can be hard to come by in this part of San Diego.) There is a new A/C unit that works great. Most coastal residences

name: Charming Beach Retreat
space: Hello, I'm Vicky!  This apartment is located in the heart of the vibrant Ocean Beach neighborhood of San Diego.  It is steps to scenic Dog Beach, Ocean Beach, Mission Bay, and the San Diego River.  It has a convenience store a three-minute walk away, and is a short walk away from restaurants such as OB Noodle House, Day Break, and Hodad's.  There's plenty of fun to be had nearby, whether you're looking to surf or sunbath, swim or sail, enjoy good food and a beer, watch dogs play on the beach, or spend a day at Sea World or the San Diego Zoo! I'm offering the entire unit, one bedroom, one bath, with a couch in the living room that converts into a  queen-size bed.  The private unit also includes a kitchen with a dinette area, ample living room, and small backyard.  The master bedroom has a comfortable queen-size Tempur-Pedic bed, a cozy comforter, extra blankets, and extra sets of bed and bath linens.  The bathroom features a tub and handheld showerhead.  I offer WiFi and a surfboard.  W

host_about:
I live in Chiang Mai Thailand with my dog. While I may live far away from my home state of California, my love for it hasn't faded. I keep the San Francisco Bay Area in my heart as I continue to explore onwards. 

Besides being a traveler, I'm an entrepreneur, artist, life-long learner, and food lover. I enjoy listening to science podcasts and all types of music. My favorite activities include meeting interesting people, backpacking through forests, trying new recipes, and kayaking to secluded beaches. The things I care about most are friends and family.

host_neighbourhood: South Park is one of San Diego's hidden gems. It's small enough to evoke a strong sense of community, but bustling with great restaurants, bars, shops, and more.  A quick 5 minute walk and you'll be in the heart of the neighborhood. We'll fill you in on some of our favorite spots.  If you're looking to turn it up a notch, the North Park neighborhood is nearby with great nightlife and microbrewery options.  Hillcrest and downtown San Diego/Gaslamp are also a cheap Uber/Lyft ride away. For those looking to enjoy the great outdoors, our place backs up to  Balboa Park. You'll enjoy easy access to hiking trails, the Balboa Park Golf Course, the Balboa Tennis Club, the Bud Kearns Memorial Swimming Pool, the San Diego Velodrome, and the Morley Field Disc Golf Course.  On the west side of the park, you'll find the world famous San Diego Zoo, the San Diego Natural History Museum, the San Diego Air & Space Museum, The Old Globe Theater, and much more. It's definitely worth exploring.
host_listings_count: As with most neighborhoods in metro San Diego, we get a bit of airplane noise as planes descend into San Diego International Airport. It's a non-issue for 99% of our guests, but if you are very sensitive to noise, our listing might not be for you.
host_total_listings_count: San Diego is pretty spread out so it's usually best to rent a car. We offer several free parking options and easy access to multiple freeways.  You can be at the beach in less than 10 minutes! If a car is not an option, you can utilize the MTS bus line #2 (to North Park or Downtown), bike/scooter rentals, or the friendly Uber/Lyft drivers who live in the neighborhood (only $10 to the airport!).
host_has_profile_pic: Guests will have a private entrance down our driveway. The guesthouse is a standalone structure with its own secluded back deck.  A key will be waiting for you in a lock-box upon arrival so you can come and go as you please. The laundry room is inside the main house, but accessible through a back door that the hosts will leave unlocked upon request.
host_identity_verified: We tend to be more hands-off as hosts because we want our guest house to be a relaxing oasis during your busy days of exploring San Diego. Everything is prepped for your arrival, but if you have any questions or need a few extra amenities, we're here to help.
street: * No extra or undisclosed guests.  * Quiet hours between 10:00 pm and 8:00 am.  * No loud music, partying, or disruptive behavior.  Any complaints from neighbors will result in termination of rental.  * Towels are not to be used for makeup or cleaning shoes.

name: Lovely La Jolla Cottage Minutes from the Beach
summary: Enjoy the partial ocean view from the privacy of your custom-built cottage facing the Pacific. Open the French doors to allow the ocean breeze and unwind while enjoying magnificent sunsets.  The Eastern King Bed and marble top kitchenette provide amenities for the perfect get-away.  Wood floors throughout, a custom-tiled bathroom with radiant floor heat - all the comforts of a luxury vacation.
space: Awesome location! Right in the heart of Bird Rock/La Jolla close to some of Southern California's best beaches! The Beach Cottage is detached and located towards the rear of our property. You will have your own private entrance with key-less entry. To access The Cottage, walk down the drive way, up the stairs to your suite. The Cottage was custom built with luxury in mind. This one-of-a-kind space provides the ultimate beach getaway! Custom doors and lighting, private balcony off your bedroom, black-out curtains, amazing shower with heated tile flooring, new super-comfortable Eastern King bed with luxury memory foam topper, remote controlled A/C and heating unit, bar sink and mini fridge, Nespresso coffee maker, tea kettle,  Direct TV, closet, beach chairs and towels, and more.  Unrestricted street parking.  Local surf board and bike rental around the corner and if traveling with your four-legged friend, check out online sites for in-home doggie care within blocks.   Walk to Bird Rock
description: Enjoy the partial ocean view from the privacy of your custom-built cottage facing the Pacific. Open the French doors to allow the ocean breeze and unwind while enjoying magnificent sunsets.  The Eastern King Bed and marble top kitchenette provide amenities for the perfect get-away. neighborhood_overview: The cottage is a 4-minute walk from the ocean that has a lovely park and benches to enjoy the view, the sunrise and sunset, and clean ocean air.  Just steps away from some of the best coffee shops, bakery and cuisine in the Bird Rock, LaJolla neighborhood.  Enjoy great bars, shops and casual dining.  It’s within a very short ride to Wind n'Sea Beach as well as the sand and surf of Pacific Beach and Mission Bay.  LaJolla Cove is an 8-minute car ride.
notes: Access to The Cottage is down the driveway, and up the stairs.   No smoking on property, including private balcony and deck. Southern California is known for being especially dry and fires can spread easily. Thanks for understanding!
transit: Walking is the BEST way to see La Jolla! Explore the neighborhood and its architecture, see the sea lions in the Cove, shop downtown La Jolla or just hang by the beach! If you want to explore more, Uber is the best way to get around! Pacific beach is 5-min away, Mission beach is 8-min away and downtown San Diego is only 15-min away!
interaction: We are available to help with any questions or concerns during your stay. We look forward to having you!

neighborhood_overview: Find your Funk & Groove in Ocean Beach If you’re looking for a laid back beach to hang out like a local, look no further than Ocean Beach. This small beach town is a favorite among locals who spend their days surfing, sun bathing around the pier, hanging out in their vintage VW vans, and strolling through the many surf shops, taco stands and antique malls. Ocean Beach offers the pitch perfect throw-back groovy vibe of vintage SoCal, coupled with friendly locals, great dining, and a vibrant night life scene. Nestled between the San Diego River and the hills of Point Loma, Ocean Beach is perfect for surfers to enjoy the waves created by jetties. The beach is also friendly for swimmers, sun bathers, even dogs too!

transit: The easiest option is to rent a car, so you can roam freely through the vast and various San Diego regions. But if you’re looking to save a buck or be eco-friendly, plan to make the most of San Diego’s convenient and easy public transport options. There are plenty of lines and routes that are serviced throughout San Diego. Be sure to check timetables and schedules, and plan your routes in advance. For bus schedules and information, visit Metropolitan Transit System. For bus schedules and information for San Diego's North County, visit Breeze.

host_about: I like adventure and richly varying experiences! Keeps the mind kickin' in overdrive.... Kitesurfed in the Canary Islands...Canyon Swung in the Swiss Alps (Interlaken)... Cocooned by mother nature in Iceland...Toured through war torn Bosnia, Serbia, and the Baltic States...Scuba dived in Cozumel...Shark cage diving in South Africa with great whites...Dirt biked up the Greek island of Corfu to see the clouds push over Albania...Bought a condo in Jaco, Coasta Rico...Experienced the Hammams in Istanbul...last but not least, partied in Ibiza till dawn.

name: Mike's House and Garden
summary: The care taken to honor the atmosphere of the original 1910 house creates a feeling of another time and place. The house is secluded in a prize winning garden and approached through a stone pergola. The Craftsman furniture, lighting and antique Persian carpets reflect a distant and captivating sensibility.  This house has been featured in three books and “American Bungalow” magazine.  The garden was mentioned in Sunset Magazine and  featured as one of the premier gardens of University Heights.
space: The house has a period California Bungalow layout with a large front porch.  Entrance is through a four foot wide original front door into the living room and sun room. The separate dining room is visible beyond, The living room is centered on a brick fireplace with flanking wood cabinets.  A Stickley china cabinet behind a large craftsman chair creates its own reading area. The sun room features a Stickley day bed for lazy afternoons. The dining room features a beautiful built in hutch with stained glass windows above. A Period chandelier and wall sconces set the mood.  The adjoining kitchen includes a 1930’s stove, a spacious refrigerator and upgraded  sink and counter area with microwave, dishes, etc...  A breakfast nook illuminated by a bank of French windows and natural wood wainscoting completes the room. The master bedroom is accessed through an adjoining hallway where the queen sized Tempur-Pedic bed is placed within a broad bay that includes windows on either side for fresh ni

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood consists of houses from the turn of the century through the 20’s and 30’s. It is great for walking, and it is surrounded by natural canyons. Within a city block is a pedestrian bridge that adjoins a shopping center with coffee houses, restaurants, and grocery stores. Public transportation is available there with quick access to downtown and Balboa Park. The ocean and bay are minutes away.
notes: A cottage exists at the rear of the property which is rented separately. The artist’s studio is self contained and is the sole residence of the host, which is not available for use by the guests. The two cats are only outside and in Art Studio, not in main house or cottage.
transit: Our location has high ratings for walkability. Balboa Park is just a mile from here. Express buses are within walking distance that can take one to all corners of the city. Downtown is about 12 minutes by express bus. The airport is about 15 minutes away by car. The village of Hillcrest is a stones throw away with many unique restaurants, movie theaters, book stores, and shops.
access: Guests have sole access to the house. The side garden, the front garden and the front porch are available for resting, wandering and enjoying. A second bedroom at the back of the house is used for storage and remains locked.
interaction: An artist’s studio is located at the back of the property where the host lives. General questions can be answered, and assistance gladly offered when the host is present.
house_rules: Guests are considerate of others on the property and the neighbors. No parties or gatherings are permitted . Friends may visit but not stay. All art objects and furnishings should be treated with respect. There is no space for pets.
host_about: I am a painter and an art instructor and have worked in the field for thirty years. I have lived in this residence for 26 years and have applied all of my skills and interest to restoring this house to its historic roots.  I was delighted when my zero-scape garden won the neighborhood award and was mentioned in a Sunset Magazine" walking tour of the area.  I spend most of my time painting in the art studio and therefore

description: This 1939 factory-worker's residence was occupied by the original owner's  family until the '70s. Subsequent residents have been few, and it was rarely a rental. Bedrooms, each measuring 12'x 10', are  adequately sized to provide easy access to both sides of the bed.

notes: along a low-land corridor that serves as a flyway for seagulls, ducks, parrots, tanagers, hummingbirds, crows, and redtail hawks. This 1939 factory-worker's residence was occupied by the original owner's  family until the '70s. Subsequent residents have been few, and it was rarely a rental. The sun-filled living room offers a few comfy spots for reading and/or birdwatching;  an open front door invites cool ocean breeze. The dining room's octagonal table can accommodate up to eight people (cozily). Recently updated bathroom still sports the original tub and receives southern exposure sunlight. Bedrooms, each measuring 12'x 10', are  adequately sized to provide easy access to both sides of the bed. Entire ho
transit: Point Loma is one of San Diego's oldest suburbs. This particular house (built in 1939) is located on a street of mostly two-bedroom homes constructed for the city's blue-collar workers and fishermen.
access: Poe Street residents are a tight group and appreciate the quiet of the neighborhood. Though all the adjacent neighbors are quite friendly (all dog people!),  they've made calls to police after being disturbed by undue noise outside during nighttime hours. Thank you for keeping the mood mellow.
interaction: Bike the two miles west to Ocean Beach on a relatively flat street named Voltaire — if you want a workout, another route to Ocean Beach requires that you pedal up and down (and up and down again) via Narragansett Avenue. Heading in a southwesterly direction  (for about six miles) on Catalina Boulevard will get you to Cabrillo National Monument at the mouth of San Diego Bay, passing Ft. Rosecrans National Cemetery along the way.
house_rules: Entire house (except for one owner-occupied closet) and back patio. Please don't utilize landing outside front door or sidewalks as smoking area, as it affects neighbors. Please use caution with the driveway: only high-clearance cars/SUVs can make it up without scraping either the front end or the back.
thumbnail_url: Contact me anytime via phone or text.
host_id: No fires in fireplace. Please note that there is a$25 per-person/per-night fee beyond two guests (four-person maximum). Gatherings of more than two people must be taken inside after 9 p.m. so as not to disturb neighbors. $100 pet fee applies for approved dogs under 25 pounds (for consideration, pls send info on breed, size, and temperament). Dogs not allowed on furniture or beds. Cleaning fee covers laundry, dusting, garbage emptying, and vacuuming. Please wash dishes. Thank you!
host_response_rate: I'm a former newspaper guy (remember those?!) who moved here in 1989. Once I found Ocean Beach/Point Loma (It was a foggy morning...), I never wanted to live anywhere else.

neighborhood_overview: Located in the beautiful Loma Portal neighborhood of Point Loma, we are close to many attractions but at the same time our Casita is off the beaten path and private.  We are walking distance to the Historic Liberty Station that houses great restaurants, parks, shops, the LOT Movie Theater, galleries and museums, bike paths and rentals, markets and grocery stores.  Using an Uber, cab,  or your own car,  we are a short ride to downtown, Little Italy, PETCO Park, Sea World, Shelter Island, Cabrillo Monument, Ocean Beach, Mission Bay, Mission Beach.......we are centrally located with easy freeway access to almost anywhere in the San Diego area.
notes: Being close to the San Diego International Airport (10 minute drive) we do experience some noise from the departing flight patterns. The Casita is very insulated and it hasn't been a problem for previous friends and guests, ( or for us who live here year round) but if you are very noise sensitive,  this area might not be for you.  The neighborhood itself is very quiet.
transit: If arriving with your own car, parking is easy and usually wide open. We are on a dead-end street.  Getting around by Uber or cab is quick and easy to all of San Diego.
access: The Casita is close to our house but is completely private and separate for both guest and host.  There is no shared access with the main house.
interaction: We love meeting new people, and will be happy to give recommendations to our guests as needed. We live in the main house but we respect the privacy of our guests.  We are there if you need us, we are not, if you don't. :)

notes: Please note that bedrooms are daisy-chained.  One of the bedrooms has access from the other bedroom and the outside. Our house does not have air conditioning, but does have central heating and a space heater for colder days. Most homes in our neighborhood do not have AC, as we rarely have enough hot days to warrant needing it. There are ceiling fans and a tower fan in each room to keep the air circulating. With the nice breeze that kicks in almost every day around 5pm, we hope you'll stay nice and cool in the evenings. We live in a busy city neighborhood near the airport. We aren't directly in the flight path, but you may hear some airplane noises between the hours of 5AM and 10PM. If the noise bothers you, we recommend closing the windows and turning on the fan. name: Sunset Cliffs Holistic Garden Studio
summary: Located 1 block from Sunset Cliffs Natural Park. Watch amazing sunsets everyday & do yoga on the cliffs facing the ocean! The garden studio is cozy, cute, AND we use natural products for cleaning, etc. It's good for couples, solo adventurers, & business travelers. We're kid/baby-friendly too. We are located 3 miles from Seaworld & close to Ocean Beach, Pt. Loma, Cabrillo Light House, downtown San Diego, Pt. Loma Nazarine University.
space: The garden studio has a fully functional kitchen and vaulted ceilings with a big ceiling fan. There's lots of light, and it's pretty darn cute. The bathroom has a bathtub, so you can take a soak after a long day. We have little ones too, so if there's anything specific you need for your baby or tot, just give us a holler! If we don't have what you need, we'll try to point you in the right direction so you can get it. We've traveled a ton, so we try to make sure the studio has what you need. Full length mirror? Check! Kitchen gadgets? Check! Spices for your cooking needs? Done! Salt and pepper? You got it!

neighborhood_overview: Sunset Cliffs is perfect for walking around and getting some fresh ocean air. The neighborhood is very dog friendly, kid friendly, and there are tons of surfers. If you like to surf, this is the spot! Head north about a mile and you'll hit downtown Ocean Beach. It's a fun place to grab surfer eats, hit some antique stores, or just hang at the beach (end of Newport Ave.). You can also walk out to the pier and you'll probably see brown pelicans and lots of fishermen. Check this link for more on brown pelicans: (Website hidden by Airbnb)
notes: If you're bothered by a few farm noises such as a clucking chicken or the braying of a goat, you may not like it here. Just next door live 2 miniature goats and 5 chickens (no roosters, so don't worry!). The main house has a friendly dog, but she stays in the back yard and is pretty quiet.
transit: Downtown San Diego is 5 miles from here. It takes about an hour to get there by public transportation. Uber or Lyft are great options. Our nearest bus stop is a 12 minute walk (Bus #35 at Point Loma Ave & Sunset Cliffs Blvd.) You can throw your bike on the bus though, and bikes are also allowed on the trolley and the Coronado Island ferry ride. If you're driving, there's plenty of street parking in front of our house. No permits required.
access: You'll have the garden studio to yourself during your stay. The entry from the street is via a shared patio. My parents live in the main house, so they're your neighbor on one side, and I'm your neighbor on the other side. We're all friendly folks and happy to help your stay be a great one! Please take your conversations inside after 10pm. No smoking is allowed on the property at all.
interaction: We're pretty busy, but we love to meet our guests and strive for lots of smiles and keeping you happy. If there's anything you need, we're happy to make recommendations and share a cup of tea when we have some down time.
house_rules: - Quiet hours must be maintained after 10pm.  - Guests must lock the front gate behind them when coming and going.  - There is a $30 fee for losing keys to the studio or gate. - No smoking is allowed on this property, not even outdoor patios.
host_about:
I love to travel and meet people. I'm a property manager, and I pride my business on great customer service. I speak both english and spanish fluently. 
I trained in college in woodworking/furniture design and love craft and all things hand made. I enjoy spending time with my goats and my daughter. My husband and I have a small urban farm and we live a holistic lifestyle... another one of my many interests!

name: Bougainvillea Cottage
summary: Newly renovated and decorated guest cottage with all upgraded amenities.  Located within minutes of downtown La Jolla, La Jolla Cove, La Jolla Shores, UCSD as well as highway 5, 52 and 805.  Our property is completely fenced and gated, guests are welcomed to park inside the gates on our property. Whether on vacation or in town for work, Bougainvillea Cottage is the perfect place to meet all your needs.
space: Entire cottage, consisting of the bedroom area, kitchenette and private bathroom. You will be given a key to the cottage and an opener to the gate so you may come and go as you please.

Guest are provided with a key and gate opener to come and go as they please. Please feel free to let us know if there is anything you need or if you would like any recommendatio
neighborhood_overview: La Jolla is 'the jewel' of Southern California with almost perfect weather year round. We are only minutes from some of the most beautiful beaches in the country. La Jolla Cove is ideal for swimming, snorkeling, scuba diving and kayaking. Water visibility at the Cove can at times exceed 30 feet. The Cove has an underwater park which is an ecological reserve. Fishing and the removal of any object is strictly forbidden. La Jolla Shores is a one mile long sandy beach, ideal for swimming, kayaking, surfing and picnicking.  La Jolla offers a variety of award winning restaurants, unique stores, the renown Museum of Contemporary Art, Birch Aquarium, The Lodge at Torrey Pines, The Hotel Valencia, and the world famous Torrey Pines Golf Course. We are also only a few minutes drive from UCSD.
notes: Our cottage is ideal for one or two people, whether in town for vacation or work. We have 3  adorable small dogs and a  brown hen named ‘Teriyaki’. If you happen to be outside there is a good chance ‘Teriyaki’ will walk up to the fence and introduce herself, she is quite the conversationalist.  Our pets are  are secured on our property by a secondary fence have no access to the cottage or driveway.   You are welcome to park inside our property which is completely secured by fencing and gates.  We have provided a binder in the cottage with lots of useful information to make you stay as enjoyable as possible. In the binder is the WiFi access code, recommendations for local shops, restaurants, sight seeing and activities such as hiking, surfing, etc. Please feel free to reach out to us via the Airbnb site or text for more recommendations or if we can answer any questions. Unfortunately our accommodations are not suitable for very young children or pets.
transit: The easiest way to get around is with a car. Everything is relatively close and parking is usually available. If you are going to a big event or don't want to worry about finding parking Uber or Lyft are great alternatives.
access: Guests have the entire cottage to themselves including the kitchenette and bathroom. They also have access to private parking next to the cottage, the entire property is fenced in and gated for your additional security and comfort. Guest are provided with a key and gate opener to come and go as they please.
interaction: Please feel free to let us know if there is anything you need or if you would like any recommendations for restaurants, sight-seeing, or activities. The easiest way to contact us is via text or the Airbnb site.
house_rules: No loud music / noise after 10:00 pm. Please turn lights, air-conditioning, heating, TV off and leave keys and gate opener in the cottage before leaving, thank you.

Hi there! 
I'm TJ and I'm originally from Pleasantville, NY. I've called Brooklyn home for 3 years now, during which I've graduated The New School with an Environmental Science degree. During my time in school I worked as a kitchen expediter at Momofuku Ssam Bar and now I work at a farm-to-table restaurant called Blue Hill. I love the work but I also am interested in cooking,  health and wellness, and teaching fitness to others via Crossfit. 

I have hosted AirBnB guests through my roommate while he has been out of town and I feel I have learned how to be a good guest through being a good host. I am very respectful, clean, and positive person. 

Cheers! 
TJ

Little Italy, with some of the best bars and restaurants in San Diego is just down the hill. Downtown San Diego, where the Gaslamp Quarter is located, a 7 minute Uber away. The San Diego Convention Center is a 10 minute Uber away. Loads of boutique shops, restaurants, and cafés line the Little Italy neighborhood are all just blocks away. Petco Park, home of the San Diego Padres, is only 10 minutes away. And we're located super close to the San Diego International Airport, just 8 minutes away.
notes: Because many people ask: 1. Payment- You “submit a booking” which means you pay the full amount now. We do not get paid until after your arrival. There are no cash transactions, and unfortunately you may not put down a deposit. 2. Deposit - Airbnb does not charge the deposit at all unless there is a claim for damages after check-out. 3. Unfortunately, we don’t have more pictures of the house and are unable to send you any more. 4. The site blocks telephone numbers until you have booked your trip, so we are unable to call you. Thanks!
transit: There is a bus stop across the street from the home. There's always electric scooters and bike rentals near the home for quick and convenient local transportation. UBER/Lyft are also great ways to get around San Diego. If you're driving, there is plenty of free street parking around the house.

Little Italy, with some of the best bars and restaurants in San Diego is just down the hill. Downtown San Diego, where the Gaslamp Quarter is located, a 7 minute Uber away. The San Diego Convention Center is a 10 minute Uber away. Loads of boutique shops, restaurants, and cafés line the Little Italy neighborhood are all just blocks away. Petco Park, home of the San Diego Padres, is only 10 minutes away. And we're located super close to the San Diego International Airport, just 8 minutes away.
notes: Because many people ask: 1. Payment- You “submit a booking” which means you pay the full amount now. We do not get paid until after your arrival. There are no cash transactions, and unfortunately you may not put down a deposit. 2. Deposit - Airbnb does not charge the deposit at all unless there is a claim for damages after check-out. 3. Unfortunately, we don’t have more pictures of the house and are unable to send you any more. 4. The site blocks telephone numbers until you have booked your trip, so we are unable to call you. Thanks!
transit: There is a bus stop across the street from the home. There's always electric scooters and bike rentals near the home for quick and convenient local transportation. UBER/Lyft are also great ways to get around San Diego. If you're driving, there is plenty of free street parking around the house.
access: Your room is completely private. You will be sharing the rest of the home with myself, my roommate, and other guests.
interaction: I'm constantly traveling, but my roommate lives onsite and can assist with any need you have while in town. My units are set up for self-service and are completely private spaces for only guests' use.
host_about:
I currently split my time between Northern and Southern California. I'm a traveling paramedic who is studying to become a doctor. When I'm not working or studying, I'm planning out my next adventure usually with the help of Airbnb.

My brother Rob and I love hosting guests at our homes.

host_about:
Aloha! I'm originally from Honolulu, Hawaii and I've called San Diego, California my home since 2013. 
I'm a former Hawaii lū'au Polynesian dancer, but I still have a grass skirt on standby :) I love designing art- creating garments, accessories, printing fabrics and sketching.

I've traveled to France, Italy, Spain, Greece, Malta, Canada, Mexico, Thailand, Japan, Taiwan, Samoa, American Samoa, Kiribati, French Polynesia, New Zealand and all over the US, but my favorite destinations are Bali, Indonesia and home in Hawaii (to visit family).

Love hosting Airbnb guests to my home here in Hillcrest and North Park along with my Aloha upbringing!

notes: We only host guests with uploaded verified Government ID. Yard is shared with us. Absolutely no parties. Go out and enjoy all the wonderful beaches, local businesses, bars and restaurants and come home to a cozy relaxing bed.  Pacific Beach is a dense neighbourhood and neighbours live close by and overlook the yard.  There are families next door with young children.  A small dog lives on site.  We live on site, on the second floor which overlooks the yard. No visitors please. Just two registered guest per reservation.  Do not book for someone else. No third party bookings. If there are any unapproved visitors, you will be asked to leave without refund. This is not a hotel, it is our home we are welcoming you to stay at.  Please use street parking. There is street sweeping twice a month in Pacific Beach. Please read the signs. The hours vary street to street. Please note - on our street it is first Wednesday and Thursday of the month between 7am and 10am. So do not park there between th
transit: Everything you need in Pacific Beach is within walking distance from our place, but if you need, the bus stop is less than 2 blocks away.   There are always Uber and Lyft drivers in the area and it's usually less than a 5 minute wait for a ride.
access: You may use our yard and hot tub from 8am-10pm. Quiet time is 10pm-8am as our neighbours are close and families live next door.  We live on site so no visitors or parties of any sort. Washer and dryer are available to you upon request.  You will be sharing our yard as this is our home. You may see us or a little dog in the yard occasionally. Let us know if you are uncomfortable with dogs and we will try to accommodate. Please keep entry gate closed so the dog doesn’t escape to visit his friends :)  Maximum 2 registered guests allowed on site. Any unauthorized visitors will be charged $200 per person per day. Just let us know who will be staying ahead of time when booking. Quiet time is 10pm-8am.
interaction: You may see us in the yard which your door opens to, or in the driveway, but other than that, interaction is whatever you would like. We live on the second floor above the studio. We are available as much you need us but also respect your space. We have lived in Pacific Beach for 15 years so have a ton of recommendations and advice for anything. Just message, call or text if you need us. We want you to love Pacific Beach as much as we do.
house_rules: Absolutely no additional people on the property at any time. No gatherings, no parties - we live on site so you will be asked to leave without refund if you disrespect the rules.  Families live close by so please respect our neighbours.  Absolutely no visitors. Just two registered guests allowed. You will be charged $200 per an unauthorized visitor, per day.  Yard access and hot tub hours 8am - 10pm. Use at your own risk.  Please rinse off before using hot tub.  Do not urinate in hot tub.  Absolutely no glass in the hot tub.  Refilling the tub due to not following the house rules will incur a $500 refill charge. You are liable for any damage to the tub.  We live on site. This is our home sweet home. :) Please be respectful and treat the property as you would expect your guests to treat your own home.
host_about: We have been lucky enough to live the beach life in sunny San Diego for over 15 years. I am originally from London, and Jordan from Michigan. We both love to travel and are excited to share our space with you! We live on site and most of your interactions will likely be with Jordan who does an awesome job maintaining and caring for the space.  We have a little four legged friend whom you might see around the property and also an ever changing garden with fruit and veggies.

I Was Born And Raised In A Lill Town In South Italy Called Aversa. I Have Been Living In California For A Couple Years And I Feel Living In A Paradise. Very Outgoing, Enjoy Conversation. I´m a passionate host on Airbnb, and only happy when my guests are happy. I love to share my knowledge and appreciation for the city of San Diego.
I will always do everything I can to make your stay as perfect and as comfortable as possible. 
I am very flexible time wise, I will always meet you in person when you arrive and welcome you and share local knowledge with you. 
I love my Desert and San Diego Home that's why I always carefully select guest and only take on places I would be happy to arrive at myself if I would be the guest.

Life Is Really Short Let's Make The Best Out Of It!

Life Begin After Caffe!

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is quiet, beautiful and perfect for relaxing, but close enough to the great restaurants and nightlife of North Park, South Park, Hillcrest and downtown. You can walk one block to Morley Field where the hiking trails to Balboa Park connect. Morley Field also has public tennis courts and a swimming pool. The museums of Balboa Park and the San Diego Zoo are also walking distance (about 15-20 minutes up the hill). Great food, coffee and craft beer options at 30th Street and Upas are walking distance (about 8 blocks).
notes: We take pride in providing a clean, quiet and well-appointed space for our guests. We hope to make your stay as comfortable as possible. In return we hope for respectful guests that treat our home as if it was their own. **We can sometimes accommodate earlier check-in or later check-out, so just ask!
transit: North Park is centrally located, so you have easy access to freeways and a five minute drive to downtown, Convention Center, Gaslamp District, Petco Park and Seaport Village. You will also be just a 15 minute drive from beautiful Coronado Beach and the Hotel del Coronado.  We use Uber and Lyft quite a bit and it's very convenient to get around from our house if you don't have a car. Usual pick up time takes 10 minutes or less. You will also see dockless bike/scooter sharing around the neighborhood (LimeBike, Bird Scooters etc...) You can download their app and ride around for pretty cheap. It's a fun way to see the neighborhood.
access: Guests will have their own private parking spot behind the unit. You will access it through our alley behind the house.  If you are traveling without a car, the guest house also has a front entrance you can access by walking straight back up the walkway of our main house.
interaction: We will give you your space and privacy, but we are more than happy to meet you and answer any questions you might have about the area if you'd like. Please let us know if you need anything at all during your stay!
house_rules: This is a very quiet, peaceful neighborhood and due to the close proximity of our neighbors and our own home, we ask that you keep noise to a minimum, especially when using the outside spaces. This is very important. We also do not allow smoking anywhere on our property. Lastly, we do not allow more than two people in the guest house at any time. Thank you for respecting our space and our neighbors!
host_about:
Hello! We are Linda (graphic designer) and Andrew (architect/developer). We travel, cycle, rock climb and enjoy San Diego’s awesome weather and food. As creative professionals, we also love to seek out art galleries, museums and interesting architecture, both locally and around the world.

Hosting guests as well as using Airbnb when we travel gives us a unique and personal experience - and we get to meet some really great people!

neighborhood_overview: First and foremost, our home is one-half block walk to world-renowned  Windansea Beach & Natual Water Park and is a designated historical landmark. Next its walkable to local establishments of all sorts of amenities such as Busy Bee bagel, La Clochette Du Coin cafe,  8 Elements West gym, Ashen hair salon, Liquor Box, 7-11 and The Shack, Nautilus Tavern, Su Casa, The Promiscuous Fork, Rigobertos-JUST to name a few. We have bike trails close by that connect Windansea to Birdrock and all its amenities- including our favorite restauraunt in Birdrock-Wheat and Water, owned by our local friend. And we have the coastal walk that leads to the Village of La Jolla.
transit: Once you park here and want to spend time at the beach, you won't want to use your car because you can walk to almost anything you need. However, we are close to the bus line. Our city is full of fun and free things to do. Hiking, biking, chillin at the beach. There are the tourist locations as well such as Birch Aquarium, SD Zoo, Wild Animal Park, Sea World. SO much to discover here in Americas Finest City.

house_rules: We ask that you respect our home as you would your own! No smoking inside the loft or building hallways No parties or large gathering allowed Lock door and turn off heat or A/C each time you leave the loft Notify us of any damage or maintenance request immediately via email or phone call. host_about: Hi. I was born in Brazil and I have been living in San Diego for about 13 years. I like to live a simple life. I love learning about holistic health and I love helping people. host_since: Banker’s Hill is the laidback Heart of San Diego. Walk three quick blocks to Balboa Park and enjoy the museums, theater, or famous San Diego Zoo. Walk ten minutes - past coffee shops and cafes - to Little Italy’s bustling arts district, food corridor & bar/speakeasy scene. We’re conveniently located for a quick, ten-minute Uber ride to the Convention Center and to bypass downtown parking to explore the Gaslamp District. And we’re right next to Hillcrest, North Park, Mission Hills: small neighborhoods with big personalities and big nightlife.
host_about: Free street parking is always available in front of the property, and we can additionally arrange on-site parking with proper notice. If you’re without car, no worries - much of San Diego is walkable to you and Lyft is available to help you bypass any traffic.
host_response_rate: We’re as present as you’d like us to be - our living space is quite separate and our busy schedules leave the house to you. However, as lifelong travelers, we’re happy to play San Diego Ambassadors and show you what makes our city so unique.
host_acceptance_rate: Our walkway occasionally hosts a friendly squirrel or raccoon; a gorgeous red tailed hawk enjoys perching on our railing; at night, you can hear the crickets. We ask that you respect our natural habitat.
street: I'm a writer and traveler who parks her Volvo station wagon for literary meccas, wine tastings, dizzy hikes, and impossibly heartbreaking vistas.

name: Boho Getaway-OCEAN VIEWS-Private Patio-WALKtoBEACH
summary: Our cute little home is nestled on iconic Newport Ave. in Ocean Beach with amazing elevated views of the ocean, Mission Bay, Pacific Beach up to Birdrock & Mt Solidad. The sunsets views are sublime and you can even spy the water from your Queen size bed! It's only a short stroll down to the main part of town, but you are far enough above the rat-race to enjoy a surprising amount of peace n quiet.  There are 2 great outdoor areas to enjoy, including your own private back patio turned tiki oasis.
space: Our home is perched up above Ocean Beach, only 2 blocks from the shops and less than a 10 minute stroll down to the sand and the pier along Newport Avenue (4 blocks to beach). Photos don't quite do justice to just how great the views are, you won't be dissapointed!  The amazing outdoor areas - a large shared deck on the front, plus a partially covered and privately fenced 'tiki' patio out the back - almost triple the useable space of this cute 1 bedder. Both have tables and chairs, extra benches or armchairs, and awesome ocean views. Between the two areas you will catch all the precious sun you need at various times of the day no matter the time of year. Just be aware that the front deck is shared with guests from upstairs as well, while the back area is exclusively yours. Sun bake in private out the back listening to the trickle of our water feature, or try yoga in the sea breeze with views of the Pacific from the front deck.  *we also supply you with YOGA MATS and beach chairs for yo

Our home is perched up above Ocean Beach, only 2 blocks from the shops and less than a 10 minute stroll down to the sand and the pier along Newport Avenue (4 blocks to beach). Photos don't quite do justice to just how great the views are, you won't be dissapointed!  The amazing outdoor areas - a large shared deck on the front, plus a partially covered and privately fenced 'tiki' patio out the back - almost triple the useable space of this cute 1 bedder. Both have tables and chairs, extra benches
neighborhood_overview: Ocean Beach is an eclectic, vibrant community like no other... The streets and the people are colorful and cheery. It has a little grit, but plenty of personality which all add to the OB charm!! Expect live music, breweries, weekly street markets (every Wed night), antique stores, restaurants, surfing, beach yoga and more... all just a few minutes walk away. Being a few blocks from the action, however, has the added bonus of your own peace and quiet. We have very likeminded neighbors who are all very peaceful, quiet and respectful. Enjoy the laid back Cali break, while extending the courtesy to everyone else around you. This is in no way a party house ! We also AirBnb the 2 bedroom unit above separately for the owner. It does share access to the front deck area with you, so at times people may be out there (whereas the back garden area is all yours!). We have the same respectful rules in place upstairs, and are careful to select people who understand it is not for large groups, parties
notes: There are many fun things to do which are quite close to our home. Some of these are listed below: Seaworld 4 miles  San Diego Zoo 9 miles San Diego Zoo Safari Park 40 miles  Lego Land 36 miles Farmers Market - 4 blocks away every Wednesday Balboa Park (7 miles) – beautiful historic park in the heart of San Diego with museums, flower gardens, and historic Spanish-style architecture. Gas Lamp District 9 miles– historic district in the heart of downtown. Lots of restaurants, bars, and nightlife. Old Town 5 miles– the original center of San Diego. Boutique shopping and restaurants. Mission Valley 7 miles– shopping malls and movie theaters. La Jolla 9 miles – a beautiful city with a rugged coastline. High-end boutique shopping in the downtown. Mission Bay Park 5 miles– a playground for everyone. Bike riding, running, water sports, sailing, kayaking, stand-up paddle boarding, picnicking, radio controlled sailboats.  Belmont Park 4 miles- A small amusement park with rides and games. We are n
access: You'll have the entire ground floor apartment to yourself, including a secluded back patio partially undercover with wood dining table. The front deck with amazing views is all yours to enjoy as well, but is also shared with the upstairs apartment which we AirBnb separately.  Be aware that some noise from the unit above can be heard at times, such as plumbing sounds through the wall or heavy footsteps on the floor. Our guests above are asked to be respectful of this, remove their shoes while inside and not use washer/dryer after 10pm. Excessive noise is not allowed and we take care in selecting people who understand it is not for large groups, parties or loud activities. Feel free to let us know if someone is not respecting the rules. Apartment is located at the back of the block, accessible up a flight of stairs from street level, but if you have heavy bags you can walk straight in from the alley access (drop off only, no parking). name: San Diego Shangri La
summary: This small but very comfortable, 650 SF 1-bedroom house sits at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac in a residential neighborhood up on a hill.  We have good views of the canyon below and the ocean in the background.  We sit on a half acre lot and right across the street from the beautiful Kate Sessions Park where you'll find some great hiking trails and killer views of downtown, Mission Bay and SeaWorld.  You'll love how super comfortable this place is!
space: We're calling this a one-bedroom even though we've removed the wall between the bedroom and living room to maximize the open concept.  So with the high ceilings, amazing Tigerwood hard wood floors, and perfect sized kitchen you'll probably want to extend your stay.  We are across the street from San Diego's nicest neighborhood park - Kate Sessions Park, just blocks from public transport, 1 mile from the beach and just 15 minutes from downtown and the airport.  Our place is perfect for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers.

neighborhood_overview: Kensington is a village within the city with lovingly maintained vintage homes.  Great for walking and exploring the best of San Diego!  Within walking distance are two coffeeshops and great restaurants.
notes: We do allow pets, provided they are approved in advance.  We ask that guests do not allow their pets on the furniture.  We also have a dog, his name is Joey and he is a very friendly pit bull.  We keep Joey in our house and on our own private deck, so he does not intrude on our guests.  Joey is very accustomed to guests coming and going.
transit: Our property is a 0.7 mile walk to Adams Ave. which has bus service by the #11 bus.  You can pick up the #11 bus in front of Clem's bottle shop.  The east bound #11 bus goes to the SDSU transit center where you can pick up the green line trolley to go to Santee.  The west bound #11 bus goes to Adams Ave. through Normal Heights and University Heights.  It then goes down Park Blvd. to University Avenue through Hillcrest.  It then goes south on First Avenue to downtown San Diego.  The last stop is at Front and G Street which is about 3 blocks from the convention center, about a 5 minute walk.  The fare is $2.25.  This is a great option to get to and from the convention center because the trip is about 40 minutes in the morning and 50 minutes in the evening during rush hour.
access: Guests have exclusive use of the front courtyard as well as the back yard with the fire pit and grill.
interaction: The hosts live on the property in the main house and are always available, but we make it a point not to intrude on our guests space and peace.  Call or text us with anything needed and we are happy to loan a pan or dish or other need.
host_about: I am the owner of a small company offering MRI equipment in the laboratory marketplace.  I travel throughout North and South America and Asia.  My wife Julie and I have been married for 33 years and we have our own little slice of heaven in San Diego which we rent for vacation rentals.  I love to visit other's accommodations and see how they create their own space for their guests.

It is positioned in the heart of Mission Beach, a gorgeous beach community in San Diego. Mission Beach is a super narrow strip of land between the Pacific Ocean and Mission Bay. Walk in either direction (West or East) and you'll encounter pristine white beaches. Both sides have wide boardwalks for bicycle riding or walking. On the bay-side you'll enjoy a relaxing sail
neighborhood_overview: The best thing about the neighborhood is that there is so much within walking distance that you really don't need a car.  You could just take a taxi from the airport (7 miles away), get dropped off here and you're at the beach!  We have local restaurants, trendy beach bars, excellent coffee spots, and breakfasts cafes all within a few short blocks.  Sea World is just 3 miles away.  - The Heart of Mission Beach - The location is on the south side of Santa Clara Place (the only traffic light in North Mission Beach). It is equally centered between Belmont Park (the roller coaster area) and Crystal Pier in Pacific Beach. - Outdoor Activities -  Recreational opportunities abound! The beach cottage is within walking distance to Santa Clara point where there are numerous recreation activities and rentals available including: stand up paddle boards, kayaks, jet skis, windsurfing, catamarans, sail boats, water ski boats, and even jet packs. There are group classes and private lessons available
notes: We love children and want you to know that they are more than welcome as our guests. This means that children of any age, even infants, are counted as guests in your guest count. Please let us know in advance the ages of all children. We can hook you up with a service that will set up a private bonfire on the beach. Includes set up and take down, portable steel fire drum, roasting sticks, hot dogs, and s'mores. A perfect activity while waiting for the nightly summer Sea World fireworks over the bay.  Inquire for details. Want family pictures on the beach? What better backdrop for a group shot than the stunning backdrop of the ocean or bay at sunset! For an extra fee we can arrange for a local portrait photographer to do a photo session of your family on the beach. Let us know in advanced if you're interested and we can make an appointment with the photographer during your stay.  The unit is thoroughly cleaned between each stay. However if you wish for a cleaning and change of linens du
transit: To orient you here are some distances from the home: 3 miles to Sea World 4 miles to La Jolla Cove 5 miles to Historic Old Town 7 miles to San Diego Airport 9.5 miles to San Diego Zoo/Balboa Park 10 miles to Gaslamp Quarter - No car needed - If you choose not to bring a car you will be totally fine here!  More than half of our guests have come without a car and all have gotten around quite easily! With the bay right out your front door, the beach a mere 1-minute walk away, and restaurants, shops, and convenience stores all within walking distance, a car is not really needed. - Parking Provided -  For those who do bring a car we offer a reserved parking that will fit any full sized SUV. But you'll probably find that you'll park it once and forget about it because nearly everything you need is walking distance or easy to take Uber. It is less than a 10-15 minute walk to Belmont Park where there is a giant roller coaster, rides, restaurants, bars, and shops.   - Bikes - Riding bikes along
access: We offer self-check in with access to a lockbox to make your arrival as easy as possible. This is a whole home rental meaning you will have private use of the whole apartment. There is a spacious rooftop patio that is shared between 4 units. (All are vacation rentals so feel free to mingle and make some new friends who are also our guests and fellow travelers.) Guests also have access to the laundry machines which are shared with the other 3 other units.
interaction: Scott and Janet are your hosts. We are a husband and wife team and  we live around the corner. We will be available to answer questions during your stay. I work just two miles from home and can easily come home if you need anything. My husband, Scott, works partly from our home. He is available as well if you have any questions. We provide you our cell phone numbers for calling if any emergencies arise.
house_rules: House Rules  Airbnb Smart Phone App: We request all of our guests download the Airbnb App to their smart phones. We will do most of our communications through Airbnb so that we both have a record of our conversations and Airbnb can mediate if ever needed. (But feel free to phone us if there are any urgent matters.) Please let us know if you do not have a smart phone so that we can communicate by other means once you have arrived.  3 pm Check in time (or anytime after) 10 am Check out time (strict) Check in and check out times are strict unless prior arrangements have been made. Exceptions can be made for a nominal extra fee only when there are no other conflicts in the cleaning schedule and with other check ins and checkouts.   Checkout procedures:   For your convenience you are able to do a self-check out. Take out the trash and put it in the trash bin out back. Be sure to do your dishes before you go. If you tracked in any sand from the beach please sweep or vacuum it up. Close the w
host_about:
Hi! We are Janet and Scott. We live on the beach in San Diego with our toddler.  We absolutely love being AirBnb hosts and find delight in sharing the beautiful area where we live!  

We make every effort to make sure you feel relaxed and comfortable during your stay and that you get the most out of your time while in San Diego, whether that means sightseeing around town or just chilling out on the beach. We provide you with activity ideas and favorite local restaurants.  We are available when you need us. We live around the corner to most of the properties and can be easily contacted through Airbnb messaging most any time of the day. Let us know if you have any special needs or requests and we will do what we can to accommodate you.

With AirBnb, we've found all of our guests to be delightful people. We will welcome you as friends and look forward to showing you our bit of paradise on the beach!

name: Private San Diego Casita!""
summary: Stay in our separate entry little house! Completely private with queen size bed, bathroom and kitchenette. Perfect for one or two adults.  Great central location in Bay Park neighborhood close to the beach and bay. 10-15 min drive to Mission Beach, Downtown, Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, and La Jolla Cove.  5 min drive to Sea World.  Walking distance to Coronado brewery, great bars and restaurants, and an excellent neighborhood market.
space: The Casita is it's own mini house.  It's a fun little space with everything you need in a place to stay while visiting San Diego.  It has great windows and french doors that you can leave open if you like the breeze.  There is no air conditioning but there is a window fan.  The little patio is a great place for a cup of coffee in the morning or a glass of wine in the evening.

neighborhood_overview: Bay Park is arguably the best central location for experiencing San Diego. 10 minutes to the beach. 5 minutes to Old Town.  10 minutes to Downtown. 10 minutes to La Jolla. You get the picture.  In addition, we have some great little places you can walk to in a couple minutes.  Coffee shops, groceries, bars and restaurants are only 3 blocks away.  If you like jogging, Tecolote canyon is a 5 minute jog through the neighborhood and a nice piece of nature in a big city. There's a golf course and driving range in the canyon as well. There are a couple of breweries that are a 5 minute drive from us.  Coronado Brewing Company is a half mile through the neighborhood so certainly walkable.  They have their own kitchen now with tasty bar food. If you have time, drive up the hill and see the beautiful campus of the University of San Diego.
notes: Please enjoy our backyard.   It's o.k. to look around at the plants if they interest you. There are two varieties of avocado, three fig trees, two orange, one tangerine, one lime, one lemon, banana, and many other fun plants to see. Don't miss the Sea World fire works during the three summer holiday weekends from our backyard. You get a really neat perspective viewing them through the giant palm trees in the neighborhood.
transit: Bus stops are a short walk.  There's plenty of parking if you have a car.  Many guests use Uber or Lyft especially if they're in town for business including conventions.  San Diego does have a trolley system but it will be a few years before the stop in our neighborhood is complete.  Closest stop is a little more than a mile currently.
access: You will have a queen size bed, large bathroom, and kitchenette. There is a TV with cable, including movie channels and WIFI. We keep a fan and a space heater in there.  Microwave, sink, mini fridge. We keep some paper plates, plastic silverware, and paper towels available. Outside enjoy our premium weber grill and grill tools.  There is a table with stools and patio chairs.  We have a foam surf board and body board, as well as an umbrella that you can take to the beach.  There are beach towels and some good books as well.
interaction: We'll be around if you need anything but you will certainly have as much privacy as you wish.  We're outgoing people but we're not going to get in your way.  If you are looking for suggestions on fun activities we'd be happy to let you know some of our favorite things to do in San Diego County!
house_rules: Have fun, just try not to destroy our lovely casita. Please respect the space. Sorry no pets. No smoking inside the Casita, but you can smoke outside if you clean up your butts. Please park in the driveway. If something isn't working please let us know. If something gets spilled and needs cleaning let us know. Please do not take white bath towels to the beach. There are two beach towels for that purpose. If you shed a lot of hair please clean your hair from shower and sink drain. Just common sense stuff. Think that about covers it.
host_about: We are early middle aged. Speech pathologist and librarian. Love sports. We enjoy gardening and cooking.  Love going to the beach and body surfing. Enjoy a good IPA or glass of wine. Like to camp and go hiking. We enjoy listening to and playing music. Naturally, we love spending time with friends and family.   We still love traveling when we can and hosting has been really fun and rewarding as well.

is_location_exact: Welcoming guests to our property and offering them a very unique, heartwarming experience is a dream come true! Airbnb offers a perfect opportunity for me as I've been in the hospitality industry for many years. Our life in South Park is exciting as we enjoy living in this fun neighborhood and so close to Balboa Park. Rick built our stunning 3 story craftsman guesthouse 12 years ago before he retired as an Architect.  We've raised our 5 kids and are also Grandparents. Our daughter in law Romany is our Co-Host for which we are very thankful and she is a delight to our guests also. Our garden keeps us in shape and we go for bike rides, walks and runs through South Park for daily exercise.  Being in love with California just never gets old for me as I was born and raised in The Netherlands.  We enjoy regular trips to our cabin in the Oregon mountains near Rick's family. It's what we live for I should say.   We are also passionate about food, love to cook and entertain with our family and friends.
