name: New Teardrop Camper for Comic-Con Stay
summary: Clean, cozy 12' teardrop trailer with charming outdoor lounge area off private entrance in desirable South Park. It's a 15-minute drive to the Convention Center and Downtown. The king size bed is convertible to a dining/work area. Bed is adjacent to the small but functional kitchen (two gas burners, small fridge, electric kettle, and sink), and shower/toilet. Unit has a Jensen entertainment center with TV screen, DVD player and stereo. Some DVDs provided. This is tiny home glamping.
space: We have a bit of a small, urban farm along with our home dog boarding business. The mealworms have moved out, but our egg-laying chickens are part of the family and live in a well-maintained coop near the gated entrance. We have two small-medium size dogs and they have a lot of friends who visit regularly. We keep play time as quiet as possible, but there will be some doggie and chicken sounds.

neighborhood_overview: South Park is one of San Diego's gems. It's walkable, friendly, diverse, and hip, and it's right next to North Park with all its breweries, charming Balboa Park, and The World Famous San Diego Zoo. There are great restaurants, shops, and bars nearby, though our part of the neighborhood is quiet and safe.
notes: Though we're welcoming and hospitable and we've stayed in Airbnbs ourselves, we're new to Airbnb hosting, and even our NuCamp T@B 2016 S teardrop is new to us. We think it's cool and novel, and we can't wait to use it on the road. For now we're happy to share it with you.
transit: Transportation solutions include plentiful Lyft and Uber service; LimeBike and Ofo rental bikes and BIRD scooters; a bus stop for the #2 Downtown is a mile away.
access: Your separate entrance and fully enclosed area offer you complete privacy, if you'd like it. And we're right next door should you need anything. Our washer and dryer in the garage can be available to you on request.
interaction: We're familiar with all the good haunts and attractions, and we'll be available to you as needed. Ask us anything! We'd love for you to feel comfortable during your stay.
house_rules: - We respect our neighbors nearby and keep things civil 9pish to 8aish. - No shoes in the teardrop, please. - Smoking of cigarettes, marijuana, or vaping is absolutely not allowed inside or on the property. A $500 penalty will be charged to anyone who smokes inside or close enough to the house so it smells. Please respect the space and our desire to keep it clean and habitable for ourselves and future guests.
host_about: Midwestern gal who loves outdoor adventure. I'm enthusiastic about most everything I put my mind to, am loyal to my friends, responsible with my home, business, and animals, enjoy two book clubs and use my movie passes every chance I get. I've completed the AIDS/Lifecycle, a 545 mile charitable bike ride from San Francisco to Los Angeles. I've walked across England on Wainwright's Coast to Coast. I've hiked Half Dome and have plans to revisit it along the John Muir Trail. I've trekked 28 miles in one day along the PCT for Make-A-Wish kids--twice. We bought a T@B teardrop so we can enjoy even more of the outdoors. I'd love to stay in all of the National Parks...before they're gone. I believe life begins at the edge of your comfort zone--but overnights should be as comfortable as possible!

neighborhood_overview: We are a 15 room boutique BnB located in the heart of La Jolla Village in San Diego County.  Each guest room is appointed with different amenities and in their own style and design.  Listed as Historical Site 179  on the San Diego Registry, our Inn has a rich historical past that allows guests to explore and become lost in its stories. It was originally built as a residence for George Kautz family in 1913. The original Gardens were designed by famed horticulturist Kate Sessions, also a well known San Diego figure, who was responsible for Balboa Park and the Scripps Family Gardens. Both these individuals are honored as names of our guest rooms. It also served as the home to the March King
notes: John Philip Sousa's family in the 1920s. It is one of the premier romantic inns in San Diego. Celebrating over 100 years of Architectural History, the bed and breakfast Inn is considered one of the finest examples of Irving Gill’s 1913 Cubist Style" Architecture."

You will have access to the whole house other than my bedroom.  The bathroom is shared and will be clean and have towels and basis supplies to use. The kitchen is pretty large for the size of the house. The backyard is in work in progress, but I have a very nice patio built with a couple of picnic tables and evening lighting, and a BBQ The living room / dining room area is available to use, I have a 40 inch TV with basic cable + HBO.  Feel free to use it! I am out and about a lot of the time, so you may have the place to yourself during the days
neighborhood_overview: It is a generally quiet neighborhood tucked away, but it is very central and surprisingly quick to drive to the more active parts of town.  There is a small market right at the bottom of Gateway, as well as a 7-11 that's open 24 hours.  There is also a taco shop and pizza joint in the same area (all within walking distance).  Other than those spots, the neighborhood is totally residential, so you will likely be driving to other parts of town for nightlife or activity.
notes: I have a few guitars, a banjo, ukulele, and djembe drum laying around, so if you are a musician and like something to strum at night, there will be some toys available.
transit: There is a bus stop 5 minutes walk away on gateway and Home Ave where the 965 pick up.  If you are a visitor to the area, this is likely not terribly useful and I would probably only suggest staying in this area if you had a car to use or felt comfortable using Uber/Lyft, or taxi.  However with a car you can be downtown or at the Ballpark in 5-7 minutes.  Same for Mission valley / Qualcom Stadium area, or Balboa park / Zoo.  It takes about 15 minutes to drive to mission/pacific beach.
access: You will have access to the whole house other than my bedroom.  The bathroom is shared and will be clean and have towels and basis supplies to use. The kitchen is pretty large for the size of the house. The backyard is in work in progress, but I have a very nice patio built with a couple of picnic tables and evening lighting, and a BBQ The living room / dining room area is available to use, I have a 40 inch TV with basic cable + HBO.  Feel free to use it!
interaction: I am out and about a lot of the time, so you may have the place to yourself during the days.  I rarely watch TV so its all yours.  I sometimes cook, or BBQ, so if you are around, we can share a meal or two.
house_rules: No smoking at all in the house.  You may smoke out on the back patio if you like.  I have nice neighbors with children so I try not to blast music at night, but reasonable house noise is fine at most any hour.  I have experienced my share of roommates and shared house activity over the years, so I will be pretty accommodating :-)
host_about:
I've lived in San Diego for 7 years and have been hosting Airbnb guests here at my little house for about 3 years now.  It has been great meeting people from around the world and introducing them to my amazing city.  Originally from Northern California, I've lived in San Francisco, Los Angeles, Washington DC, New York, and finally here in San Diego.  I've yet to live abroad, and really hope I get the chance to sometime in the future.  My work schedule is pretty flexible and allows me the freedom to travel and explore often. I like to think I'm a good balance between outdoorsy/city dweller.  Love camping, skiing, hiking, sleeping on the beach, backpacking, as well as night life, bars, restaurants, historic sites, museums, etc.

I have made friends from all over the world through Airbnb, which is probably my favorite thing about being a host.  I've had guests from all corners of the globe, and its amazing to hear all of their unique stories.  I'm happy to give restaurant, or neighborhood recommendations, and even on occasion taking my guests out on a little tour.  I want my guests to have the best possible time during their visit to San Diego.

Basic office supplies are also provided, even fax/scan, printer, if req'd. Large walk-in shower + outdoor shower - for after beach activities. Hi-speed Wifi  Shared yard with outdoor dining area and small patio. Full sized washer and dryer (includes bio degradable detergent) located on exterior of main house. Outdoor gas and charcoal BBQ. No A/C, but you won't need it. The weather is amazing year-round and there is a beautiful breeze off the ocean. House is equipped with a gas
interaction: Give my guests space but am available when needed I live nearby and welcome interaction. I'll take your lead on how much....I'm   willing to be your local guide, take you on a hike,  Stuart might take you for a surf, share a glass of wine or craft brew with you, and show you what I love about San Diego.
house_rules: - Quiet time after 10:00 pm - No shoes in home please
host_about:
Hi I’m Stuart- I’ve been living in North County San Diego for a good 40 years now and I have lots of love for this place I call home. I’m happy to share with you many of the amazing known and unknown sights and experiences that the greater San Diego area has to offer. From Torrey Pines State Beach at our doorstep to the nightlife downtown  I’m happy to help you get the most from your stay. Feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns about your upcoming visit to out beautiful place in the sun.
A Big PS: This property has been with airbnb for several years with a 4.98 star rating on all accounts. The former manager/owner is now overseas and has asked me to take over. He was a top rated super host and I hope to earn your business and trust as well. Thanks!

name: * Ocean Breeze Holiday - Steps to Sand + Bikes!
summary: This fully outfitted studio is setup for getting the most out of your beach vacation. Studio features super comfy queen bed and relaxing living. Located steps from the sand in Mission Beach!  We supply you with beach towels, beach chairs, & boogie boards, PLUS the use of 2 bicycles for riding on the boardwalk! Outdoor shower for rinsing off. Ideal space for 2 people. Ideally located next to the beach and just 2 miles from Sea World & 8 miles from the airport! Perfect for travelers without a car.
space: If you're looking for a relaxing beach getaway look no further!  This cozy little beach vacation rental offers all you need for a fun filled beach vacation.  It is positioned in the ♡ of Mission Beach, a gorgeous beach community on a super narrow strip of land between the Pacific Ocean and Mission Bay. Walk in either direction (West or East) and you'll encounter pristine white beaches. Both sides have wide boardwalks for bicycle riding or walking. On the bay-side you'll enjoy a relaxing sail bay with a calm atmosphere, while on the ocean-side you'll enjoy ocean waves for surfing and a lively beach scene.  Either way, you'll call it paradise. We simply call it home!    The vacation rental is a small studio. There is a queen size bed and a sofa. (The sofa does not pull out.) It offers one bathroom and a fully supplied kitchen.  The kitchen includes a stove, refrigerator, microwave, blender, and a coffee maker. We supply you with all the cooking pans, dishes, and utensils you might need.

neighborhood_overview: The best thing about the neighborhood is that there is so much within walking distance that you may not need a car.  You could just take a taxi from the airport (8 miles away), get dropped off here and you're at the beach!  We have local restaurants, trendy beach bars, excellent coffee spots, and breakfasts cafes all within a few short blocks.  Sea World is just 3 miles away. The location is the best spot of all of Mission Beach.  It is on the south side of Santa Clara Place (the only traffic light in North Mission Beach), which means a non district area. It is far enough (1 mile) north of the roller coaster area so it's very removed from the tourist noise. It is off of the main boulevard with friendly neighbors and a quiet homey atmosphere.   Recreational opportunities abound. This beach rental is a few minutes walking distance to Santa Clara point where there are numerous recreation activities and rentals available including: stand up paddle boards, kayaks, jet skis, windsurfing, cat
notes: This property does NOT include a parking space and therefore this unit is recommended for people traveling without a car.  Due to its location across from the beach, street parking can be very challenging, especially during the summer months, late at night, or sunny weekends the rest of the year. Most guests arrive via Uber/Lyft. Once you get here there is no need for a car. The beach is across the street and there are plenty of restaurants and bars within walking distance.  The space is quite small and compact. We recommend this unit for just 1 or 2 people.  The couch does not open into a sofa bed.  For guests with infants or toddlers, we can supply you with a pack and play and high chair upon request. We supply you with up to 2 beach cruiser bicycles for cruising down the boardwalk. Should you need additional bikes or helmets there is a bike rental shop a couple blocks away. (They also rent kid-sized bikes and baby seats if you need those too.)  You will have access to a patio and BB
transit: To orient you here are some distances from the home: 3 miles to Sea World 4 miles to La Jolla Cove 5 miles to Historic Old Town 8 miles to San Diego Airport 9.5 miles to San Diego Zoo/Balboa Park 10 miles to Gaslamp Quarter If you don't bring a car you will be fine. More than half of our guests have come without a car and all have gotten around quite easily.  Restaurants, shops, and convenience stores are within walking distance.  It is less than a 10-15 minute walk to Belmont Park where there is a giant roller coaster, rides, restaurants, bars, and shops.   Uber cars are readily available for local transport at an affordable rate. If you've never used this service before download the phone app and use this code to get your first ride free (up to $15): janetb397. Riding bikes along the boardwalk is usually the most scenic way to get around and take in the atmosphere. We provide 15% off for beach cruiser bicycles at a nearby rental shop just 3 blocks away that rents bikes by the hour, d
access: We offer self-check in via lockbox. You will have private access to the unit so you may come and go as you please.  Included with the rental is the use of beach cruiser bikes, boogie boards, beach towels, beach chairs, beach umbrellas, and sand toys for the kids. Plus there is a rental shop just a 3 minute walk away that rents surfboards, wetsuits, stand up paddle boards, kayaks, etc. They have very affordable rates, plus we give you a 15% discount on all the rentals they have to offer after booking with us.  There is plenty street parking and nearby free parking lots. (However, during the summer months we highly recommend not renting a car because due to the beach being across the street parking will be in high demand. Other times of year street parking is very doable.)
interaction: My husband and I are your hosts (Janet & Scott). We live one block away. We typically offer a self-check in so you can arrive at your convenience, anytime after the 3 pm check-in time. We live a block away and will always be available to answer questions during your stay. While we prefer communications through the Airbnb messaging on their phone app, we do provide you our cell phone numbers for calling if any urgent needs arise.  Before your stay we are happy to suggest our favorite restaurants, tourist attractions and will help you get acquainted with the area.
house_rules: House Rules  Airbnb Smart Phone App: We request all of our guests download the Airbnb App to their smart phones. We will do most of our communications through Airbnb but feel free to phone us if there are any urgent matters. Please let us know if you do not have a smart phone so that we can communicate by other means once you have arrived.  3 pm Check in time (or anytime after) 10 am Check out time (strict) Check in and check out times are strict unless prior arrangements have been made. Exceptions can be made for a nominal extra fee only when there are no other conflicts in the cleaning schedule, maintenance, and with other check ins and checkouts.   Checkout procedures:   For your convenience you are able to do a self-check out. Take out the trash and put it in the trash bin out back (west side of bldg). Be sure to do your dishes before you go, we'll empty the dish rack. If you tracked in any sand from the beach please sweep or vacuum it up. When leaving close the windows, leave the
host_about:
Hi! We are Janet and Scott. We live on the beach in San Diego with our toddler.  We absolutely love being AirBnb hosts and find delight in sharing the beautiful area where we live!  

We make every effort to make sure you feel relaxed and comfortable during your stay and that you get the most out of your time while in San Diego, whether that means sightseeing around town or just chilling out on the beach. We provide you with activity ideas and favorite local restaurants.  We are available when you need us. We live around the corner to most of the properties and can be easily contacted through Airbnb messaging most any time of the day. Let us know if you have any special needs or requests and we will do what we can to accommodate you.

With AirBnb, we've found all of our guests to be delightful people. We will welcome you as friends and look forward to showing you our bit of paradise on the beach!

name: New! SKYLINE VIEWS! Awesome Location!
summary: We recently upgraded this sweet space! Enjoy sweet views of the city scape from a private deck off the master bedroom! This home was thoughtfully designed with the Trendy Airbnb guest in mind. Location is perfect for seeing all major attractions and there is plenty walking or biking distance! You'll love it!!
space: Our heart and soul went into the design and functionality of this awesome space. We completely gutted and upgraded this space to make it especially unique but stylish and sophisticated with a modern mid century twist.  What make our place unique you ask? The view. Golden hill is a trendy neighborhood perched a top a hill with city and bay views. Out home sits on top of a hill--on top of the hill-- and the unit is 2 story's so the upstairs is like a nest in the middle of an urban neighborhood. It's gets great trade wind breeze and great light. Wake up with a cup of coffee and enjoying the sunrise and fill the sky with light--right from bed! Ya know, It's the little things in life!

neighborhood_overview: conveniently located on the boarder of balboa park and just down the street from the Gaslamp. Golden Hill is the very best location if your planning on visiting many different areas in San Diego with HWY 5 & the 94 just close enough to not hear it!  Golden hill is a trending up and coming neighborhood. Although it's in a dense urban area, it still has that sort of small town feel. There's an awesome local bakery, a neighborhood butcher, typical diner, market and much more! We think it's perfect!
notes: Every home has its quirks...please note the following; -Dense urban area -right on the bus line  -8 mins from airport so you WILL hear the occasional plane -a small dog has lived in this property so FYI if you’re allergic -street (Website hidden by Airbnb) curb your tires and watch out for street cleaning or you may be ticketed! Especially on Tuesday and Thursday!
transit: Uber and Lyft are great options since we are very centrally located to many different attractions. Ask you might want to try Bird scooters. They are everywhere and are a fun way to zip around and now worry about parking.
access: Guest will have full reign of the place
interaction: We try to meet you in person but if not we are always available should you need anything more to make your stay more comfortable.
house_rules: Checkin time is at 3pm Checkout is at 11am No parties No smoking Quite hours at 10pm strictly enforced
host_about:
Like you, We are passionate travelers with 30 years combined experience in hospitality and customer service, and have ourselves many times, opted for private rentals--in search of the best home away from home experience at an affordable price! 

After our own first hand experience the rental world – misleading photos, poor housekeeping, and lack of management by the rental agencies - We knew our passion for travel and hospitality would culminate in America’s Finest City, San Diego, with one fundamental element in mind: the friendly hospitality service every traveler yearns for. Whereas the traditional rental world lacks the vital follow-up service and care, we are committed to ensuring your stay is nothing short of spectacular!

Looking forward to hosting you! 

Warmest regards,

Holly, Devin, & Halo

The location is ideal, but it’s not a space to throw parties nor is it a space for more than two people. I invite guests to use my kitchen, enjoy the large front patio, and have quick access to the best beaches in San Diego! It is a more happening neighborhood, with some relaxed bars and casual dining nearby, but overall a pretty quiet neighborhood. I also have a sound machine for sleeping and my amazon Echo device for music, which makes all the difference if needed!
host_about:
Greetings!
I am a nature lover and local stylist in San Diego. I am outgoing and service oriented! I have a small dog who is well trained, doesn't bark but he is very friendly. We love to take hikes and go on road trips whenever we have free time. As a stylist, I get to cut, color and style hair while helping clients feel beautiful inside and out! I worked for years in the fashion industry as well, it's hard to call it work since it's my passion and it brings me so much joy! 
I am pretty social, but I can be a homebody as well so I look for the same in my guests. Quiet beach bungalow.  
Please feel free to email me anytime if you have questions about my home please let me know! We look forward to meeting you!

Safe Travels, Laura Claire

name: Look out over Little Italy from a Unique Urban Treehouse
summary: Marvel at 180-degree city and bay views in this sunset-facing industrial penthouse atop a design-focused building by a local architect. Relax on the succulent-filled private patio with a cup of locally roasted coffee or a glass of red wine on tap. Important notes:  — The space is accessed via a five-story flight of outdoor stairs & there is no elevator.  — As expected with city living, street noises are often heard in this unit.  This space booked? Check out our other listings:  https://www.airbnb.com/users/81135905/listings
space: Urban Treehouse is a bright and charming unit located in the heart of San Diego’s beloved Little Italy neighborhood. Housed on the very top of a design-focused building by a local architect, the apartment is extremely unique, comfortable, with loads of character and industrial touches. There is an airy kitchen area with a stove, oven, a mini fridge, gold-trimmed vintage glassware & complimentary local coffee. We encourage you to enjoy soak up stunning bay views on the expansive outdoor patio which has an urban feel with warm touches such as string lights and a ton of succulents. We offer our guests a complimentary welcome drink as well as bikes to use during your stay. A few important notes:  — The space is accessed via a five-story flight of outdoor stairs, and there is no elevator available. neighborhood_overview: The penthouse sits in one of San Diego’s most charming neighborhoods: Little Italy. It’s known to locals as the epicenter of culinary hotspots. The area is extremely walkable and bikeable and just a few blocks from the gorgeous San Diego Bay.
notes: This is no smoking and no pets allowed at this property (inside & on patios), and is not a location for hosting large groups/parties. There will be a $500 extra cleaning fee for smoking or bringing pets. There is another private AirBNB unit directly below this unit, so please only use your designated deck. As with all AirBNB properties, please treat our space as you would your own & respect the neighbors.
transit: The Urban Treehouse is conveniently located in the heart of San Diego’s Little Italy neighborhood. The area is extremely walkable (and bikeable) — and you’ll be just a few blocks away from the some of the best restaurants in the city & a few blocks away from the gorgeous San Diego bay front. Parking in Little Italy can be a bit tricky/expensive (as with any city), but we have one parking spot available to reserve for a minimal daily fee ($10 per day). This spot is shared between both of our units and priority is given to whoever reserves first - just inquire if you have any questions on this. If you don’t have a car, you can easily get around by bike, Uber or taxi as well as the trolley (the nearest station is just a few blocks away).
interaction: We want to make sure you have an incredible experience in San Diego, and we are happy to help at any time by phone or email during your stay if you need recommendations or have any questions. When you arrive, we also have a full welcome book that outlines our favorite places in the neighborhood and activities in the city.
house_rules: All photo and film shoots must be approved in advance and there may be an additional location fee if approved.
host_about:
We’re Stephanie & Nathan, a 30-something couple that is passionate about good food & drinks, travel and going on adventures. Stephanie is a Colorado native, a compulsive global wanderer, and a closet coffee snob. Nathan is a ceviche-loving Washington transplant, and sneaks away to Baja, Mexico every chance possible. 

We love to call San Diego home. In our free time, we paddle board, watch sunsets, go on picnics, try new restaurants, bike in different neighborhoods, make bonfires on the beach and simply enjoy living in this beautiful place. We both enjoy connecting with new people and sharing stories, and we’re sincerely happy to host you. In our travels, we have realized the place you stay in while visiting a destination can make or break an experience. Our goal is to make your experience, so please let us know if there’s anything we can do to make your time here better.

neighborhood_overview: All travelers will feel safe in this very desirable, quiet, suburban neighborhood where neighbors still look out for each other.   It's a great walking neighborhood, and has a park and nearby hiking trails. There is a strip mall with grocery store ~ 2 miles away, and many retail stores and restaurants within a few minutes drive. Beach is ~ 8 miles away. Large indoor mall about 8 miles away in Escondido. There are a couple of fitness facilities with pools within a few miles.
notes: There are many micro breweries a short drive away, as well as nearby wineries. San Diego has special events going on all the time. Always something to see and do whether traveling solo or with others.
transit: Convenient to I-56 East/West which goes to beach and I-15 North/South which connects to other highways. There is public transportation a short drive away.

Indoor washer/dryer, iron & board. High-speed wifi

name: Private City Apt. with backyard!
summary: Hello! We are a young couple living in San Diego with our dog Bear. We often like to camp/travel, so while we are away we like to open up our home to guests visiting or staying in the area! Our space is perfect for 1-2 people looking to stay close to everything that San Diego has to offer! We are a short Uber ride to downtown & Little Italy, the Beach, and walking distance to Balboa Park and some great restaurants.  We also have a backyard, fire-pit and grill that you are free to enjoy as well!
space: Our unit is hidden in a quaint nook of the house with a wrap-around porch that offers a view of the sunset. We are one block away from local corner stores, and some great places to eat like: Papa's & Taco's Mexican Food, Bankers Hill Restaurant (a must!), and the Hob Nob Hill Breakfast Restaurant. We are also walking distance to Balboa Park including everything it has to office such as the San Diego Zoo, Air & Space Museum, Comic-Con Museum, Natural History Museum, and the Spanish Village Art Center.

zipcode: My husband and I like to interact with people but also appreciate privacy.   We have lived in La Jolla for 40 years and have raised our children here. They left the nest some time ago.  We are very interested in people and their stories. There is still so much to learn from others. We have travelled extensively ourselves and now enjoy being settled down. My husband Reinhard is very active with kayaking and swimming in the ocean. He enjoys woodwork, building kayaks and recently tried some artwork.   My swimming days are over but I still love walking and some biking.  My hobbies are knitting and crocheting beanies, booties, scarves and knitting blankets with leftover yarn .  We do our best to make our guests feel comfortable. We love kids and we still have the toys our kids played with.

Chuck, my husband, is a retired architect and my back ground is in interior design, photography and art. We are very adventurous, athletic and outdoorsy. We love to travel and have been to many places. I am from the Netherlands, so we travel back to Europe quite often. It is one of our favorite destinations. There are so many other places we want to see one day, especially South America and explore more of Mexico. We enjoy the Mexican people and their culture very much. We can't complain about the food either. We are not much into 5 star traveling, even though we have done it from time to time. We find that when you go off the beaten path and stay at different homes, B&B's or small non-chain hotels instead of big luxurious hotels, you meet the most interesting people and learn the most of one's culture.

Our moto in life: collect as many positive experiences and friends rather than personal possessions.

name: Beachway Hobbit Home
summary: 1 bd/bth apt. is centrally located, less than 2 blocks from beach & main avenue, where you'll find the heart of OB. From restaurants, antique shops, bars, & all things eclectic to OB. Full Kitchen, wifi, & SMALL (12.5') alley parking space.
space: The bedroom contains a full/queen size bed and a long comfy couch with a TV that we can provide access to Roku with our Netflix & Amazon Prime accounts. Will also provide wifi, kitchen, and an alley parking spot that will fit a compact car 12.5 feet in length. 2 adult size very old bikes available for use.

The bedroom contains a full/queen size bed and a long comfy couch with a TV that we can provide access to Roku with our Netflix & Amazon Prime accounts. We'll be living in the apartment in front of yours, so if you have any questions or would like to grab or beer/wine etc. or bbq out we love meeting new people! Howeve
neighborhood_overview: Ocean Beach is an old hippie town known for it's 70's reputation. There are some great restaurants and natural wonders to experience. Such as, Sunset Cliffs which are amazing and a sight to see before eroding away. Dog Beach is just a couple blocks away as well as the longest west coast pier, which doesn't require a fishing license.
notes: Ocean Beach is near the airport so plane traffic is between 6:30am-10:30pm.  We also, do have a cat and a puppy that will be on premises. So if you're allergic or don't like critters, please note. They will not be in your apartment, however may from time to time be in the shared patio area. Since we have a full house when it comes to animals we don't allow guests to have any during there stay. There are also personal and sentimental items that we wish to be undisturbed.
transit: Parking is tough especially in the summer months, so that parking spot will come in handy! Please note, it's a small spot in the alley roughly 12.5' long. Many bike rentals available either by a nearby shop/Jump or birds/lime scooters. Otherwise Uber and Lyft are a friend, if you'd like to see what else San Diego has to offer, but if your trip is short everything is pretty much walking distance from our little hobbit home.

neighborhood_overview: The place is located on a quiet street in north Pacific Beach.  Approximately 5 blocks from the beach. A short walk to the beach and to all the restaurants and shops on Garnet Avenue.  There is always plenty of street parking in front of the house.
notes: I want to make sure you know this is a bungalow cabin and not a 4 or 5 star type of accommodation. Its not a brand new condo. It has a cool cabin like feel to it. Please see pics. Southern California in the winter is fairly mild overall but it can get chilly on some nights. The bungalow does have a fireplace for if it gets down to where you may need to warm the place up at night, but it does not have a furnace or heater. host_about:
While David, my husband, is a real Californian, I myself moved here from Germany 8 years ago.
Having family in two continents - we are proud parents of five young adults - we travel as often as possible. 
Our first experience with airbnb was as guests and we liked it so much that we decided to open our doors for travelers like us.
We believe that our little cottage is located in a very beautiful spot of the world, and we hope it will serve our guests as a cozy home base for their explorations to the manifold tourist attractions in Southern California.
Besides our family, some of the passions David and me share, are: practicing Yoga, hiking the state, checking out the infinite number of restaurants around and studying cross cultural relations, psychology and meditation.
My favorite hobby is gardening in my garden, followed by photography and playing the guitar, whereas David enjoys political discussions and, as an engineer, is always up to date with the newest software developments.

host_about:
Hi and thanks for checking out my property!  My name is MJ and although I wasn't born in So Cal, I moved to Mission Beach with my family when I was 13.  I spent the next 10+ years living in the beach communities of both Mission and Pacific Beach, graduated from Mission Bay High and attended SDSU.  It was in my late 20s that I moved to NY, where I finished my Undergraduate degree and earned my Masters.  

Although I enjoyed spending 7 years on the East Coast, home was in San Diego and I made it my mission to return back home without changing employers.  I needed to get back to the beach and I was fortunate in that an opportunity allowed me to move back in 2010.  Starting in 2013, I actively worked with my real estate agent to find the perfect property, which is this gem :).

I purchased the condo in Dec 2015 and have been up and running hosting on Airbnb since March of 2016.  While this is an investment, I'm heavily involved including being a member of the HOA board.   I've done quite a bit of upgrades and living only 1 mile away from the condo proves itself to be invaluable time and time again. 

I take pride in providing a clean, comfortable and affordable place to stay.  I aim to ensure that those are the critical as that's what I look for when on personal or business travel.

While I do have a day-job"

You will be able to self check-in upon arrival or I can show you around if you'd prefer. Sherman Heights is named after Mathew Sherman who purchased the land in 1867 jus
neighborhood_overview: Sherman Heights is named after Mathew Sherman who purchased the land in 1867 just after Alonzo Horton purchased much of the area in now Downtown San Diego. Sherman Heights is known for the beautiful historic building named the Villa Montezuma which was build in 1887 by world traveler, noted spiritualist and pianist, Jesse Shepard. Sherman Heights is a historic district with primarily historic homes. Since the turn of the century up until today, Sherman Heights has had a variety of immigrants come from all over the world. In the 1920's a wave of German-American's came through Sherman Heights followed by waves of Japanese-Americans through the 1940s, African-American's through the 1970's and lastly a wave of Mexican-American's from then until today.

neighborhood_overview: Cortez Hill is a little-known residential neighborhood just at the edge of the downtown district, bordered on the other side by Balboa Park. The Gaslamp, Little Italy, Balboa Park and zoo are walking distance, or a short ride away. Entrance to state highway 163 is four blocks away. Interstate 5 south is two blocks away, allowing access to highway 94. Access to the 5 north is a few blocks further.
transit: You do not need a car here for most local trips. Uber or Lyft are recommended for trips to places out of the area (such as Coronado Island). You can also take a taxi from the airport, which is only 2.5 miles away. Bicycle sharing options have taken root here, as have electric scooters. FRED (Free Ride Every Downtown), is easily accessed through an app. Drivers will pick you up in a gem car at your location for free.The service runs from 7AM to 9PM Monday through Friday, and 7AM to midnight on weekends. It covers an area from 17th Street to the convention center. You can get the app online, as well as any further information you may want.
access: The front porch looking out past magnolias onto the jacaranda-lined street is available to all guests, as is the comfortable lobby. You will usually find that you can have these areas to yourself.
interaction: One of us is usually on the property. We are available to help.

name: Serene San Diego Canyon Getaway
summary: Our cozy studio-style guest house perched above a tree-filled canyon is a serene getaway in the center of San Diego, just a few minutes' drive to all local tourist attractions. The casita is comfortable for two or even a small family, with kitchen capacity to prepare at-home meals.  Our weather here is temperate, but if it gets really hot we have a silent A/C unit to cool down the casita whenever it's needed.
space: Our guest house overlooks a canyon with a nature conservancy atmosphere: our tree-filled yard hosts hummingbirds and many other avian visitors. We live in the Clairemont area of San Diego, close to central San Diego and its diverse neighborhoods. The coastal communities of Ocean Beach, Mission Beach, Pacific Beach and La Jolla are just a few minutes from here. Sea World is down the hill from us, and Balboa Park, with our world-famous zoo and many different museums, is a short drive from here. We provide broadband (wi-fi) internet access and a flat-screen TV. The lounging area features two comfortable Bellini chairs. The queen-size bed is in a sleeping nook next to French doors that open onto the canyon. We now have a silent A/C unit to keep the casita as cool as you like, no matter what the outside weather may be.  Louvered privacy blinds on all the doors & windows provide privacy or shade from our typically bright sunlit days. The kitchen area has a four-burner stove, spacious counter

neighborhood_overview: Our Clairemont neighborhood is a centrally located right above Mission Bay, so you can drive to most destinations in a few minutes: 10~15 minutes to downtown, Balboa Park (museums, zoo), La Jolla, Pacific Beach, Ocean Beach & other coastal areas; 15~20 minutes to north county (Del Mar, Encinitas), or south to the South Bay area and the border (Tijuana, Mexico).
notes: This neighborhood offers a lot of shopping options, from the usual supermarkets and health food stores (Sprouts, Whole Foods) to a wide range of Asian, Middle Eastern, European and Latin American markets as well. Check our Guidebook notes. Sprouts is nearby (three minutes), and many other markets within a few minutes' drive offer high-quality produce and organic foods of many different styles. Just east of here is the Convoy Street corridor with many Asian markets & restaurants; Chinese, Japanese, Korean, VietNamese, Indian, Persian & more -- from full-service markets to bargain dining, both sit down and take-out, and a few more expensive restaurants as well.
transit: Our public transit system (buses) here is poor at best, but trolley lines do offer a convenient option for some outings or for special occasions that provide shuttle service. Most visitors find it convenient to rent a car, or you may use a ride service (Lyft, Uber).  In general having a car is the easiest way to get around in San Diego, but if you prefer to avoid the chore of parking, using a car service is an easy way to go to & from anywhere you want to visit in the city or even within the county. We are a 15-minute drive from the airport. Our street (a cul-de-sac) always has plenty of free parking space.
access: Guests may use our washer and dryer by arrangement.  Many items for children and families are available: high chair, Pack'n'Play crib, baby bath tub, stroller, beach toys, swim gear (face masks & snorkels), beach towels, chairs, umbrella, and more.
interaction: Al is usually home and happy to advise guests on what to see and do in San Diego.
house_rules: Our Guest House is in our backyard, but it has its own private gated entrance from the street and a privacy fence that separates it from our yard. * No smoking inside, please. Smoking outside is permitted, of course. * No pets, sorry--it's simply not practical to host animals in our small space. * Laundry may be arranged by appointment. Ironing board & iron are available by request. * We have numerous accessories for children, as noted in the description. * Parties or gatherings are allowed by arrangement in advance. Our guest house is not large, but our patio has lots of space for small to moderate events. Tables & chairs for extra seating can also be arranged.
host_about:
My wife is a book artist, teacher and co-founder of a small fine arts press. I am an editor, writer, teacher and tutor. We are art and music lovers who work with local arts organizations in many ways.

We have lived here for over 40 years; now we are happy to share our quiet 'getaway' guest house with visitors to San Diego.

We've traveled to Europe, Mexico, the Middle East and Asia; we are pleased to welcome you to America's Finest City" with a perfect climate and many picturesque attractions."

host_about: La jolla resident for the last 30 years.  Easy going, friendly, enjoy meeting new people. At the same time I like to enjoy spending quiet time alone. Enjoy beautiful walks along the ocean, swimming at the cove, ballet, yoga.  Japan is my favorite place to visit.. Love to have a guests who is respectable, kind and friendly. I will be happy to show you around any of my favorite spots, restaurants , walking trails.....

name: Guest House
summary: A terrific location in Normal Heights just 5 blocks to restaurants and cafes on Adams Ave. We're centrally located, close to all freeways, SD Zoo, and Balboa Park. The closest beach is about 7 or 8 miles away, which is a 15 minute drive.  You'll like our comfortable, private guest house and shared garden.
space: Enjoy a complimentary bottle of wine when you arrive. We'll help to make your stay comfortable in any way we can, whether it's telling about all that SD has to offer, or leaving you to yourself.
description: A terrific location in Normal Heights just 5 blocks to restaurants and cafes on Adams Ave. We're centrally located, close to all freeways, SD Zoo, and Balboa Park. The closest beach is about 7 or 8 miles away, which is a 15 minute drive.  You'll like our comfortable, private guest house and shared garden. Enjoy a complimentary bottle of wine when you arrive. We'll help to make your stay comfortable in any way we can, whether it's telling about all that SD has to offer, or leaving you to yourself. You'll enjoy a comfy king size bed. The kitchen area has a mini-fridge/freezer with some bottled water, sodas, and cream for your coffee. There's a toaster, microwave, coffee, coffee pot and grinder. There is also a TV with limited channels, hair dryer, iron, and wireless internet. Enjoy off street parking, and right outside your door is the spa and patio for enjoying San Diego's great weather. If you're here for 6:00 cocktail hour on the patio on either Friday or Saturday, please join us, you
neighborhood_overview: Normal Heights is one of San Diego's centrally located, unique neighborhoods. It's 8 miles from the ocean, near freeways and 4 miles from Balboa Park, downtown and the harbor. One of our favorite restaurants, Dao Fu, is about 8 blocks away on Adams Avenue, where there are other restaurant choices as well.
notes: Sorry, but we have a 3 night minimum booking policy, no pets, and the space is not appropriate for children.
transit: San Diego's metro bus transportation is a block and a half away.
access: You'll enjoy a comfy king size bed. The kitchen area has a mini-fridge/freezer with some bottled water, sodas, and cream for your coffee. There's a toaster, microwave, coffee, coffee pot and grinder. There is also a TV with limited channels, hair dryer, iron, and wireless internet. Enjoy off street parking, and right outside your door is the spa and patio for enjoying San Diego's great weather.
interaction: If you're here for 6:00 cocktail hour on the patio on either Friday or Saturday, please join us, your hosts, Arthur and Don. We live in the main house and may cross paths in the backyard now and then, but the guesthouse is completely private with your own entrance through the gate. When you arrive, just pull up the driveway to the back where you'll see the gated entrance.
house_rules: Hot tub is generally operational, though at times it's down for maintenance. You'll see a list of the house rules when you arrive.
host_about: We've lived in this house for 15 years but have been in SD much longer. Before California, we've lived in New York, Michigan, Colorado, and Arizona. We enjoy concerts, musicals, sailing, sunset picnics, hiking, beach bonfires and traveling as much as we can. We can't live without music, wine and great food!

name: Tree House Retreat in North Park
summary: Bright, private, 2nd story apartment with view of trees, sky, and garden. Beautifully renovated 1 bedroom with full kitchen, dining room, laundry and small deck for sun and sun sets! Bus to downtown on the corner. North Park amenities a walk away. Sweet !!
space: This is such a pretty apartment - and it feels so airy up in the pepper tree. Beautiful light filled rooms; it's a very relaxing space, an urban retreat. I love being up in the trees! The apartment was for many years my art studio but the focus of my creativity gravitated more and more toward music and the studio became lonely and unused. It was in need of considerable repair and renovation so in 2013 I started tearing out the kitchen, removing and repairing all the original double hung sash windows, laying tile, installing cabinets etc. etc. etc. One year later and it is finally ready for your stay.
description: Bright, private, 2nd story apartment with view of trees, sky, and garden. Beautifully renovated 1 bedroom with full kitchen, dining room, laundry and small deck for sun and sun sets! Bus to downtown on the corner. North Park amenities a walk away. Sweet !! This is such a pretty apartment - and it feels so airy up in the pepper tree. Beautiful light filled rooms; it's a very relaxing space, an urban retreat. I love being up in the trees! The apartment was for many years my art studio but the focus of my creativity gravitated more and more toward music and the studio became lonely and unused. The Tree House is the second story above our detached double car garage. We don't use the garage for cars, only storage, so there are n
neighborhood_overview: North Park has so many great restaurants, breweries and shops!  Balboa Park is a huge park the northeast corner of which (Bird Park) is just a couple of blocks away. There are tennis courts and an outdoor pool (which is open most of the year). It will take 15 or 20 minutes to walk to the zoo and the many museums, gardens, the Organ Pavilion, the Japanese friendship garden, the Old Globe theater. Lots to do in Balboa Park! University and 30th is the main commercial area - a 10 minute walk away but there are several other small commercial hubs with a variety of shops, restaurants, bars etc. One is at Thorn and 32nd. Another is at Juniper and 30th and yet another at Fern and Beech.
notes: There is no TV in the apartment. Good wi-fi!  This is a 2 person space but it could accommodate a 3rd person. Please check with me first! Note that this is not a child friendly apartment.   If you are interested in a longer say of a month or more please contact me regarding price.
transit: There is a bus stop just around the corner. Take the #2 bus to downtown where you can wander and discover the city's Gaslamp area, take in a baseball game, check out Little Italy, visit the harbor and Seaport village.  A taxi from the airport will cost about $18.
access: The Tree House is the second story above our detached double car garage. We don't use the garage for cars, only storage, so there are no cars coming and going. There is a small deck adjacent the entrance with a couple of deck chairs, table and umbrella for you to soak up the sun or enjoy the beautiful evening sky. You are welcome to enjoy the garden, too, help yourself to the Meyer's lemons, limes and oranges! There is a parking spot available in the alley just outside the locked back gate to the apartment stairs. You can also park on the street - normally lots of parking space there. There is another locked gate at the front of the property for your use if you choose that to come and go that way.
interaction: My husband, Paul, and I and our house mate Wayne live in the main house. If we are away, Wayne will be here to take care of things during your stay. We'll be here to help you with any questions you may have about the neighborhood, local shops and restaurants.  The apartment has the privacy of an urban retreat and as such you may enjoy it without any interaction with us, as you please.  If you are a musician, I'd love to play with you. We have a piano, guitars, bass guitar and a drum kit in our house. If you are a music student I can give you a theory,  jazz piano or voice lesson!
house_rules: 1. Please don't smoke in the apartment, the deck or in the garden. 2. Please be respectful of the neighbors. 3. Sorry, no pets. We have cats and they aren't happy with strange critters in their space. 4. Please leave your shoes at the door. 5. Children are welcome but please check with me before you book.  6. No parties, please. A few friends over for an evening is fine.
host_about:
I am from Vancouver, B.C. and have been living in the US for 20 years. I'm a musician and artist. I'm a jazz lover; sing jazz and play jazz piano. My husband is a retired UCSD Computer Science prof. We enjoy the outdoors, desert camping, being on the water. I love gardening, cooking and learning new subjects or just digging deep into my current passion. 
I'd like my guests to be comfy and cozy. Help me make your stay the best. If there's anything thing you need - just ask!

name: Seabreeze Family Farm Strawbale House
summary: Welcome to Seabreeze Family Farm! Are you looking for a mini- retreat near Del Mar and La Jolla? Artistic cottage nestled in a  jewel of a family farm with access to almost 2000 natural acres. A charming place to relax, have peace and quiet, enjoy the beauty of nature & animals in a secure & private property.  Close to Torrey Pines Park and ocean. This unique ecological cottage has a kitchen, fireplace, private bath area, private south facing patio and access to fresh garden food.
space: Bring a moderate sense of adventure, a taste for Glamcamping and an ecological awareness.  Wake up to the smell of fresh air, nature & beautiful views. Feel like you are in the country with birds singing, artistic environment and yet close to all retail stores and restaurants.  You will feel very safe & private here. This is truly a place to relax and explore the area. The farm is gated for privacy and security.  We highly recommend arriving before sunset to orient yourself.  The area is like a wild life sanctuary and do not have blazing street lights on the farm.   We are located on the south side of Arroyo Sorrento Road and the nearest major cross street is Carmel Valley Road and El Camino Real.

neighborhood_overview: We are located just down the road from the Del Mar Thoroughbred Club and fair grounds.    Minutes from the San Diego 5 freeway. Close to the Torrey Pines Reserve and many beaches. Excellent restaurants near by or picnicking on the beach.  Freeway close to explore beautiful San Diego.  Miles of natural hiking paths.
notes: This unique and comfortable cottage is recommended for people with a love of the outdoors and nature.  The bath facilities are adjacent to the cottage with an outdoor bath and composting toilet in complete privacy.  This will be a new experience for some, however it's practical, odorless, and helps the environment.  Water is expensive and we ask guests to be very conservative in use.  The outdoor bath's water is for some trees and that's good.  There are no other inhabited  (people) dwellings nearby (well, except for the sweet goats but they're not too close).   The south facing patio is surrounded by fencing and trees and shrubs (one of the hummingbirds favorite housing units).  There is parking for one car only and we recommend using Uber if appropriate.  compact parking requested.  Some pets will be considered however will need supervision as we are next to a nature preserve. Farm-fresh fruits and vegetables for you to pick and you'll have fresh fruits, snacks, 'emergency' foods,  l
transit: We're not close to public transportation and there is parking available for one car.
access: You have access to over 2000 natural acres adjacent to the farm (website is (URL HIDDEN)  for walks and the  Strawbale House for staying in.  We live on the property in a separate home and are available if you have requests or needs.   You have your own private access to the guest house where you can come or go as you please.  Please park your car not blocking vehicles in front of the cottage.  .  24 hr notice if you'd like to use the bread/pizza oven. You will be given the gate code to the security gate when you book.  Go up the long driveway to the top of the bluff, go down the little road to the Strawbale House on the left. It will be open and ready for you.  If you need assistance, please call the cell number given when you confirm your reservation.
interaction: My husband, Kendall, and I live in the top lodgette and we are here to support your stay. We are busy running the farm however will give you a tour if you'd like . We can answer any questions you have about the area or reccomend sites to see.  We are almost always here tending to things.
house_rules: -  Water conservation is a top priority on the farm and if guests use the shower house, we ask you to be very conservative (brief).  The outdoor bath (the water is used for irrigating trees) in your patio is private and relaxing and our recommendation.   - We take pride in our farm & work very hard to keep it running smoothly please be respectful of the area and leave it how you found it. - Parking is limited to the area just outside the strawbale house for one vehicle only.
host_about: Owner and manager of Seabreeze Organic Farm, established 1988.

name: Beautiful apartment in Gaslamp San Diego
summary: You will be staying in a beautiful apartment on the 6th floor with a gorgeous view of the city even from your bed! The amenities include a big study room, a swimming pool, jacuzzi, and gym. The apartment is fully furnished and you will be provided with all the kitchenware to make food at home as well as a spacious refrigerator. You will have access to a free parking spot inside the building, which is protected from the sun and rain.
space: The apartment has 1 bedroom with a queen-size bed and a walk-in closet containing an iron, iron table, hangers, and towels. You will have a full bathroom with a washing machine and dryer. A courtesy cleaning kit and personal hygiene products will be provided as well as a courtesy kitchen kit, a toolbox, a fire extinguisher, a first-aid kit, and a grill all for yourself in the balcony. Its location is ideal: high enough for you to have a wonderful view and avoid the downtown noise, but without compromising the closeness to all kinds of interesting restaurants, bars, convenient supermarkets, pharmacies, etc. I will be happy to give you information about San Diego and different activities that you could do, places you could explore and recommendations for restaurants. I am a food lover!

The North Park Theater and the Ray Street Arts District are also bastions of creativity in the area'. The Los Angeles Times writes: 'North Park has all the ingredients for the cool school: It's culturally diverse and has art galleries, boutiques, trendy bars with handcrafted cocktails and local brews, and foodie-approved eateries.' An eclectic and diverse array of restaurants, as well as independent coffee shops, can be found along the main arteries of 30th Street and University Avenue. The area is also dotted with bars and night clubs that cater to a wide diversity of patrons. Downtown North Park contains the Ray Street Arts District. neighborhood_overview: For those of you new to the Hillcrest neighborhood of San Diego, it is very popular. It has a higher density than other neighborhoods in the city and, therefore, parking is at a premium. Experience tells us that, depending on the time of day, parking on 4th or nearby streets is possible, but can be challenging. Hillcrest is worth it!. Downtown and Convention Center is a short 10 minute scooter/uber/car ride down the hill, so avoid the noisy hotels of the Gaslamp for our little enclave:) Hillcrest is the best place to be in San Diego- cutting edge and happening yet quiet and peaceful... It has blossomed over the past decade into one of the hippest, most happening communities in all of San Diego and is known for its tolerance, youthfulness, culture, and diversity as well as numerous locally-owned businesses, including restaurants, cafés, bars, clubs, trendy thrift-stores, and other independent specialty stores. host_about:
Aloha! I'm originally from Honolulu, Hawaii and I've called San Diego, California my home since 2013. 
I'm a former Hawaii lū'au Polynesian dancer, but I still have a grass skirt on standby :) I love designing art- creating garments, accessories, printing fabrics and sketching.

I've traveled to France, Italy, Spain, Greece, Malta, Canada, Mexico, Thailand, Japan, Taiwan, Samoa, American Samoa, Kiribati, French Polynesia, New Zealand and all over the US, but my favorite destinations are Bali, Indonesia and home in Hawaii (to visit family).

Love hosting Airbnb guests to my home here in Hillcrest and North Park along with my Aloha upbringing!

transit: Plenty of reasonable public transit options nearby, but San Diego is a commuter town and culture, best experienced via automobile.
access: You have access to your  private studio and the grounds of the home, including a roof-top deck.
interaction: I love, love, love helping my guests. Whether is it teaching them how to drive to take their driver's license exam or taking guests to Tijuana for some of the best restaurants on the planet (bring your passport!).
house_rules: This is a great studio but expect my guests to treat it as they would their own home. No Smoking inside or outside.
host_about:
Native San Diegan...Reformed attorney, turned life coach and property manager...father of 2 wonderful ladies and married to the coolest woman on the planet for the last 25 years...love sports (competitive and participatory), reading, dancing, travel and anytime I get to spend on my bicycle. 

Since I have only been on ABB I only have a few reviews...however I have been on Flip key and Home away for a much longer stretch and have a significantly larger number of reviews there so please take a look at them if you would like more feedback on what it is like to stay with us at one of our units.

name: Bright & Private Studio 2 Blocks from Mission Bay!
summary: Studio in apartment complex 2 blocks from Mission Bay! Local restaurants and bars. Walking distance to Pacific Beach and Mission Beach. A 10 min drive to Ocean Beach & Sunset Cliffs. A 12 min drive to the airport, the Gaslamp District, Balboa Park and La Jolla. Includes a kitchen, private patio, and queen size bed. Street parking available - can usually find a spot within a couple of blocks during the day. The area is popular, so it can be noisy and parking may be competitive in the evenings.

name: Casa Mission Valley
summary: Enjoy Summer in San Diego! Steps to trolley...Shops, Dining, Movies, etc. 15 minutes to the pristine beaches, Sea World, the Zoo, and Downtown San Diego. This is a 30 day minimum rental for a fully furnished master bedroom in the heart of San Diego.
space: Welcome to Mission Valley! Central to everything, you will be steps away from the trolley and close to everything San Diego has to offer. The home is situated in a gated community, 20 feet away from the trolley, and 15 minutes away from Downtown, Sea World, Zoo, and Beaches. Enjoy a private bedroom and private bathroom with free wifi. The living area is shared with just one person (me - I will not be home) with natural light and breezes. host_about: San Diego is a big city. A car can come in handy, and we provide parking for you. Many of our guests arrive without a car. Our Beach is just a few houses away, with Restaurants, Night Life, and Shops all within 4 to 10 blocks.  When you want to explore other parts of our wonderful city, UBER & LYFT are very efficient and affordable here. We are also conveniently located 1/2 block from our San Diego Transit Bus system which can get you anywhere and to the San Diego Trolley System.

street: Hi ! We're Steve & Karron Hohe ( HOHE ). My wife, Karron and I are San Diego natives... Born and raised at the Beach. The Beach is in our blood, and an integral part of our lives. We have raised our children here, and are now blessed to have our five grandkids continue the beach lineage. I've been Surfing since I was nine, and Karron is a long distance runner who loves to be able to kick back at the waters edge with a good book.  As the co founder of The Souplantation & Sweet Tomatoes Restaurants over 38 years ago, we have continued a passion for hospitality . As we have retired from the restaurant life, we have not lost that passion.

name: Crown Point Beach Oasis- 2 blocks to the Bay!
summary: • This cozy and charming beach pad is two blocks from Mission Bay and walking distance to several amazing dining options.  • Just a quick bike ride to both Sea World and the Pacific Ocean!  • All amenities provided to make you feel relaxed and completely at home:)
space: We provide just about everything you can imagine: • two beach cruisers with a lock • tv/cable • private outdoor patio with bistro lights  • washer/dryer and complimentary detergent/dryer sheets • fully supplied kitchen • coffee maker and complimentary coffee/tea  • shower/bath • fresh white towels • bed/pillows/sheets • iron/ironing board • large closet with plenty of hangers  • two large sets of dresser drawers • heater/fan • dining table • wine rack • dishwasher • shampoo and conditioner • hair dryer • beach towels  • extra sheets

You will have access to the entire back house you are renting as well as the back private patio that can be accessed right from the bedroom! We live on the property in the front hom
neighborhood_overview: • Crown Point is on the outskirts of Pacific Beach and is significantly quieter and more mellow.  • It is more of a family community and the heart of the town is focused around the beach activities.  • The bay is not nearly as crowded and wild as the ocean/boardwalk and in our minds is much more peaceful!
notes: We are looking for guests who are coming for a quiet couples trip or friend trip (solo guests too)!  The house is not completely child-proof and may not be the right fit for youngsters.
transit: • We have two bikes available for our guests so you can cruise around the bay/boardwalk.  • We are walking distance to: Crown Point Coffee, Rocky's Crown Pub, Bayside Landing, Promiscuous Fork, and more! • You can take a cheap Uber/Lyft to several Pacific Beach and Gaslamp/Downtown dining establishments.
access: PRIVATE SPACE! You will have access to the entire back house you are renting as well as the back private patio that can be accessed right from the bedroom!
interaction: We live on the property in the front home and are more than willing to cater to your privacy needs.  However, our door is always open and we love making new friends!  If you would like to pop over and say hi, we would love that!
house_rules: *We are very adamant on a two-person maximum for our space. * We live in a family-oriented neighborhood. We are looking for guests who will respect the tranquility of the area and the privacy of our neighbors. Loud noise and music will not be tolerated.  * Please ONLY park in the driveway or in front of the house. Parking is extremely limited around the area. * Please no smoking on the property. *Absolutely NO pets (including guests of yours who may come to visit)
host_about:
We are a newly married couple who lead a very active and adventurous lifestyle! We take a lot of pride in where we live and love our community and what Crown Point has to offer. Our favorite thing to do around here is to go on walks along the bay, which we highly recommend! We love a good Rocky's burger (just a few blocks away) and surfing at the nearby beaches. We also love to travel and spend time with our out-of-town families. We want our guests to love San Diego, our home and our area as much as we do! We hope that we can make your stay one you will always remember. 

We are avid Airbnb users almost everywhere we go! We have had some of the greatest experiences and built several lasting friendships throughout our travels. We hope to do the same with you!

We would love to hear about you and your travel expectations!

name: Historic & Bright Downtown San Diego Apartment
summary: Enjoy a historic and bright one bedroom apartment, with downtown and peek-a-boo ocean views. The 1928 castle-like building sits atop of the Cortez Hill, next to the famous El Cortez. This residential part of downtown is quiet and safe. It is also walking distance to many of the best spots in San Diego, including: Balboa Park (0.8 miles) Little Italy (0.8 miles) Gas Lamp (0.8 miles) East Village (1.0 miles) Marina (1.3 miles)  Free WiFi is included.
space: The sunsets in this apartment are incredible due to the fact there are many windows in each room.

house_rules: --No unregistered guests are allowed on the property -Check in is 4pm & check out 11am on the day of your departure. - No street shoes inside- pls bring indoor slipper. - please be respectful to my other guests( if any) -arrival instruction; pls text arrival time on the day of arrival or prior if you know the time... When u arrive, proceed to drive in to  driveway and park( I will guide you through). Unload the luggage and check in. You can move the car later when parking space become available on the street. Daily evening turn down service will be provided including trash removal, freshing up the unit, restocking  whatever necessary. For ladies; pls DO NOT USE TOWELS to remove makeups. Pls use kleenex or make up remover.
host_about: La jolla resident for the last 30 years.  Easy going, friendly, enjoy meeting new people. At the same time I like to enjoy spending quiet time alone. Enjoy beautiful walks along the ocean, swimming at the cove, ballet, yoga.  Japan is my favorite place to visit.. Love to have a guests who is respectable, kind and friendly. I will be happy to show you around any of my favorite spots, restaurants , walking trails.....

neighborhood_overview: We love how close we are to the beach (6 blocks from the village of Ocean Beach) with its eclectic shops and cool restaurants. It's a fun walk down to grab a bite to eat, visit the outdoor Farmer's Market on Wednesdays, or to catch the bus.
notes: PARKING:  Ample street parking. The village and beach is within walking distance, but the walk back home is uphill; we love it and do it all the time! Although public transportation is nearby, we  wouldn't recommend relying on it as it is not all that easy to use.  Uber or Lyft are both great options, but we still recommend having a car while in San Diego. OVERHEAD PLANES: We are near to the flight path of the San Diego airport and provide new, never-used earplugs for sensitive sleepers.
transit: We definitely recommend renting a car while here as San Diego is pretty spread out. The bus system is pretty good, and we are just a few blocks from two bus stops, and Lyft or Uber are wonderful options as well, but again, we do recommend renting a car.
access: No kitchen or food prep area is available, however, your space has a mini-frig and a Keurig coffeemaker with coffee. There are all kinds of cool eateries nearby for breakfast, lunch and dinner (recommendations provided upon arrival).
interaction: We live here and are friendly and helpful, but your space is all your own!

NOTE:  We hold a City of San Diego Rental Business License, and have a TOT and TMD Rental Cert #612141 to whom we pay the required 11+% local hotel tax.

Hi, 

My name is Matt, I'm 26, and I'm from Hawaii. I currently work at a software company downtown San Diego. I graduated from BYU-Hawaii in psychology and mathematics, with an emphasis on consumer behavior and marketing. I'm also a part-time law student. 

I enjoy sports, surfing, eating, relaxing, meeting new people, and renting out my most personal space to complete strangers.

On a slightly serious note, I think Airbnb offers a great service, because I think there's something endearing  about sharing personal spaces with strangers (Did that sound weird?). I hope your stay lightens your burden.

name: Urban Treehouse Jr - Location, Food & Drinks
summary: Perched atop the charming skyline in Little Italy, Urban Treehouse is a hidden gem that features:  +Free welcome drink +Reservations at any CH Projects restaurant/bar +Free locally roasted coffee +Free bike use +Parachute linens + towels +Malin + Goetz bath products +Marshall bluetooth speaker +Clean space with loads of character +Walking distance to city’s best restaurants +Parking spot available - $10/day See our other listings: https://www.airbnb.com/users/81135905/listings
space: Urban Treehouse is a bright & airy, fully-equipped studio located in the heart of San Diego’s beloved Little Italy neighborhood. Housed in a design-focused building by a local architect, the apartment is extremely unique, comfortable, with loads of character and industrial touches.  The lofted bed is queen size and there is a compact kitchen area with a stove top, a mini fridge, gold-trimmed vintage glassware & complimentary local coffee. We encourage you to enjoy the nearly perfect year-round weather on the chic outdoor patio which has an urban feel with warm touches such as string lights and succulents. We offer our guests a complimentary welcome drink as well as bikes to use during your stay. A few important notes:  — The space is accessed via a four-story flight of outdoor stairs, and there is no elevator available. If you’re unable to walk up stairs daily, this is not a good fit for a place to stay. Otherwise, think of it as your daily exercise without the gym fee.  — As expected

neighborhood_overview: Little Italy is one of San Diego’s most charming neighborhoods. It’s known to locals at the epicenter of the best culinary hot spots, so if you like to eat - you’re in the right place. We work in the restaurant and hospitality industry, and we are more than happy to give our guests recommendations for the best San Diego has to offer for every palate. Little Italy is extremely centrally located and will be a breeze to get around to other neighborhoods and attractions.  It’s a 5-minute drive from the airport, an easy walk/drive to the Convention Center, and is 5-15 minutes away from popular destinations like Balboa Park, Gaslamp, North Park, Hillcrest, Sea World, Coronado, & Pacific Beach.
notes: This is no smoking and no pets allowed at this property (inside & on patios), and is not a location for hosting large groups/parties. All photo and film shoots must be approved in advance and there may be an additional location fee. There will be a $500 extra cleaning fee for smoking or bringing pets. There is another private AirBNB unit directly above this unit, so please only use your designated deck. As with all AirBNB properties, please treat our space as you would your own & respect the neighbors.
transit: The Urban Treehouse is conveniently located in the heart of San Diego’s Little Italy neighborhood. The area is extremely walkable (and bikeable) — and you’ll be just a few blocks away from the some of the best restaurants in the city & a few blocks away from the gorgeous San Diego bay front. Parking in Little Italy can be a bit tricky/expensive (as with any city), but we have one parking spot available to reserve for a minimal daily fee ($10 per day). This spot is shared between both of our units and priority is given to whoever reserves first - just inquire if you have any questions on this. If you don’t have a car, you can easily get around by bike, Uber or taxi as well as the trolley (the nearest station is just a few blocks away).
interaction: We want to make sure you have an incredible experience in San Diego, and we are happy to help at any time by phone or email during your stay if you need recommendations or have any questions. When you arrive, we also have a full welcome book that outlines our favorite places in the neighborhood and activities in the city.
host_about:
We’re Stephanie & Nathan, a 30-something couple that is passionate about good food & drinks, travel and going on adventures. Stephanie is a Colorado native, a compulsive global wanderer, and a closet coffee snob. Nathan is a ceviche-loving Washington transplant, and sneaks away to Baja, Mexico every chance possible. 

We love to call San Diego home. In our free time, we paddle board, watch sunsets, go on picnics, try new restaurants, bike in different neighborhoods, make bonfires on the beach and simply enjoy living in this beautiful place. We both enjoy connecting with new people and sharing stories, and we’re sincerely happy to host you. In our travels, we have realized the place you stay in while visiting a destination can make or break an experience. Our goal is to make your experience, so please let us know if there’s anything we can do to make your time here better.

neighborhood_overview: Del Mar is a beautiful neighborhood with world class dining, shopping, beaches, friendly locals, and beautiful nature.  The world famous Del Mar Racing is near by, and it's only 5 minutes away from the ocean. Across the street from my house there is a trendy shopping mall Del Mar Highlands Town Center, where you can grab a coffee, snack, groceries, go to a fancy movie theater Cinépolis, grab a nice dinner, access a bank or get to a pharmacy. All a short walk away from my place. For other things a car is needed. Del Mar and Torrey Pines are two beaches that are the closest (and nicest in my opinion). Del Mar beach has a lovely park and great restaurants. Torrey Pines has an amazing hike trail called Torrey Pines State Reserve with gorgeous ocean views - I think it's a must if you're in San Diego. The I-5 is 2 min away if you would like to go elsewhere, like Orange County, Los Angeles, La Jolla or Downtown San Diego (where the airport is).

Nearby, Newport Avenue is lined with antiques shops, beachwear and surf boutiques, organic groceries, restaurants and brewpubs. name: Hawthorne Historic Inn - Room 101
summary: Hawthorne Inn, a national historic landmark, looks the same as when it was built in the 1890s. Even the interior hallways have not been altered. Very close to the airport, the Convention Center and to Balboa Park which has 17 museums, gardens, the Old Globe Theater and San Diego Zoo.  **The building is directly under the airplane landing path and so can be rather noisy throughout the day until 11pm, although its also very cool to see :) We do provide earplugs to help for light sleepers.
space: If you are coming from the airport, the Uber is about five dollars.  You can rent electric bikes and scooters everywhere in the downtown area. The often are just on the from of the building or nearby.  No real need to rent a car from the airport.  A convenience store is across the street .  So you can buy milk, etc.  Balboa Park is four blocks away!  You can almost walk to the convention center for Comicon.  The Harbor with three floating museums is about the five dollar Uber Ride too.

amenities:
I have been a long-time resident of Pacific Beach and cannot imagine living anywhere else.  You will have a wonderful time here!  

I can provide free airport pickup if you like.
Driveway parking is available for one car.

The room has a full-size bed, sofa, 32” TV, desk, office chair, cabinets, closets, cable, and WiFi.
The home is kept well maintained, neat and clean.

Located in the heart of PB – close to all yet quiet and peaceful.  Walk or bike ride to beach, bay, markets, shops, and night clubs.  Avoid the parking issues.

You will like the large landscaped backyard with BBQ, deck, plenty of chairs, cushions, umbrellas and tables for your enjoyment.

A continental breakfast of fruit, cereals, coffee, yogurt, hardboiled eggs, and pastries will be provided every morning at your convenience. You are welcome to enjoy your breakfast in the garden, in your room or at the dining room table. 

The kitchen has two refrigerators so you will have plenty of room for storing food, drinks, etc.

I have created a Guidebook for you featuring San Diego’s most overlooked locations and experiences, that you will be talking about long after you return home!  I would be happy to give you a tour to any of these, if you find that helpful.

Deco Bike Rental Stations are located throughout the area and there are many shops that rent bikes, surfboards, snorkels, fins, masks, and wetsuits at reasonable prices.

Mission Bay features many miles of bike paths and flat topography, making it possible to see much of the area with minimal street traffic.  Ocean Beach is an easy bike ride via the bike paths along the flood control channel.  This is a funky beach community with many things to do and see.  Such as: Hodad’s famous burgers, a walk on the pier, lunch at the pier café, watch the surfers up close from the pier, check-out the tide pools, and visit the shops.  Great Farmer’s Market Wednesdays 4-8p.
