name: San Diego Harbor with a View! A Unique Experience!
summary: We welcome you to experience one of the coolest, most unique places you could stay, in one of the most beautiful locations in the world! Our boat sits on the water in San Diego Harbor and everything you could ever want to see or do is only steps away! Walking distance from San Diego International Airport, 5 minute Uber ride to Gaslamp Downtown area, steps from 3 amazing restaurants with world class views, and miles of safe and scenic biking paths right on the water! What are you waiting for?
space: Our 36' boat is as cozy as it comes for 2 people.  One main berth (bedroom). Beautiful view of Downtown San Diego skyline. All amenities such as pool/spa, bathroom/shower facilities, and fire pits for hanging out are included! We also have 2 beach cruisers for use to pedal your way around over 6 miles of easy access and safe and scenic bike paths to explore everything San Diego offers. Walk to Coasterra Restaurant and experience great food and a world class view as fireworks go off over the water! Next door is C-level and Island Prime both offering a high end or casual dining experience. Very short distance (5 minute drive) to Downtown Gaslamp area for those wanting a true city experience. Walking distance (1/4 mile) from the Airport for those flying into town. The boat itself has everything you could want in a floating condo on the water! Comfy bed, Bathroom, TV (Dvd or streaming only), Bluetooth Stereo, LED lighting, Water, Coffee Maker, etc. Plus a nice welcome gift will be waiting
description: We welcome you to experience one of the coolest, most unique places you could stay, in one of the most beautiful locations in the world! Our boat sits on the water in San Diego Harbor and everything you could ever want to see or do is only steps away! Walking distance from San Diego International Airport, 5 minute Uber ride to Gaslamp Downtown area, steps from 3 amazing restaurants with world class views, and miles of safe and scenic biking paths right on the water! What are you waiting for? Our 36' boat is as cozy as it comes for 2 people.  One main berth (bedroom). Beautiful view of Downtown San Diego skyline. All amenities such as pool/spa, bathroom/shower facilities, and fire pits for hanging out are included! We also have 2 beach cruisers for use to pedal your way around over 6 miles of easy access and safe and scenic bike paths to explore everything San Diego offers. Walk to Coasterra Restaurant and experience great food and a world class view as fireworks go off over the water!
neighborhood_overview: Quiet and safe with everything you need within walking distance. The world class views at the nearby restaurants will be a welcome treat that you will not want to miss! Being that you are right on the water, every view is a reminder that you are in America’s Finest City!
notes: Waking up on the calm water is unlike anything else you can do and provides a unique way to visit and explore everything San Diego has to offer!
transit: Ubers are always close by as well as Taxi and shuttle services! Or use the 2 bikes provided to go and do whatever you want! Electric Jump bikes and Scooters are also close by!
access: You have access to all Pool/Spa amenities, nice and clean showers, as well as a beautiful gym/rec area to chill at!
interaction: You will have a warm welcome from one of your hosts and will briefly go over and recommend things to see and do while you visit!
house_rules: Due to the small size and limited hot water available on our boat we suggest that the shower not be used. There are very nice shower facilities that are available exclusively for guests of the marina.  The toilet on the boat is for liquids only!  No solid wastes or feminine products may be used on board. No one likes a stinky boat! Full bathroom facilities including showers are available for guests within a few hundred yards from boat. No guests or parties are allowed!!
host_about: Always looking for the next adventure! New sights, new sounds, new people is something we love to experience as often as we can! Good food, good drink, good people is a close second!

name: SunsetPatioCottage:magnificent ocean view La Jolla
summary: welcome to celebrate holidays in SD's top one neighborhood, enjoying the beautiful pacific ocean view and peaceful sunset.     Being super hosts for three years with over hundreds of reviews, to offer this charming ocean-view cottage (single family one guest suite). The guest suite is located in the backyard garden with stunning 180 degree ocean views.  5mins driving to beaches, Cove and La Jolla village. Big Closet: Yes.  -Entertainment: high speed WiFi, smart TV + Apple TV, all apple TV apps and free access to Netflix, HBO Now. -Parking: on property driveway. -Beach kit: 2 beach chairs+beach umbrella, 2 beach towels, 1 cooler box are provided for a perfect beach day.
interaction: I am available when guests need me. Also we like to provide privacy for our guests.

The hosts live on the upper level. - Please share off sand as much as possible before entering the room, it will create all kinds of problems, especially in the shower.  -No shoes house, no loud music after 10pm.
host_about: We are a fun loving sporty couple who love traveling and experiencing various cultures and life styles. We would love to make friends and to share life with nice people from all around the world. We are into movies and cooking on weekends.  Welcome to our cozy and sunny oceanview home in La Jolla.  Landy&Michael

name: Light-Filled Industrial Loft in Little Italy
summary: Sip on the welcome drink and bask in the sense of space that comes from the 20-foot-high ceilings and massive vintage windows. After a refreshing shower with Malin+Goetz toiletries, brew some locally roasted beans in the Chemex coffee maker. Important notes: — As expected with city living, street noises are often heard in this unit. We provide ear plugs & a sound machine.  — The bedroom is accessed via a steep ladder.  — Due to the beautiful 20-ft windows, there can be a considerable amount of light that floods the space, even at night.
space: The loft is a welcoming space located in the heart of San Diego’s beloved Little Italy neighborhood. Housed on the ground floor in a design-focused building by a local architect, the apartment is extremely unique with 20-ft ceilings, massive vintage windows, and industrial touches. There is a compact kitchenette area with a mini fridge with a complimentary welcome drink, reverse-osmosis drinking water, Fellow electric kettle, Chemex coffee maker, and complimentary local coffee. There are not cooking capabilities, but we do have serving ware and silverware for enjoying snacks you pick up from the local farmers market. We encourage you to enjoy the nearly perfect year-round weather on the chic outdoor patio which has an urban feel along with a lemon tree and other greenery. A few important notes:  — As expected with city living, street noises are often heard in this unit. There are a couple of restaurants and bars across the street which tend to play loud music into the night. Please kee
description: Sip on the welcome drink and bask in the sense of space that comes from the 20-foot-high ceilings and massive vintage windows. After a refreshing shower with Malin+Goetz toiletries, brew some locally roasted beans in the Chemex coffee maker. Important notes: — As expected with city living, street noises are often heard in this unit. We provide ear plugs & a sound machine.  — The bedroom is accessed via a steep ladder.  — Due to the beautiful 20-ft windows, there can be a considerable amount of light that floods the space, even at night.
neighborhood_overview: Little Italy is one of San Diego’s most charming neighborhoods. Centrally located, it’s known to locals at the city's culinary epicentre, and as the hosts work in the restaurant and hospitality industry themselves, they know the best places to go.
transit: The loft is conveniently located in the heart of San Diego’s Little Italy neighborhood. The area is extremely walkable (and bikeable) — and you’ll be just a few blocks away from the some of the best restaurants in the city & a few blocks away from the gorgeous San Diego bay front. Parking in Little Italy can be a bit tricky/expensive (as with any city), but we have one parking spot available to reserve for a minimal daily fee ($10 per day). The spots are shared between all of our units and priority is given to whoever reserves first - just inquire if you have any questions on this. If you don’t have a car, you can easily get around by bike, Uber or taxi as well as the trolley (the nearest station is just a few blocks away).
interaction: We live next door, and are available anytime during your stay. Our goal is to make sure you have a wonderful San Diego trip.
house_rules: All photo and film shoots must be approved in advance and there may be an additional location fee.
host_about:
We’re Stephanie & Nathan, a 30-something couple that is passionate about good food & drinks, travel and going on adventures. Stephanie is a Colorado native, a compulsive global wanderer, and a closet coffee snob. Nathan is a ceviche-loving Washington transplant, and sneaks away to Baja, Mexico every chance possible. 

We love to call San Diego home. In our free time, we paddle board, watch sunsets, go on picnics, try new restaurants, bike in different neighborhoods, make bonfires on the beach and simply enjoy living in this beautiful place. We both enjoy connecting with new people and sharing stories, and we’re sincerely happy to host you. In our travels, we have realized the place you stay in while visiting a destination can make or break an experience. Our goal is to make your experience, so please let us know if there’s anything we can do to make your time here better.

Located just down the hill from La Jolla Scenic Drive, Mt Soledad and beautiful sweeping panoramic views of the ocean, bay, and downtown San Diego. No better place to spend an Endless Summer! 10% off if you stay longer than a week! 25% off for a month!

neighborhood_overview: 10 minute walk from California's FIRST surfing only break. One block from a gourmet market, a ton of great restaurants including the best fish tacos in San Diego, Hawaiian food, French food, authentic wood fired Italian pizza, live music and Spanish tapas. We really have it all! Plus the beach and bay are extremely nearby. There are also beautiful parks nearby that are perfect for relaxing afternoons enjoying the sun and looking out over the ocean. Only a few miles from SeaWorld, about 8 miles to the World Famous San Diego Zoo, Balboa Park and downtown as well as the airport.
transit: Getting around on foot is easy especially with the weather being nice most of the year. There are also shared scooters and bikes all over the place. Uber and Lyft are very popular here so you'll never have to wait longer than 5 minutes to get picked up.
access: You'll have access to your own private bedroom which includes a comfy queen sized bed and a dresser you're welcome to use. You're also welcome to hangout in the living room and make use of the home theater. The kitchen, refrigerator, microwave, pots, pans, silverware, glassware, plates, oven and stove, etc. are all available for you to use I just ask you clean up after yourselves and make sure to turn things off after use.
interaction: I'm happy to show you the area and give you many local tips as I have lived here at the beach for over 20 years. Of course I can also stay out of your way if you prefer more privacy during your stay.
house_rules: No drugs/Not 420 friendly (alcohol is OK) No visitors outside of those on reservation No shoes in the house
host_about: Hello I'm a craft beer brewer and surfer who lives at the beach in warm sunny San Diego. I'd like to think I'm a great guest and an even better host. I have hosted folks from all over the world for over a decade long before Air BnB existed so giving it a try was a no-brainer. Before becoming an Air BnB host, was fortunate enough to host roommates in my furnished room from all over the world such as Hong Kong, Italy, France, Germany, Spain, Thailand, and Japan. Now it's your turn! If you decide to stay with me you're not only just at a great place near the beach you'll have access to a great resource on everything to see and do, possibly even drink, that San Diego has to offer!

If you have a car, you'll have no trouble finding easy parking right in front, where I park everyday. Parking is easy, free and plentiful. Mostly single family homes in the house area. Walk to the Park's 'Morley-Field-Sports-Complex' (can do online search of those four words for details), the World Famous San Diego Zoo & more that a dozen museums. notes: We have a 3-day minimum the week of Comic Con 2018. We have a very shy, mostly outdoor black cat that we share custody of with a neighbor. We have wireless Internet. We do not have a TV. The extensive back patio, walkways and yard are private to the home with high fences and locked gates for security. our lot is over 5,000+ square feet; there are many trees and succulents surrounding the multi level patios and walkways. It is a good place to day dream and watch the trees in the breeze, or enjoy the strings of night lights decorate and surround the property!
transit: There are several public transit options that are easy to access. We are located 3.5 Blocks South of University Ave. If you are driving, there is easy, free street parking. neighborhood_overview: Where do I even start!? I'm not saying this because I leave here and I think it's awesome and the perfect neighborhood, I'm saying this because it really is awesome and the perfect neighborhood!!! South Park is a historic, unique and charming place. It's definitely the neighborhood everyone wants to live in. Lots of local small businesses, such as boutiques, shops, restaurants, bars, wine bars, breweries, markets, food trucks, yoga studios, juice bar, ice cream parlor, tattoo parlors, gym, dog parks, and the list goes on and on. Btw there's a Target Express (which I heard this is the only one in the nation) two blocks away. Very convenient and perfect for getting any essentials you need. And the best thing about it, is that it's all walking distance!!! So if you want to experience a real neighborhood filled with everything you need and want! Come to South Park :)  If you'd like to learn more about the neighborhood go to southparkscene
transit: Studio is centrally located, literally walking distance from public transportation and we also have city bikes that you can rent, which are across the street.  Close to all major freeways. 5 minutes drive to Downtown. $10 cab ride to Downtown too, or you can always do an easy Uber/Lyft.  South Park is nestled between Golden Hills, North Park, Balboa Park where all the beautiful museums are, San Diego world famous Zoo, Downtown, Hillcrest and Mission Hills. It couldn't be a more perfect location!
access: Guest has access to its own private studio at all times during their stay. Again - Studio does not come with private parking, but lot's of street parking.
interaction: I've lived in South Park most of my life, so I know the neighborhood, San Diego and Tijuana/Rosarito very well (in case you're feeling adventurous and want to cross the border ;) So I'm more than happy to give you tips and recommendations on what to see and where to go.
house_rules: Just use common sense. RESPECT your surroundings and be mindful of others.  No smoking inside the studio but feel free to smoke outside on the front patio.
host_about:
Love traveling. I was born in California, grew up here in San Diego and in Mexico, then lived in Liberia, West Africa for 3 years. While I was there I started an NGO/social enterprise, called Bosh Bosh, which is an ethical fashion brand that unites people from all over the world that believe poverty can be alleviated by empowering women and girls through education and economic development. It's been an amazing journey thus far...

I'm interested in photography, design, dancing (salsa and african music), social entrepreneurship, start ups, international development, girls education, women empowerment, gender equality, volunteering, and did I mention traveling?? ;)

name: San Diego Casita
summary: This Airbnb has a new owner and may now be found under the title Captivating Casita in Historic Mission Hills."  All reservations made prior to the new ownership will be honored."
space: Wake to the sounds of chirping birds and step out your front door to the outdoor living room furnished with a cushioned loveseat and chairs. Refreshing breezes waft through the space and, in the event of a hot day, the overhead fan cools the air. Dine al fresco at the umbrella covered table and chairs in your backyard oasis. Take a peek through yet another red gate to see beehives nestled next to the fragrant lemon tree and gurgling fountain surrounded by milkweed and buddleia to attract butterflies and birds. Walk around the corner to the front of the main bungalow to take in the hypnotic evening scent of the giant angel's trumpet trees. The private garden surrounding the bungalow and casita has been selected as one of 11 on the 2019 Mission Hills Garden Walk showcasing Birds & Bees, Flowers & Trees.

access: You couldn't pick a better location. Mission Hills is one of San Diego's oldest and most desirable neighborhoods defined by a delightful mixture of old stately homes, quaint craftsman bungalows, and sumptuous mansions lining immaculately-manicured quiet streets. We love to recommend locally owned, independent business and they abound in Mission Hills. Within walking distance of the casita you can get your caffeine fix at Heartwork Coffee Bar or Kettle & Stone before strolling to Venissimo Cheese to stock up on snacks. Dining options are many and one of our favorites is the hip and aptly named Fort Oak.  Nothing beats hand-crafted popsicles and ice cream from Dixie Pops. Lazy Acres Natural Market is three short blocks away with Von's just across the street. Treat yourself or someone back home with a gift from Maison en Provence (a lovely little French store) or Lavish Aromatherapy Spa & Store.
interaction: While the casita does offer a kitchenette with a microwave, toaster, fridge, and coffeemaker it does not provide a stove or oven. Hence the description kitchenette." We do have a cat on the property. Gianni will keep his distance unless you welcome him onto your lap."
house_rules: Venture out for a 10 to 20-minute ride and you'll arrive at Balboa Park featuring the San Diego Zoo and museums galore, Little Italy, the Gaslamp Quarter, Petco Park, or Old Town. And getting to and from the airport is a cinch with a ten-minute ride during off-peak hours.
thumbnail_url: Our casita guests have full access to the outdoor living room and dining area which are shared with the main house. Once you park in your off-street parking space, use the code sent to your before you arrive to open the red gate and escape into your haven of serenity.  Simple door codes, WiFi user and passwords are emailed to you before you arrive so that you can have complete alone time or engage me by text anytime you're in need of assistance or a recommendation.

neighborhood_overview: Located in the heart of San Diego, North Park is a young, hip neighborhood with walkable restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and fun local shopping. It is close to tourist destinations such as Balboa Park, the San Diego Zoo, the Gaslamp Quarter downtown, and a 15 minute drive to the beach.
transit: Bus routes are located within walking distance, although some of the best nightlife in San Diego and great restaurants are a short stroll away. Driving a car is probably ideal for getting around San Diego. Parking is available on site, as well as on the street.

interaction: We are happy to meet you in person or provide the location of a key to the studio, prior to your arrival. We live in the adjoining house, and can be available throughout your stay.
host_about:
I have been living in San Diego for seven years but am originally from NYC. I love my new city and exploring the nearby area. My husband, young son, daughter and I live in the heart of San Diego. We try to travel as much as possible, even though it is sometimes difficult with the babes. Trying new restaurants, listening to music, going to family friendly parks and museums, and having fun outside make for a perfect vacation for our family.

In our previous life (pre babies), we used airbnb while traveling throughout Europe and LOVED the experience. We are excited to begin our airbnb journey again! We love meeting new people and helping them have an amazing vacation in San Diego. We are happy to provide recommendations for things to do and places to go.

name: Mid-century Mediterranean Hideaway
summary: Cozy little eclectic mid-century studio flat, located on the hillside just above the famous Pacific Beach. Stunning views of Mission Bay and the Pacific Ocean.  Quick and easy access to interstate 5, surrounding beaches, Old Town, Little Italy, La Jolla, the airport and the Downtown Gaslamp district are all about 10-15 mins. depending on traffic. Kitchenette has a toaster oven with griddle, coffee/tea maker, microwave, little fridge and a sink. We are not set up for full cooking options.
space: My partner and I have put a lot of our own imagination and attention to detail into this very private and sun filled studio, with and eye towards vintage finishes.  Lush tropical landscaping surrounding the patio and a hammock hanging between the palms under the sun will help you relax after a long day exploring San Diego.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is very quiet and allows for beautiful morning and sunset walks to take in the surround views. Many bars & restaurants, a small market, little brewery, cafes and Mission Bay are with a 1-2 mile walk (30-45 mins.) or bike ride (10-15 mins.) to the south as well as a Costco 2 miles to the north, all locations are just off Morena Bl.
notes: Plenty of street parking right out front.  We are more set up for couples then single people with 1 tempur-pedic style queen bed yet we also have 1 fold down sofa bed as additional sleeping option with extra bedding that we provide a foam pad for to use for more comfort. Our Kitchenette is set up with a small toaster oven with griddle, small coffee pot, Water kettle, microwave, sink and fridge, perfect for making small snacks but not full cooking. We also provide beach towels, a little Ice chest, cooling packs and sandwich containers for your fun Beach adventures.  We live 10 minutes from the beach up on a hill that provides us with cool ocean breezes so we have not needed AC and there is a big fan for you for the unexpected heatwaves we seldom encounter.
transit: Parking is easy as there are plenty of spots on the street out front. Best bet is to get a Lyft, have a car or another option would be an electric or pedal bike as there are some good bike lanes and bike paths which will take you in numerous ways to get to some of the many beaches which is about 6-7 miles from here.
access: Downstairs patio with private entrance through sliding glass doors into the studio.
interaction: Limited, if at all.
house_rules: - No more then two guests, (exceptions may be made for a small child with prior communication), 2nd guest must either have their own airbnb account and be included in their reservation request, or provide full name and copy of their passport or drivers license before reservation date, if 2nd guest will be using sofa bed please be sure to advise  us so we can provide additional bedding, no loud music, no chemicals or food to be washed down kitchen sink, biodegradable soap provided.
host_about: I'm currently living in San Diego with my wife Frances, surfing, playing music, selling real estate and getting out doors whenever possible.

name: Mission Hills Guesthouse w/panoramic bay view
summary: Private level, including private entrance, master bedroom, and balcony (no couch or full kitchen). Completely private! Enter through the side gate, walk down a pathway, and then down a flight of concrete stairs (no railing).  You can have your morning cup of Joe while overlooking the San Diego Bay undisturbed. Or lay out and soak up some sun on the 2 lounge chairs. Amazing panoramic view from Downtown to Coronado, Point Loma, and Seaworld. You'll want to catch at least 1 sunset during your stay!
space: This is iconic Mission Hills, we even have neighbors with a tourist attraction, Harper's Topiary Garden--a pretty great Instagram spot ;) This neighborhood is full of high end, eclectic homes nestled into canyons looking out to the harbor and city.

neighborhood_overview: Located in the upscale community of Mission Hills overlooking the San Diego airport, Downtown, and Bay. Centrally located, you won't miss out on anything San Diego. We are minutes from the vibrant city life of Little Italy and Gaslamp Quarter. If you want to get your relaxation on, pack your beach bag and head to Ocean Beach or Coronado Beach. Want to walk through a beautiful park with museums? Hit up Balboa Park! Are you a fashion junkie and wanna shop until ya drop? Fashion Valley will not disappoint. And you can't miss out on the San Diego Zoo. Whether its for business or pleasure, with a stunning view, and things to do, we've got you :)
notes: For Fourth of July Booker's, this is the best view of the Big Bay Boom fireworks show. You can see up to 5 separate shows.
transit: This location is close to the Washington Street station and the Old Town central hub for the trolley. 10 minutes from the airport. Minutes from Little Italy, Hillcrest, and Balboa Park. name: Captivating Casita in Historic Mission Hills
summary: Step through the inviting red door of this charming casita to your San Diego home away from home. Tucked behind an irresistible 1925 craftsman bungalow, the casita features a comfortable king bed, sofa, hardwood and polished concrete floors, spacious kitchenette, and luxurious bathroom with a shower large enough to dance in. While we don't encourage chores, the full-sized washer and dryer do come in handy. The shared outdoor space boasts a living room and dining area surrounded by lush gardens.
space: Walk around the corner to the main bungalow to take in the hypnotic evening scent of the giant angel's trumpet trees. The private garden surrounding the bungalow and casita has been selected as one of 11 on the 2019 Mission Hills Garden Walk showcasing Birds & Bees, Flowers & Trees.

You couldn't pick a better location. Mission Hills is one of San Diego's oldest and most desirable neighborhoods defined by a delightful mixture of old stately homes, quaint craftsman bungalows, and sumptuous mansion
neighborhood_overview: You couldn't pick a better location. Mission Hills is one of San Diego's oldest and most desirable neighborhoods defined by a delightful mixture of old stately homes, quaint craftsman bungalows, and sumptuous mansions lining immaculately-manicured quiet streets. We love to recommend locally owned, independent business and they abound in Mission Hills. Within walking distance of the casita you can get your caffeine fix at Heartwork Coffee Bar or Kettle & Stone before strolling to Venissimo Cheese to stock up on snacks. Dining options are many and one of our favorites is the hip and aptly named Fort Oak.  Nothing beats hand-crafted popsicles and ice cream from Dixie Pops. Lazy Acres Natural Market is three short blocks away with Von's just across the street.
transit: Venture out for a 10 to 20-minute ride and you'll arrive at Balboa Park featuring the San Diego Zoo and museums galore, Little Italy, the Gaslamp Quarter, Petco Park, or Old Town. And getting to and from the airport is a cinch with a ten-minute ride during off-peak hours.
house_rules: No vaping or e-cigarettes. There are honey beehives tended by a volunteer beekeeper in a secluded area of the garden separated by walls and gates. They are mellow bees and will not bother people unless their space is invaded.

name: The Dust-free, Modern Studio near SDSU!
summary: Our allergy-friendly studio (no pets, no smoke, no dust) is fresh and clean, outfitted with modern furnishings.  It comfortably accommodates two, is in a safe, upscale neighborhood, and is within 10-15 minutes of all of San Diego's major attractions.
space: This recently-remodeled 350 sq. ft. (33 sq. meters) modern studio is attached to our main house.  It is quiet, pretty, private, and in a safe neighborhood.  You have your own separate entrance.   The queen-size bed is topped with a memory foam pad, mattress cover, a cotton mattress pad, and 450 thread-count sheets.  You'll have a fluffy comforter and pillows with zippered, protective pillow covers and pillow cases.   Your private zen-style bathroom has a separate soaking tub, a separate large shower with frameless glass doors, and plush towels.  We've also provided you with shampoo, conditioner, body wash, a hair dryer and snuggly robes.  Your kitchenette has: -  dishes, silverware, glasses, mugs, wine glasses - wine bottle/beer openers - sink - microwave - electric kettle, coffee maker - toaster - small refrigerator/freezer - (There is no stove or oven.) Your studio is equipped with its own dedicated air conditioning (A/C) and heating unit.

neighborhood_overview: Our location is super central and offers easy hop-on-hop-off freeway access. We are just across the freeway from SDSU and 5 to 15 minutes to all that San Diego has to offer: Mission Valley, the San Diego Mission de Alcala, Fashion Valley, Old Town, Balboa Park, the Zoo, Downtown, East County, Qualcomm Stadium, Little Italy, the Convention Center, Seaport Village, Coronado, and our world-class beaches, of course.  My grandparents raised my mom here, my mom and dad raised me here, and we're raising our kids here!  We love Del Cerro!  My mom lives just down the street, my sister lives just up the road - - it's safe, tranquil, and centrally located. We are a short walking distance to a natural foods grocery store, a restaurant, a wine bar, a coffee shop, New York pizza-by-the-slice, a CrossFit gym, and a barber shop.
notes: There is no TV or cable in the studio, but we'll provide you with a Wi-Fi password to use with your phone, iPad or laptop. If you’re traveling with a larger group, check the availability of our other listing that’s on the property: The Happy, Sparkling Clean Guesthouse near SDSU. We request that our guests remove their shoes upon entering the guesthouse to keep sand & dirt at bay and keep the space clean. Of course, this is only a suggestion! If you’re more comfortable with your shoes on, by all means, wear them.
transit: You’ll want to get around San Diego via car. Either rent one or use Uber or Lyft!  Your reservation comes with a parking spot for one car on the street.
access: Enter through a private, gated courtyard, pass the main house, and you'll find your own private entrance to the studio.
interaction: We are available for questions, and we love giving restaurant and sights recommendations, as requested.
house_rules: We understand asthma/allergies, so we like to offer a happy respiratory environment to all our guests. So. . . no pets.  No smoking, whatsoever.  Not even outside, please.   The Studio accommodates two people maximum. **Please don't invite guests onto the property at all.** This is a quiet neighborhood, so if you're looking for a place to relax and refresh, this is it. Thanks!
host_about: I'm a third-generation San Diegan - - passionate about design, dance, language & culture.  My family is the apple of my eye.  :)

name: Craftsman Home - 1 Bed - Great North Park Location
summary: Beautiful craftsman bungalow in fantastic location in heart of North Park.  Huge kitchen with open layout to dining and living room.  Queen bedroom with full bath and large yard, small patio off of bedroom.  Only available occasionally when we are out of town, this is our primary home and we  love sharing with others looking to enjoy San Diego.
space: ** IMPORTANT NOTE ** Please note that this property is a family home and primarily used by a family including young children.  It is not a professional hotel and although we use a housekeeper before and after every guest to ensure a clean stay it is not as immaculate as a Hilton. Additionally, this house is in the urban neighborhood of North Park and is on a lot with a small cottage behind the home, on the rear of the lot and accessed via the same shared yard.  Urban areas often have people walking and neighboring properties that are nearby and there is noise.  The property does not have AC and uses fans and a whole house fan to enjoy the temperate San Diego weather.  If any of these things will bother you please do not book our property.  It is a wonderful home in the heart of a great neighborhood but is not a great fit for everyone.  We would gladly host any of our friends or family in our home, but everyone has different preferences.  ** Great location in San Diego's best neighborho

neighborhood_overview: North Park is the best neighborhood in San Diego. Central location and tons of shops, breweries, coffee shops, etc.  If you want a great experience you won't find a better area to stay in than North Park.  Our property is just two blocks from the center of the neighborhood so very easy to walk, bike, and enjoy all that San Diego has to offer.
notes: Listing includes full kitchen access and a stocked private bathroom with linens, towels, toiletries, etc.
transit: Well served by bus lines and great for walking or biking.  Freeway connections nearby as well.
access: This listing is for a beautiful 1920s Craftsman Bungalow in a great location in North Park.  It is for the whole home, including the following spaces: One bedroom - one queen bed One bathroom - recently updated with subway tile and new toilet, paint, etc. Kitchen Living Room Dining Room Yard A second and third bedroom in the home is not accessible by guests.
interaction: We offer this property to guests while we are not in town, so communications will be done from out of town.  Our property manager and housekeeper live in the area and will be available for in-person needs, if any arise.
house_rules: No smoking or any drugs except alcohol. Not suitable for large groups or events. Quiet, respectful guests only.
host_about:
I live in San Diego, enjoy hiking, running, reading, cooking, and trying to surf.  I love learning about my adopted city and am happy to share recommendations and insights on the local scene for outdoor activities, restaurants, bars, breweries, museums, and whatever else you might be interested in.

I enjoy travelling via Airbnb to stay in neighborhoods and experience places less as a tourist.  Hosting via Airbnb has been a great way to showcase our great city and give visitors an authentic feel for San Diego.

name: Cozy Refuge in the Heart of the Action
summary: On the same street as Balboa Park and the San Diego Zoo, this small one-bedroom apartment is in the midst of the lively neighborhood of University Heights. Outside the door is a happening block of international restaurants, boutiques, coffee houses, bars, lounges and a craft brewery. Within a block are are markets, live theater, public transportation and a community park popular for free summer concerts. At the end of the day retreat to a cozy, restorative haven where urban noise is silenced.

name: Travel Twin Artist Retreat w/ Pool & Jacuzzi!
summary: Enjoy this incredibly relaxing and cheerful artistic space to relocate while your in San Diego! This home can be booked anywhere from a 1 bedroom or up to 4 bedrooms. It's cozy, comfy and you'll feel right at home! We welcome everyone plus your furry loved ones! Although we are family friendly, please let us know if you have children. We are close to all major freeways, Sharp Hospital, Fashion and Mission Valley malls, restaurants, shopping, all San Diego beaches and of course Downtown!
space: Welcome to CASA De ARTISTA ~ Travel Twin Bedroom w/ shared guest hallway bathroom (Options to add on additional bedrooms in house at extra cost). This is an artist's home with many paintings and artistic flourish through out. Tastefully and cheerfully furnished! You will love the colors! We just remodeled the kitchen and living room and it is unique and beautiful! This is a place for the visual senses and perfect place for kick back – enjoy the tranquility. Any artist would love to call this space their home! We have furnished each room up to hotel standards and to make you feel welcomed.   Included - •Linens, towels, washcloths  •Flat screen TVs in every room and DVD players in every room except Travel Twin •High speed wireless or direct connect internet in every room  •Washer/dryer located in the garage •BBQ  •Full use of the house except for Master Bed/Bath 2 which can be added on at extra cost •Wood floors throughout  •Blow-up beds are available for extra guests if needed  •Coffee

neighborhood_overview: Peaceful quiet neighborhood -    We are located central to everything, 5 – 20 minutes by car to all activities: downtown, close to freeways 163, 8 and 5. Our location is 163 and Genesee - near Sharp Hospital (just over a mile),  Rady Children's Hospital (just over a mile), close to Mesa College, Fashion Valley Mall and Mission Valley Mall (one exit away), 5 miles to the beach (we bike there occasionally), USD (2.5 miles)  and other colleges, and to the San Diego airport and Montgomery Field.
notes: #NAME?
transit: Parking is easy here on the street and spots seem to always be available. Buses are about a mile away, which is about a 15 minute walk.  It will take 30 minutes to an hour to go places by bus.  Uber or Lyft are always good bets. Download the apps and start riding!
access: You will have access to the Twin Corner Bedroom/Shared Bathroom and shared common areas of home only w/ the option to add up to 3 additional bedrooms in the main house OR the option to add on the whole house which totals 5 Bedrooms/4 Baths and 2 kitchens w/ Pool and Jacuzzi. **Add on's are available at extra cost and if available.
interaction: We will interact as much as you like or leave you to your privacy.
house_rules: **Please no children under the age of 8 using instant book.  You must clear children with the owner. **The pool does have a fence separately to enclose it.  **No inside smoking, and no disposal of cigarettes in the landscaping or in trash cans inside the house.  Smoking is allowed at the bottom of the steps along the street on the side of the house with the double doors.  Dispose of your butts in a baggie.   **This home is meant to be a respite from the outside world.  We rent other rooms to guests.  This means no after hours partying or noise after 10pm in consideration for other guests.  Please no loud talking, no loud talking on the phone, loud conversation in the living room or kitchen, or showering after 10 pm if there are other guests present.  No partying in the pool after 10 pm - in regard for the neighbors.  Thanks for understanding. **Please no eating on the beds or cosmetics on the beds.  If you have sunscreen on, just roll back the comforters.  Thanks!
host_about: My husband Neil and I are hard workers , fun, appreciate humor (Neil keeps me laughing), can dance (me, Neil has two left feet), loves Italy, likes travel and exotic places, likes animals, loves art, electronically challenged. loves the coast, is a risk taker, leader and finally.....getting old...yuk!  I am now retired.  Neil has his own business that keeps him very busy.  We have hosted guests now for 6 years and are having a great time getting to know people and becoming friends.  This could become one of the funnest things we've done.  Our motto here would be to make our guests as comfortable as possible and help them to enjoy San Diego.  Look forward to welcoming you to our home!
column97: No stairs or steps to enter}"

house_rules: House Rules 1. All bookings require a security deposit of $300 or more. You will not be charged for this in advance. 2. Guests can cancel within 24 hours of booking and receive a full refund, or cancel anytime up to seven days before the start of your trip and receive a 50% refund. Trips cancelled fewer than seven days in advance are not eligible for refunds. If you cancel within 24 hours of booking, please reach out to our team, as this refund has to be processed manually.   3. Check-in time is any time after 4 pm. Check-out time is any time before 11 am. You're welcome to request an early check in or late checkout, but this is not guaranteed and we can only confirm 24 hours in advance. 4. We do not allow smoking of any kind, including but not limited to nicotine, tobacco derived products and/or cannabis derived substances; breaking this rule will incur a $300 fine. 5. Most of our locations do not allow pets. 6. Generally, parties or excessive noise are not allowed in our locations. I
host_about: Sonder is reimagining the way people travel. Now in 20+ cities, we’ve been featured in The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal, and named 2019’s most innovative hospitality brand by Fast Company. We’ve taken the best parts of home and hotel and combined them into an entirely new experience. All of our spaces are uniquely designed, have 24/7 guest support, and contain all the essentials you need for an impeccable stay. No matter what you’re looking for, there’s a Sonder for you.

name: Apartment *Large Jet Tub, Living Rm,  Canyon Patio
summary: Large 600 sq ft.  We are in the heart of the best place in San Diego!  Next to all major downtown areas.  We are surrounded by our famous Balboa Park.  North is Hillcrest with all it's great restaurants, North Park, University Heights.  Lot's of restaurants in the area.  Coffee shops, Mexican, Thai, Italian food, gelato, brewery's and more.    Easy self-check-in.
space: This place is quiet for you to enjoy, yet minutes from the bustle of urban living. Easy 20 minute walk or uber to Little Italy, Downtown, Balboa Park.  Stay urban in the city without the noise!  Huge King Bed, huge jet tub in the bathroom.  Nespresso machine.  Small kitchenette with microwave, hotplate, bullet blender, refrigerator (not a full kitchen).  Have coffee on the beautiful deck in the morning facing the sunrise. We have left for your use: beach towels, beach chairs and mats, boogie and surboards.   There is a refrigerator (medium), microwave, hot water heater (for tea), and of course, Nespresso coffee/espresso maker. Enjoy the beach! I am a San Diego native and happy to share info about any parts of the city you would like to visit, great restaurants, amazing beaches, the best sunset spots, locals favorite fish tacos place and more!

notes: As a traveller, one hard thing about airbnb can be the check in process.  I have made it super easy for you by leaving a key in a lockbox for you and having flexible and even very late check-in hours. Also, my place is very easy to find, and there is parking in front of the house!   You will have no worries when you book our place :)
transit: 1.  Parking right in front of my house on the street.  There are always spots. 2.  Walk an easy one mile to Little Italy, downtown, Balboa Park, the harbor (waterfront). 3.  Uber/Lyft to downtown or Balboa Park is $5 to $7.  To airport is $8. 4.  Lot's of new undocked bikes in San Diego.  (Hidden by Airbnb) it and download apps.  Since March (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) , I see lots of bikes left on the neighborhood streets.  Once you walk a little closer to downtown, you will see them all over the place. 5. Trolley - (Hidden by Airbnb) the route.  Take to the Tijuana border, then walk across to explore the food scene that has exploded down there. 6.  Driving.  We love our cars here.  If you rent a car, that will get you a lot of places quickly.
access: There is only one unit downstairs. The main house is upstairs.  The backyard is a common area, but the house has it's own  deck, and your deck is off your living room.
interaction: Guest interaction changes depending if I am in town and living upstairs. I travel quite a bit.  I'd love to meet you if I am in town.
house_rules: - It is a self check in, I give you the key code.  For your convenience.  No waiting for a host to meet you!    - Parking is on the street & in front of my house.  There is plenty of  parking. - No guests allowed on premises.  It’s a nice place, rented out for the registered guests enjoyment only. - No animals — at all — allowed.  This is not a hotel or public space covered by laws that allow animals.  - Quiet time after 10pm.   - No loud music outside or inside. - No smoking or fire or matches inside or out.  You may use the lighter for the candles inside only. - No use of the Hot Tub.  It’s not guest ready.  No use of the BBQ as So Cal is fire prone. - No food deliveries or any deliveries to the house. - Late check out or early check in by advance request and approval.   - Communication is #1.  Ask me if you need anything or have any problem.  Between 7am and 9p daily.  Urgent items are 24 hours.
host_about: I am a business owner from San Diego. I travel around the world solo quite a bit.  I also host in my hometown. I love to ride bikes, often with my dog, cook Italian food, drink good wine and find new adventures.

name: Beach room with private entrance!

notes: I would recommend checking out the following places around our property: •	Morning – Walk to Copa Vida coffee shop (905 J ST)  and grab a drink, then walk next door to the Padre Stadium.  They open up the ballpark for the public to enjoy when there is not an event or ballgame.   •	Morning – Walk to The Mission (1250 Jst) for breakfast. Its around the corner and serves breakfast and lunch. If you're feeling a bit more venturous, head over to Richard Walkers (closer to Gaslamp area). It's about a 10-15 minute walk, but well worth it. Best breakfast joint in San Diego! •	Afternoon – Rent bikes or take an Uber and head over to Balboa Park.  They have really cool gardens and architecture to check out, along with talented street performers, and world renown museums and attractions. San Diego Zoo is a must! Recognized as The Best zoo in the world.  •	Afternoon- Grab a rental bike (using the shared bike app) and head to Seaport village, its right on the water and has some good restaurants and
transit: Parking: Directly in-front of the building is 2hr parking from 8am – 6pm, you may leave your car overnight (after 5pm), just make sure you move it by 10am or you could get ticketed. Directly across the street from our building is all day parking. J and K streets, which are just north and south of our building (20 sec walk), also has all day parking on both sides of the street. MAKE SURE TO CHECK THE SIGNS FOR STREET SWEEPING PARKING RESTRICTIONS!!
access: I highly recommend utilizing Uber, rental bikes and scooters and walking while staying at our apartment.  Having a car in the city is more of a hassle in my opinion :)

name: Cortez Hill, Downtown Studio 5 blocks to Gaslamp
summary: Come stay at a nice studio in the heart of downtown. We are just a few blocks from the Gaslamp Quarter and walking distance to Little Italy, Petco Park, Balboa Park, and the Convvention Center. There is a nice coffee shop and Italian restaurant right across the street. Be sure to try the Donut Bar and The Taco Stand on the next street over. Some of the best tacos in San Diego!
space: The studio has one full size bed and one full size sofa bed. The studio is not extremely big. It sleeps 2 comfortably but can sleep 4 if you don’t need a lot of space. It has a movie projector that shows bright and clear even in the daytime. It has AC, refrigerator, microwave, oven, coffee maker, strong WIFI, cable TV, and a walk in closet. It is an older building so we ask that you be courteous to the neighbors after 10pm.  I also have a tent and cooler that you can use so you can enjoy a nice day at the beach! Street parking is free 6pm-8am and free all day sundays. There is also a pay parking lot next door or you can just Uber or Lyft everywhere which would probably be easier. You can usually get a ride in less than 5 minutes.

name: WindanSea - The Bed & Breakfast Inn at La Jolla
summary: QUEEN HORIZON OCEAN VIEW:  1 Queen Tempur-pedic bed. 2nd Floor. Accessible via stairs only. No elevator. One of 3 guest rooms with peak of ocean and sunsets. Light and airy, with hardwood floors, plenty of operable windows to catch sea breezes,  plantation style ceiling fan, decorative electric fireplace, and 32 Flat screen TV-DVD and DVD library. Steps from Inn's 2nd floor public library and sun deck for relaxing and sunning. Private European style bath ( small but efficient ) Shower only. No tub.  Adult Only Room - No exceptions! Not appropriate or able to accommodate children under 15 yrs of age. Maximum two adults per room. No Pet Room - No exceptions!"
space: We are a 15 room boutique BnB located in the heart of La Jolla Village in San Diego County.  Each guest room is appointed with different amenities and in their own style and design.  Listed as Historical Site 179  on the San Diego Registry, our Inn has a rich historical past that allows guests to explore and become lost in its stories. It was originally built as a residence for George Kautz family in 1913. The original Gardens were designed by famed horticulturist Kate Sessions, also a well known San Diego figure, who was responsible for Balboa Park and the Scripps Family Gardens. Both these individuals are honored as names of our guest rooms. It also served as the home to the March King
description: John Philip Sousa's family in the 1920s. It is one of the premier romantic inns in San Diego. Celebrating over 100 years of Architectural History, the bed and breakfast Inn is considered one of the finest examples of Irving Gill’s 1913 Cubist Style" Architecture."

name: South Park Comfy Cottage
space: There are not a lot of luxuries here, very basic but it's clean and no shared walls. It's a small house, so it feels very homelike. This is my son's apartment / granny flat, but we own the property, I live in the main house. Quirky shops and restaurants within walking distance.  Public transportation very accessible, a block away heading towards downtown & North Park.  Free street parking.  I don't have a dedicated laundry room, but if you're here for a week, ask me, and I'll allow access to my laundry room in the main house.  There are 2 laundry mats walking distance as well.

Public transportation very accessible, a block away heading towards downtown & North Park.  Free street parking.  I don't have a dedicated laundry room, but if you're here for a week, ask me, and I'll allow access to my laundry room in the main house.  There are 2 laundry mats walking distance as well. Outside space is shared with main house, private walkway into the space, no need to interact with owner to come in and out. We show our guests around upon arrival, but then give them complete privacy. We are just next door so we're available if they need anything. name: Private Newly Renovated North Park Studio
summary: The best of North Park & South Park! Centrally located between both neighborhoods, this newly renovated private studio offers easy access to hip restaurants, cool independent shops, boutique cafe’s, bars and fun pubs.
space: Super clean, updated, and central to everything – our newly renovated studio provides quick access to restaurants, breweries, shops, and area attractions. Only minutes away from Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, Downtown Convention Center, Petco Park, Little Italy, Old Town, and Hillcrest. San Diego beaches, Coronado and the airport are all nearby (see list below). An all new bathroom features a marble-top sink, large mirrors, plush towels, hair dryer, iron/board and bath essentials (individual hand soap, bath gel, shampoo and conditioner). The kitchenette includes a mini refrigerator, microwave oven, and Kuerig coffee machine – complimentary bottled water, coffee, tea, and hot chocolate are provided. neighborhood_overview: Historic Burlingame is a quiet, safe, palm tree-lined neighborhood of North Park within walking distance to hip restaurants, cool independent shops, cafe’s, bars and fun pubs. Burlingame Historic District, a 10-block pocket uniquely located between North Park and South Park, offers easy access to both neighborhoods and is rich in early-century Craftsman and Spanish Revival bungalows.
notes: The studio features an updated kitchenette with mini refrigerator, microwave, and Kuerig coffee machine. Everything necessary to enjoy a snack or to reheat leftovers from one of the many nearby restaurants.
transit: The neighborhood is walkable - everything you need is within a few blocks. Uber and Lyft are prominent in the area and public transportation is also accessible. The bus stop is two blocks away with routes to Downtown, beaches, Balboa Park, Little Italy and Seaport Village.
access: The guesthouse has its own private gate on the side of the main house. You’ll be provided with a 4-digit code prior to check-in to access the keypad door lock on the guesthouse.
interaction: I make a conscious effort to give guests all the space and privacy they need, yet I’m right there at the front house if they need anything at any hour. I’m also available through text, phone and the Airbnb site. Interaction depends on guests needs, including complete privacy if that's what they desire. I'm usually available for a quick tour upon arrival and there’s a keypad door lock for easy check-in when I’m not.
house_rules: - Check-in is anytime after 3PM - Check out by 12PM (noon) - No loud music/noise after 10PM - No visitors (registered guests only)

host_about:
We are a conscious household & invite meditation or yoga by the pool or in our San Diego home.  
Although we are not vegetarian, we would be happy to prepare a vegetarian, vegan or gluten free breakfast for you.
I love to entertain, &  love being able to offer our homes to others.  I enjoy meeting people ~ my goal, is to create a peaceful, refreshing space for you.
In San Diego Point Loma, where we live, I will enjoy getting to know you & at the same time offer you plenty of privacy to enjoy the spectacular ocean views & sunsets & to relax in the back yard pool.  
At the magical Wildomar property, you will be on your own in with a private, spacious backyard, bar-b-que & fire pit ~ exploring the Santa Rosa Plateau & wine tasting in Temecula wine country, & maybe a day at Glen Ivy Spa.
Which ever home you choose, I feel certain you will want to return!

notes: No smoking - means no smoking of ANY kind ANY where on the premises. This includes e-cigs, cigars, vaporizers, hookahs etc. You will forfeit the deposit and be asked to leave the premises. transit: Uber & Lyft operate well here. We have electric bikes and scooter operating here too! Local buses also go down town (route 11), over to PB (route 30) or beyond. Very easy access to freeways  I-5  And just 10 min drive from the airport, 15 min to Coronado and 15 min to La Jolla. This area has a great city walk score of 94, so you might not even need a vehicle while here! The local Mass Transit System (MTS) includes buses, trolley and trains. The fares are generally $2.25 - $2.50 for bus & trolley for one way fare, but a day pass is only $5 using a Compass Card for frequent usage but there is a $2 fee for the card, that can then be topped up when needed. Cards can only be bought at certain locations; the nearest is Albertsons downtown (655 14th Street, 1.3miles) or Vons in Hillcrest (515 W. Washington Street, 1.5miles). name: La Jolla Windnsea Beach Cottage
summary: Our cozy beach cottage is located in a friendly neighborhood just a few blocks from Windnsea Beach and restaurants. One bedroom, newly remodeled, complete with laundry access and beach amenities make this a true gem to get away and relax.
space: This bright and cozy cottage has a very open feeling with the kitchen, dining area, and living room being all contained in one main room. Additionally, the main living area has a sliding door with access to your own private back patio. The cottage is recently remodeled and has all new furniture, fixtures, and bedding.  The bedroom has a comfortable queen bed with a connected bathroom. Built-in cabinets and a large closet allow for ample storage. The bathroom has a new shower enclosure (no bathtub) with plenty of towels, shampoo, hairdryer, and other toiletry items. For additional sleeping space, the couch in the living room pulls out into another queen bed complete with bedding. The kitchen has all new major appliances including a stove/oven, refrigerator, microwave, and quartz counter-tops, along with a toaster and coffee pot. In addition, there are plenty of pots/pans, cooking utensils, glassware and silverware. We also supply paper towels and ziplocs/tupperware for your convenience.

neighborhood_overview: The Windnsea community is a very casual and friendly environment. You'll see folks walking around enjoying the scenery and also heading down to the beach or to one of our local restaurants. There is a walking path accessible from the top of our street with beautiful ocean views. The village of La Jolla is a comfortable 20 minute walk where you can visit famous La Jolla beaches such as La Jolla Cove and The Children's Pool (now a protected sea lion area).
notes: The cottage is suitable for 4 people max being a mix of adults and children.
transit: Even though much of La Jolla is withing walking distance, there is a bus stop conveniently located about 2 blocks away where you can pick up the 30 bus that takes you straight into Downtown San Diego. The airport is about a 25-30 minute drive from La Jolla.
access: The unit is a separate structure behind the main house and is attached to our garage. Parking is only available on the street. There is a separate, gated entrance for access to the cottage in addition to a private back patio, complete with a gas bbq.
interaction: We will be available to you as needed; at the same time, we respect your privacy. We work days (sometimes from home), and are around the house most evenings and weekends. We would be happy to recommend restaurants, bars, sights to see and things to do in San Diego.
house_rules: No smoking inside the cottage.
host_about: We love to enjoy our city and explore all it has to offer. Spending time with friends and family, sipping on amazing craft beer, cooking up a storm, and working on our array of Pinball machines is how we spend our time!

description: High ceilings and open spaces give this loft-like home a relaxing and peaceful vibe reminiscent of San Diego itself. It features a lofted bedroom and large open floor space with a spacious kitchen and living room area for a stay that feels both sleek and stylish.  Bars, Cafes, Gaslamp, Petco Park, Bike Rentals, USS Midway. Walk to everything. Walking distance to the Bay. Bike Rentals are just across the street. Sign up for Car2Go before your trip and you can have a car anywhere in the neighborhood. name: Quiet and Private Studio/Loft
summary: Hi. We are a quiet and friendly family. Our Airbnb is a non smoking and quiet Airbnb. You have your own private entrance in the back of the house with your own balcony.  The 2nd floor is your own functional kitchenette and full bath.  Spiral staircase takes you to the 3rd floor with your own private living room and bedroom.  We want to make sure you have a great time.  So let us know if you need anything. We are located in Hillcrest, which is about a 5 minute drive to downtown San Diego.
space: We are a very quiet family and we offer a very quiet and cozy Airbnb.   The unit is attached to the back part of the house but is a separate living space.  (This is your own apartment with all of the amenities)  You have your own access to the unit with your own key.  The petite kitchenette is fully functionable with a microwave, refrigerator, toaster, coffee maker and stove/oven. You also have your own private full bathroom.  The spiral staircase takes you from the kitchenette area up to the bedroom with a queen bed and a sitting area with a TV and a futon.  The kitchen includes, plates, bowls, cups, glasses, silverware and coffee cups.  This is a secluded, quiet and cute space.  (You do share one wall with the rest of the house in the kitchenette area). Also, the ceiling in the bedroom and tv area has an A-Frame vaulted ceiling.  So if you are a tall person, this may be an issue for you.  The unit has a portable AC/Heating unit in the bedroom/living room area.

neighborhood_overview: We are located in heart Hillcrest and you can walk to all the shops, cafes and restaurants from our Airbnb. We are  a 5 minute drive to Little Italy, Gas Lamp District, Downtown, the Zoo, Old Town San Diego, Beaches and Balboa Park. I can't stress how many guests have stayed with us and said how central we are to everything.  Your average Uber/Lyft charge is about $5.  Our street is a historic area and is very quiet.  You are minutes to everything and so many great places to check out.
notes: We are a very quiet family and we offer a vey quiet Airbnb.   1. I want to be very transparent, it can be a little tight going up and down the spiral staircase especially if you are tall. But as long as you are a little flexible, you should be just fine.  2. The studio/loft was completely remodeled in November 2015.  However, the house is over 100 years old and let's just say it has a few old bones.   3. The ceiling in the bedroom and tv area is an A-Frame ceiling. So if you are a tall person, this may be an issue for you. 4.  The unit has a portable AC/Heating unit located in the bedroom/living room area. We live in a great neighborhood with quiet neighbors.  Please be respectful of them and say hello.   You do share a wall with the other unit.  Just like a hotel. This is a no smoking, no drugs Airbnb. No smoking allowed on entire property.   If you do smoke, this Airbnb is not for you. If you want to party, this Airbnb is not for you. No pets allowed No smoking  on entire property  N
transit: We have FREE street parking available in our neighborhood, which is actually a BIG bonus.  All city buses are just two blocks away.  Because we are so central, you're best off taking Uber/Lyft so you don't have to deal with paying for parking in other parts of the city.  Average parking fees are about $20 throughout San Diego.  You can also rent bikes 5 blocks away at Decobikes and ride over to the Zoo or Balboa Park.
access: You have your own private side entrance as well as your own balcony on the second floor.  You also have access to the back yard deck for a cup of coffee, beer or glass of wine.  Again, you have separate entrance from the rest of the house with your own set of keys, your own bathroom and your own kitchen.  You also have FREE street parking.  No permits are required and we don't have any street meters either.
interaction: I am always open to help our guests with just about any request.  I have lived in San Diego for many years and know all the great spots.  What ever you need, just tell me and I will be more than happy to assist.  If you are not happy with something in the unit, please address this with me and I am sure we will resolve the concern.
house_rules: Hello,  Please treat this like your own house.   Sorry, no pets, no parties, no extra guests unless approved. No smoking on the entire property.   Please try to leave the unit the way you found it when you checked in. For the day of check out, please place all debris and trash outside into the bins. Please also try to wash the dishes and put away.  Please strip the bed of linens and leave on the bed.   Please respect the noise level and respect the neighbors and neighborhood.  Lastly, please know that Airbnb homes are very different from hotels. Thank you!

interaction: My wife and I live on the same property as this guest house so we can be available if you need anything but otherwise you wont see us, as we want you to feel comfortable and enjoy your stay.

summary: Private guest room with a comfortable queen bed (hotel-quality sheets) and shared bathroom. Dog-friendly, and two guests max. Large yard, kitchen and close city & beach access. Vacation-vibe with friendly host experience.
space: Quiet, relaxing home centrally located. Large yard with canyon and sunset views. Centrally located and dog-friendly.
description: Private guest room with a comfortable queen bed (hotel-quality sheets) and shared bathroom. Dog-friendly, and two guests max. Large yard, kitchen and close city & beach access. Vacation-vibe with friendly host experience. Quiet, relaxing home centrally located. Large yard with canyon and sunset views. Centrally located and dog-friendly. Make yourself at home. Only space off limits is my bedroom but between the living area, sunroom, backyard and patio there are many cozy nooks to relax and unwind. I'm happy to help with any needs. Please just ask! Quiet and safe neighborhood. Very close to San Diego State University, Kensington, Normal Heights, North Park, Downtown, Little Italy, Coronado, Mission Valley and the Beach Areas. Street parking is available and very easy to find usually right in front of the house. notes: There are two friendly dogs in the house who get along with everyone including other dogs.

house_rules: Common courtesy and respect are expected. Smoking is allowed on the patio/outside only, no overnight guest, come and go as you please but after 10pm please do so respectfully.
host_about:
I'm a creative Californian gal who grew up in wine country and can appreciate a nice bottle of wine. I've also lived in London, Los Angeles, St. Tropez, France and have travelled extensively.  For the last 5 years, I've been living in San Diego and recently bought my dream home. Most days you can find me working around my house, walking my two dogs at Fiesta Island or enjoying taco Tuesday with a salty margarita. 

I work from home so I'm available for your arrival anytime, and I'd be happy to offer any assistance to make your time at my home and in San Diego great. 

I am looking forward to meeting you soon!

I often am traveling for work to different places for long period of times. My roommate often operates my air bnb for me since I often don't have service or with time changes etc. She is very helpful for when you check in and while you are staying in our home. 
We live in a 2 story house; occupying the top floor, there are 3 gentlemen that live below us however they do not have access to our house nor us to theirs. Both roommates work 8-6 mon- friday, Tiffany usually uses the restroom to get ready between 7:30-8am.

name: OB Pier #3 - Dog-friendly beachfront home surrounded by restaurants
summary: Couples in search of beach walks and small families looking for a sunny vacation they'll never forget should both consider this lovely condo. Located just a few steps from the beach, this dog-friendly condo has all the comforts you need, along with easy access to nearby attractions. This Ocean Beach condo for a couple is right across the street from the warm sands and gentle waves of the Pacific Ocean. Small-town eateries like Hoodad's and BBQ House surround you, with a nearby public park for walking off your filling meal or giving the dog a little exercise. At the same time, far more shops, restaurants, and activities are just a seven-mile drive away in downtown San Diego! This listing is for a one-bedroom, one-bathroom condo on the second floor that is ideal for couples and small groups, though it can be rented in conjunction with two other similar homes on the same property for added versatility. The building has a two-bedroom, one-bathroom rental for six to nine guests on the botto

name: DOWNTOWN GARDEN VIEW STUDIO
summary: Large wrap-around studio, linen sheets,  Nespresso coffee maker, Alexa, and a Glass-enclosed eat-in kitchen. A breakfast nook with small table for two overlooking the garden. Bottled water available in the lobby. Just blocks from Balboa Park. Private space in a garden setting, a homey feel, but in the center of the city. Located atop little known Cortez Hill, a strictly residential cul-de-sac neighborhood wedged between downtown and Balboa Park.
space: The kitchen is all windows, hardwood floors in the bedroom and a plush carpet with a king size bed, couch and additional lounger. A 60 inch smart television with Netflix and local programming,  an original decorative fireplace adds to the ambiance.   Linen sheets and a Tempurpedic mattress.  FAST High speed wireless internet and Alexa included.

house_rules: House Rules 1. All bookings require a security deposit of $300 or more. You will not be charged for this in advance. 2. Guests can cancel within 24 hours of booking and receive a full refund, or cancel anytime up to seven days before the start of your trip and receive a 50% refund. If you cancel within 24 hours of booking, please reach out to our team, as this refund has to be processed manually.   3. Check-in time is any time after 4 pm. Check-out time is any time before 11 am. You're welcome to request an early check in or late checkout, but this is not guaranteed and we can only confirm 24 hours in advance. 4. We do not allow smoking of any kind, including but not limited to nicotine, tobacco derived products and/or cannabis derived substances; breaking this rule will incur a $300 fine. 5. Most of our locations do not allow pets. 6. Generally, parties or excessive noise are not allowed in our locations. I

name: Canyon apartment hideaway
summary: This recently renovated apartment looks out to a beautifully landscaped backyard and the canyon beyond. Located to the east of the city, it provides ready access to all of San Diego without the hassle of crowded areas and parking shortages.
space: Set on a quiet and lush canyon, who would ever guess that you were in a large urban city! Although it's southern California and a car is very handy, this apartment is close to good public transit, either by trolley from San Diego State University, or a 5 minute walk to a rapid bus service to the downtown. It is close to all major freeways for anyone coming to San Diego for the zoo, beaches,the desert, and Mexico. This self-contained apartment - with a bedroom, bathroom, living room and kitchen - occupies the ground floor of 4770 and has a separate and private entrance from 55th St. It looks out on a large and terraced backyard with a B-B-Q in which the travel weary can relax and chill". It is the ideal deal for one traveler or a couple."

host_acceptance_rate: A beautiful neighborhood that hosts great local coffee shops, cafes, and bars - you'll be able to get out and explore a neighborhood of San Diego most folks don't get to! Minutes from the airport (without any noise, since we're not in the flight path!). For the folks who love city life, but love parking and quiet too!
host_neighbourhood: Parking is a non-issue; You'll be able to park within 1-2 blocks of the apartment no matter the time of day.  We also live a few blocks off two different bus lines that make getting into Gaslamp, Old Town, and Hillcrest really quick and easy!
host_listings_count: We're set right next to a small canyon park, which gives you the perfect excuse to walk for coffee at our favorite java spot, come back and cuddle on the park bench and sip cappuccinos, enjoying the canyon breeze!
host_total_listings_count: We've got lots of recommendations for how to make the most of your San Diego visit, so if you need help building an itinerary, please let us know - especially if you're looking for cocktail/brewery/restaurant recommendations.  We've got only the best designed interior spaces that offer up the best goodies in mind!

zipcode: well hello!  we love exploring worlds that are not our own, and while our wanderlust certainly hasn't decreased (as we still jump at the opportunity to immerse ourselves in local culture any chance we get), we are learning to be content with our own space and lives. Recognizing the value of inviting others in, and not always getting ourselves out; we're excited to share our space and have good people join us where we're at.

name: New North Park Stylish Studio
summary: This stylish studio cottage is centered in the historic, diverse and eclectic uptown neighborhood of North Park. It is set off the street and boasts a quiet private sitting area for morning coffee or evening drinks. You have a full kitchen, bathroom, living area as well as a washer/dryer. You will be near everything you may want or need to do: Airport, Balboa Park, SD Zoo, Downtown/Gas Lamp Quarter, Petco Park, dozens of restaurants and brew pubs,  and near all Beaches & Coronado Island.
space: This quaint cottage offers a full kitchen with full size fridge, range/oven, toaster, microwave, keurig coffee maker & tea pot.  Some coffee, hot chocolate, tea, a few bottles of water and a few snacks for your arrival. Pots, pans and dishes so you can stay in and cook or warm up leftovers. Laundry soap, hand soap, lotion, plenty of towels, shampoo & a hair dryer.  Eat at the kitchen bar counter top. Laminate wood flooring throughout with area rugs within the home.  Guests can also use the shared yard that offers a Palapa with an outdoor kitchen/ BBQ, TV, and fire pit . An additional fire pit to sit around is also available.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is made up of older homes from the early 1900's all so unique and different. We are within a few short blocks of some spectacular restaurants, brew pubs, cafe's and coffee houses and boutique shops.  North Park has been named in Forbes Magazine as one of the Hippest Neighborhoods.  Entertainment at the Historic North Park Observatory Theater offers and impressive year-round line up. Ray Street offers many art galleries along with the world famous 30th Street and nearby side streets are home to some of the city's best craft beer breweries, tasting rooms and beer friendly restaurants. Many are within an easy walk from where your are staying. We hope you love our neighborhood as much as we do.
notes: Check in is at 3 pm and check out at 11 am. We do bend if your flight is a bit later or earlier, just ask.
transit: Located within a 2 block radius of the Metro Transportation System -buses.
access: There are two options to enter the property, front or private back gate.  Choose the one that fits your needs best.  You'll have your own semi-private patio area.

host_about:
I am a local Realtor and Property Manager for 21 plus years, married, with 2 boys.  I really enjoy meeting new people.   I decided to  step into the field as an Airbnb host as of February 2018. Larry and I built a cute cottage for our guests to stay in and after much persuasion we decided to open it as an Airbnb vacation rental too.  It's  a new cottage studio behind our home  great for 2 people.  I also manage a beautiful townhouse in La Jolla  that is walking distance to Windansea Beach that became available in April 2018.  The views and beach sunsets are incredible.  A great place for a group or or family as it has 3 beds and 2.5 baths.  

This year we have traveled to Savannah, GA, Turks and Caicos and Colorado Springs booking our stays through Airbnb. It has been really fun to see new places and being someone's guest. 

I love traveling with my family and friends,  meeting new people and creating friendships.  Book your stay at one of the two places I have to offer, I'd love to be your host.

name: Lovely Studio in Landmark Victorian
summary: This lovely studio space is located within a classic Victorian house that is a San Diego historical landmark built in 1886. The exterior is preserved maintaining its traditional charm, and interior features a modern contemporary-chic living quarter, a comfortable, custom-made queen bed, al small private bathroom with a tub/shower and newly furnished decor and furniture throughout the space. This studio is perfect for a single or couple looking for a quiet, quaint getaway.
space: Conveniently located five minutes away from downtown, South Park, North Park, and immediately accessible to San Diego's major freeways, making the studio centralized to everything that America's Finest City has to offer! The studio comes complete with a custom designed queen bed, a refurbished small bathroom with clean towels and linens and a hot shower (tub/shower unit). The studio also has a closet space for your personal belongings and clothing, pull-out drawers, and a lovely living space with a comfortable, new couch to relax and unwind.

Nearby are plenty of great restaurants, markets, and everything needed for your convenience.
notes: Discounts are automatically calculated with bookings one week or longer, as well as bookings of one month or longer. We are family owned and operate and we do our best to accommodate our guests and make their stay. Check out our other listing of Quaint Guest Cottage Studio. https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/23904952?s=51 Check out our listing of Carriage House Studio https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/30201817?s=51 Check out our listing of Central Midcentury Studio with view. https://abnb.me/wVSsLSVLAV Due to the popularity of the property, early check-in is at times not possible - it is best to inquiry and pre-arrange early check in at the time when you book your stay. Guests can message us to arrange to drop off luggage prior to check-in time.
transit: The space comes with free parking on the premises for one vehicle, and is close to a bus stop that makes the rest of the city easily accessible. Within our neighborhood dockless bikes and/or scooters for rent can be found. Major attractions are just a short Uber/Lyft ride that is typically less than $10. Balboa Park, Museum, and Zoo: $5-$8 ride with Uber/Lyft Downtown, Petco Baseball Park: $5-$10 ride with Uber/Lyft Airport is about 5 miles away.
access: Guests will have access to the entire space all to themselves; the kitchen, living room, closets and cupboards, the bathroom and tub/shower, the master bedroom. This space is a private unit and is located in an original large Victorian Home. Please be respectful of others and no loud noise/music after 10pm. Return keys in lockbox when you check out. We are currently redecorating the main lobby and hall with detailed wood work. This will not impact entry or accessibility to the unit.
interaction: I speak English and Spanish! As one of the property owners, I am frequently around the area and am no further than fifteen minutes away in the event of an emergency. We are family owned and operated. As native San Diegans we are always up to answer questions about local sites, attractions, etc.
