name: A Jewel in the City
summary: Located just a brief trolley ride from downtown and the convention center, this cozy, detached bungalow features a mix of art inspired details, modern furniture, deep soaking bathtub and the comfiest bed you'll ever sleep in.
space: Situated just east of San Diego's East Village, you'll feel right at home in this comfy modern getaway. Though the reclaimed wooden walls, hardwood floors and cast iron stove give this cozy bungalow a cabin like feel, you'll hardly be roughing it with the modern touches and luxuriously comfortable Stearns and Foster mattress ensconced in high thread count sheets. The well appointed kitchen comes complete with everything you'll need for either preparing meals or just to feel like a chef while you're reheating your delicious leftovers. If you don't feel like dining indoors, step outside, fire up the gas barbecue and dine on our wood deck or tumbled stone patio. You're welcome to dine with your friends under the lights outside at our table that seats six. Curl up at night in the Lignet Roset inspired couches and enjoy a fire in the antique cast iron stove. Downloading movies to your laptop or tablet is a snap with our ultra high speed wireless connection (50 mb down, 12 mb up). Want to re

neighborhood_overview: Situated between the trendy East Village and hipster favored Golden Heights, Logan Heights is a culturally diverse, gentrifying neighborhood. Within a few doors you'll find fantastic street tacos, authentic Central American food and southern style fried chicken. And yes, you'll find a hip coffee shop down the street for your morning fix.  Within a short distance, you'll find galleries like Bread and Salt, La Bodega, Low Gallery, and Glashaus. Mixed among them are the award winning Border X and Iron Fist brew pubs and Salud!, a popular restaurant serving an updated approach to Mexican street food. The home is located in an ethnically and economically mixed urban area. The Local Heights area has gone through many changes over the years and is now in the midst of revitalization. It is the hottest selling location in the city for residential real estate because it is so affordable, centrally located and artistically vibrant. If however you are uncomfortable with the sight of people of colo
transit: The house is located one trolley stop east of San Diego's convention center. The trolley stop is situated just down the street within easy walking distance. If you're headed to any of the many San Diego attractions, you'll find the location very central and easy to get in and out of. The bus to downtown maybe found at the immediate street corner.  Of course, this is San Diego so having a car is the most convenient option for getting around. If you don't have your own car or wish to leave it at home, for about $6 to $8, the popular ride sharing apps like Uber and Lyft will get you to many popular locations like Coronado, Balboa Park, the Gaslamp District and Little Italy.
access: This home combines both indoor and outdoor spaces into one larger living area. Work inside at a desk or relax on our wooden deck under the lights as the day fades into night. As a guest, you'll have full access to both inside and outside spaces.
interaction: Guests will be able to check in on their own using an assigned combination for the front door. I'm available via text and by phone if there's any issues during the stay.
host_about: I'm a visual artist and perennial traveler. You'll find my work in public exhibitions, galleries and even in museums. I hate boring spaces so when I'm not making my art, you're as likely as not to find me creating some woodworking project around the house or making a dead space come to life. I've also written a travel guide to San Diego so if you need any suggestions for places to go and things to do, I'm your man!

interaction: We're in a wonderful location in Pacific Beach. The ocean is only five short blocks away (Mission Bay Park is only 2-3 blocks away) and the street in front of the house has a view of the ocean. There are so many great restaurants, cafes, bars and shops all around here. BetterBuzz Coffee 1/2 block away and is very popular with students and professionals who need workspace and strong Internet. 7-11 convenience store is 1/2 block away and is open 24 hours a day. Sprouts is a great 'natural foods grocery store' and is also only 1/2 block away.
house_rules: There is a key pad to enter the front door. I will provide a code which will work for the duration of your visit. Your room is on second floor but has the third floor patio directly above it so your sleep should not be disturbed by movement above your ceiling. There is a security camera on first floor which monitors the entrance, front patio and living room. Tampering with the device is not permitted. This security measure is for your safety and well-being as well as the security of the property. We respect your privacy. If you are uncomfortable with these measures, kindly seek out another listing. Check-in at 3pm. Check-out at 10am. This is so we have time to tidy room before the next guest. Please inquire if you need some flexibility. You're welcome to store your luggage if you have an early arrival or have a planned departure after checkout, please inquire in advance.
thumbnail_url: Street parking in PB is hit or miss. Plenty of spaces during the day on weekdays, but in the evening and much of the time on weekends nearby parking can be very difficult though not impossible. We do not have off-street parking available for your use. Frankly, most guests find that ride-sharing works best. For those who bring a rental car, parking is rarely that difficult to find if you're patient.  There is a bus stop in front of the 7-11 on Garnet at Fanuel.  There are many stores that rent bicycles in Pacific Beach. PB Bicycle on Mission Blvd at Grand rents beach cruisers (single speed, no gears) with bike basket and bike lock for $15/day which is a great price. Ask for Tony and say Ed n Brandy sent you. Bicycle Discovery on Mission Blvd at Felspar rents bikes by the hour and has better quality bikes including bikes with child seats and tandem bikes. Their rates are a little higher per day, $25/day.  Ask for Michael Anthony and tell him that Ed n Brandy sent you. :-) There is a bus

Guest love staying here to experience both nature as well as the many SD attractions.  We are a foodie's paradise, many restaurants and cafes located within walking distance.
notes: I have been renting my place  for over 23 years to many guests while with another rental company.  My guests through reviews tell me they enjoyed their stay with many repeat guests year to year, establishing  my 5 star rating.

host_location: shared time between Southern and Northern California
host_about:
After telling you a bit about me I thought you may want to read about my condo (below) which I have shared with others for 23 years, enjoying a 5 star rating. It was another rental service company.!

I have been to most US states and lived in 8 of them.  My career has spanned from Nursing, to real estate sales, to corporate management, owning 2 fitness gyms, writing a book and most recently combining all my experiences coaching women and young adults in transition. 
I enjoy walking, talking, sipping wine, beautiful scenery and combine the four often with new and long time friends.

I have a wonderful family which includes a beautiful daughter, terrific son-in-law and two really awesome teenage grandson's, I spend time with them often. Always fun.

My bay side condo has a  a water view of Mission Bay, it's on sail bay so you will see lots of wonderful and colorful activity. You can walk to the  sandy beach just steps away and enjoy all that San Diego has to offer!

Contemporary light and airy end unit with lots of windows and fantastic water view from the living room dining room, and patio. You can watch the sail boats glide by and watch the fireworks at Sea World from your living room.

This well maintained condo has recently been painted and has new laminate flooring in both bedrooms! The IKEA  kitchen is less than 2 years old.

The guest rental bedroom has access from the bedroom  to bathroom which has tub/shower.  The condo has relaxing pale gray flooring throughout. 
Off street covered assigned parking provided.
We are a  quiet small 13 unit complex with mostly owners and/or long term renters.

Some of the many adventures waiting for you other than simply enjoying the beautiful view are;  rollerblading, skating, biking, canoeing,  SUP, Kayaking, and  many other water sports. Rentals are available close by for most activities.

Convenient to Sea World, the San Diego Zoo, Old Towne, Balboa Park, La Jolla, and much more.
You will see that I shared a couple of photo's of the lovely Catamaran Resort Hotel and Spa just down the bay walk.

name: San Diego Escape
summary: Why only stay at an airbnb when you can be a part of a community during your trip? At Living Q, we have carefully selected a diverse group of creative professionals that are coming together to build a community.Potluck dinners, group hikes and other activities are a part of our weekly routine and this is your opportunity to join in on the fun! Whether you are visiting San Diego for business, a family event or the zoo, we will have something going on site with our members that you can partake in!
space: Newly renovated apartment in downtown San Diego and right off the 5 for easy access to all the attractions SD has to offer! Walk 10 mins to catch a Padres game at Petco Park, walk another 5 to wine & dine in one of the many restaurants and bars in the famous Gaslamp District, or take the next exit south to explore beautiful Coronado. Aside from the ideal location, the property offers a soon-to-be BBQ grill, fire pit and brand new wooden deck for soaking in the sun! FREE Street Parking available

name: Your Getaway On the Park in North Park
summary: Your private and secluded home away from home on the park in North Park. Enjoy everything you need for a comfortable and private stay.  A quick walk to all that North Park has to offer with trending restaurants, shopping, breweries, nightlife and outdoor activities. Just a 15 minute walk to the San Diego Zoo and Balboa Park. A quick drive to Downtown San Diego, Little Italy, San Diego Airport and Beaches. Note: As of January 2018, this listing no longer has access to the pool.
space: Our charming private house has a large yard with your very own BBQ, outdoor seating and dining area for your personal enjoyment.  The indoor space is open and airy with high ceilings, privacy and amenities including a rain shower, coffee/tea service, front load washer/dryer and everything you need to cook a nice meal. There is a 55 TV with full HD cable with movie channels and Netflix."
description: Your private and secluded home away from home on the park in North Park. Enjoy everything you need for a comfortable and private stay.  A quick walk to all that North Park has to offer with trending restaurants, shopping, breweries, nightlife and outdoor activities. Just a 15 minute walk to the San Diego Zoo and Balboa Park. A quick drive to Downtown San Diego, Little Italy, San Diego Airport and Beaches. Note: As of January 2018, this listing no longer has access to the pool. Our charming private house has a large yard with your very own BBQ, outdoor seating and dining area for your personal enjoyment.  The indoor space is open and airy with high ceilings, privacy and amenities including a rain shower, coffee/tea service, front load washer/dryer and everything you need to cook a nice meal. There is a 55 TV with full HD cable with movie channels and Netflix. Enjoy access to everything within the house and yard through the coded gate lock. We are available for anything you need locally"
neighborhood_overview: What is not to LOVE about North Park?  It has everything to offer for everybody.  Restaurants, shopping (with many local artisans represented), nightlife, outdoor activities and the list goes on. Situated on the boundaries of downtown San Diego, Hillcrest and Balboa Park.  Central to all that you want to do and see in San Diego.  The house is literally across the street from the portion of Balboa Park called Morley Field, which has a sports complex including: tennis, archery, a pool, a velodrome, frisbee golf, bocce ball courts (we have a bocce ball set at the house for your use), hiking, playgrounds, baseball fields, workout boot camps and yoga
notes: We supply all toiletries, fresh linen and bedding and bath towels. Coffee/tea station with a variety of teas to choose from.
transit: Uber and Lyft are readily available within our neighborhood, our average wait time has never been more than 5 minutes (typically 2). There is a Deco Bike rental station 5 blocks from the house and the MTS bus line runs several routes close the house.
access: Enjoy access to everything within the house and yard through the coded gate lock.
interaction: We are available for anything you need locally if you have questions.  We can meet you at check-in to review items about the house and we will supply a lock box code for keyed entry.
house_rules: - Be respectful of surrounding neighbors. The house is private, you share no common space with anyone but we are in a neighborhood. - Do not disturb our full time tenants in the front/main house. They have no affiliation with our Air BNB listing and should not be contacted for anything. - On occasion, we have co-hosts that assist us with our guests when we are out of town. We will inform you if we are not going to be in San Diego during your stay and exchange their information with you for check-in and anything else you might need while here. - Keep noise levels down to a respectable level after 10pm. Again, we are in a neighborhood and we love our neighbors and want to keep it that way. - Respect our house and our community.  We take great pride in our house and we want you to enjoy it as much as we do.  - If something breaks during your stay, please tell us so that we can arrange to get it fixed/replaced so all future guests (and us) can enjoy the space. - Keep the screen door closed
host_about: We love to travel, enjoy great food, soak up local cultures, hear new music, meet new people and explore. San Diego is home base where we have lived for over 20 years .We take great pride in our quaint house in North Park and know that you will love it as much as we do!

name: Extreme home stay in La Jolla!
space: This furnished room with private bathroom and balcony is located in our spacious 4 bedroom modern treehouse".  The bathroom shower is large and artistically tiled with a rain head shower. The house is very clean and has been recently remodeled with all brand new major appliances. There is no TV here but we have WIFI for our guests
description: providing you have your own laptop or smart phone to use it on. We call this an extreme home because it is. it is a very special unusual work of architecture and has been written about in magazines and newspapers over the years. We are located on a designated California Scenic Drive. Tour buses even stop here so their passengers can take photos! The house is on a hillside with beautiful views of trees and the surrounding neighborhoods.  There are many stairs leading up to the house but the hike up is worth the view! We are 1.5 miles from world famous Windansea beach and 1.2 to the seaside village of La Jolla which offers many restaurants

host_listings_count:
We have a great life for sure and are thankful everyday for this! We love the outdoors and are able to enjoy doing many outdoor activities because of our superior weather here-especially in the summer! These activities include although are not limited to hiking, surfing, swimming, and gardening. 

Our home is like a retreat from the busy world outside. We take pride in it and are constantly striving to improve it. It is a very peaceful quiet environment. Of course we also entertain once in a while and enjoy having friends and family over for a BBQ on nice summer nights.

We really enjoy meeting people from different parts of the world and learning about them and the places they come from. 

We look forward to hosting you on your next vacation or business trip!

space: I get this question alot because one of the reviews mentions a Futon at my place. Just to clarify, the Futon is only in the living room, the bedroom which this listing is for, has a real bed. name: cozy private room in pacific beach
summary: This cozy space is private room with a private bath in a quiet part of PB. You'll enjoy an outside sitting area, a beach cruiser for trips to the beach and beach towels if you need them.
space: Experience beach life from this cozy space. It has it's own private bathroom, TV, internet, small fridge, microwave and coffee maker. We have made some improvements recently and you'll find a nice closet space with plenty of room for hanging clothes. Your bathroom has a beautiful new vanity and flooring. Plenty of storage space for long term guests. From our quiet condo, you can walk to the beach (about a mile) or hit the bustling Pacific Beach nightlife.  It's also just a short walk to the bus stop, see our notes on destinations below.   If you have a car, there is ample street parking right outside the front door.

neighborhood_overview: This room is in a quiet part of PB, near Kate Sessions Park. So you can have fun and some relaxation. The beach is close, but not so close that traffic and noise are a problem. Parking is plentiful. We welcome long term guests, so if you have an internship or job contract for a few months, we've got a nice place for you to stay while you're hard at work. It's quiet and peaceful for a serious grad student.
notes: Only a few blocks away, there are some good restaurants, a grocery store, and pharmacy. 8 blocks or so you can find more restaurants, fast food, bars and all kinds shopping.  We've got a cruiser bike to use too. Check-in at 3pm. Check-out at 11am. This is so we have time to tidy room before the next guest, but there may be some flexibility here (just inquire if necessary). You're welcome to store your luggage if you have an early arrival or have a planned departure after checkout, please inquire in advance.
transit: The #30 bus can get you from downtown to historic Old Town (get the trolley to Mexico or connect to the train line to LA) and north to La Jolla and UCSD. The bus takes some time to get around, but it's only 5 blocks walk. Uber and Lyft are also easy ways to get around San Diego.
access: Guest room with private bath. It's downstairs so you can come and go without going through the entire house. We have a laundry area available (located in garage). There is no charge for laundry, just bring your own detergent. If you'd like to use our personal kitchen or the grill to cook from time to time during your stay, we can arrange that too. Our kitchen space is tiny so we do need to coordinate use so we are not in each other's way.  Most of our guest love the local eateries instead of staying in.
interaction: We'll leave you alone if you like. We can offer info on our  favorite local spots when you want. Jennifer travels for work so she may not always be here. Michelle is usually around if you need something.
house_rules: No smoking. No pets. No drugs. Yes, we know pot is legal here in Cali, but we don't want you smoking it on our property.
host_about: I like to meet new people. I enjoy cooking and have a food based business from home.

It's also within about 20 minutes walking distance to Santa Fe Train Station, San Diego Convention Center, and Coronado Ferry. Plus restaurants galore!

notes: PARKING: There are 45+ spaces that are not metered on the adjacent block and will allow you to leave your car there for extended periods of time if  you're going to spend most of your time walking around town. As long as your not looking for a space during business hours you should always be able to find a space within 2 blocks or less. Otherwise there is a Pay Parking lot across the street. Weekdays it is $12 for 12 hours during the day and $5 for 12 hours after 4pm. Weekends it is $5 for 12 hours anytime of day. BATHROOM: The bathroom will be shared with up to a maximum of 2 additional people.
transit: Walking distance to Santa Fe Train Station, Coronado Ferry, Trolley, and bus lines (1 mile or less). Only 9 blocks to the waterfront. It's a 1 mile walk to the Convention Center and 2 miles from The San Diego International airport. I highly recommend downloading the Uber or Lyft app. These on-demand private driver services work fast and efficiently in the downtown area and can be as cheap as $3 a ride (cheaper than a taxi).

name: Beachy, In-Home Guest Suite. La Jolla, San Diego
summary: Extremely private, quiet, large master suite with super comfy bed, goodies in the fridge, seating area w/ desk and TV. Bathroom has excellent water pressure, plenty of hot water and many extra touches. Our solar powered home heats the spa just outside your room. Preset at 103 degrees, it’s easily adjusted. New patio set includes cozy fire pit where graceful bamboo and fruit trees thrive. Walk or bike to beautiful beaches, restaurants, shops and entertainment. Bikes + beach amenities included.
space: Your room is nestled at the back of the house, very private and very quiet, with its own entrance if you prefer. With several skylights, windows and french doors, the room is bright and airy. On large swells you can hear the waves crashing. The room has a large closet, dresser, Roku TV, side tables, small fridge, ceiling fan, coffee maker and snacks and like a suite, includes a separate sitting area. The large, private, in-room bathroom features a sink/counter area with a basket of useful items you may have forgotten. It also has a large shower/bath with great water pressure. Take a quick rinse before dipping into the jacuzzi just outside your door. Afterward, nestle into your comfy terry robe and kick back in the separate, in-room sitting area. Enjoy a good book from our well-stocked library, or get a bit of work done at the small desk. A 10 minute walk will take you to a breathtaking beach where you can mingle with locals while watching for the green flash at sunset. A 30 second walk

host_about: Easy going and casual, we love traveling and meeting people from other places.
column99: No stairs or steps to enter

name: Perfect Little Italy Condo for 2
summary: Bright and airy 1 bedroom, office, 1 bath, fully furnished condo located a couple blocks from the heart of Little Italy with walking distance to Embarcadero and Downtown San Diego. Luxurious living with on site guard and great views of San Diego. Includes W/D, fitness center, pool, spa and BBQ.
space: This condo beats staying in a pricey hotel. -It features a unique floor plan that boasts floor to ceiling views facing Little Italy from both bedrooms and living room. -The unit is perfectly located on the same floor as the pool/jacuzzi and BBQ area for entertaining.  -Close to the elevators for ease of access.  -Custom made wine glass cabinet and unique art give the condo a contemporary, but cozy atmosphere.  -Condo includes: Washer/dryer Dishwasher  Stove Refrigerator  Microwave  Garbage disposal Central A/C Forced air heat Coffee maker Kitchenware Dishes  Linens Bath towels

neighborhood_overview: With all of the amazing restaurants, services, shops, and entertainment only steps away, you will fall in love with the charm and convenience of staying in this vibrant Little Italy neighborhood.  -Take afternoon or evening walks down to the U.S.S. Midway and wonderful San Diego Harbor front. Stroll down to the Gaslamp Quarter where you can live it up at one of numerous reputable restaurants or clubs.  -The San Diego Zoo and Balboa Park (my personal favorite) with all its museums and beauty is just minutes away.  -When it comes time to bid farewell, the airport is a convenient 10 min drive and exits to major highways are just a few blocks away.
notes: Children and pets welcome
transit: San Diego Metropolitan Transit System (SDMTS) has conveniently located the County Center/Little Italy station as part of the San Diego Trolley Green Line. -The trolley stop is approximately 5 blocks from this condo. -Amtrak train station is a 3 min cab or Uber ride.
access: 24 hr on site security guard -In building fitness center -Pool/jacuzzi -Multiple BBQs and patio area
interaction: Available, but not invasive. -Booking: Available and quick to respond to any questions or concerns. Email is the preferred option. -Upon arrival: Greeted with a smile at the door and show of the condo with instructions. -Upon departure: Pick up keys.
house_rules: Check-in at 3pm. Check-out is by 11 am. Arriving slightly earlier or want that extra hour to sleep? Should be fine, but please check with us first.  If you're coming to San Diego to party you've picked a great city to do so. Unfortunately, just not at our place. Though we're sure it won't come to it, complaints of items thrown off the balcony or loud and unruly behavior will unfortunately result in you being asked to leave. Not good for you. Not good for us. Being a family condo, we have a no smoking policy and strict no drug use policy. Have a dog? Should be no problem...but please ask us first. Cleaning fee is included in. We kindly ask that you switch off lights and the A/C when it is not in use or leaving the condo. Mother Nature thanks you too.  We understand that accidents happen. But we do ask that you please let us know when they do. Chances are we can fix them as effortlessly as possible which also means better chances of having your full security deposit returned too.

name: New Year's Eve in Gaslamp Quarter and more!
summary: The Gaslamp Plaza Suites is a historic hotel built in 1913.  This listing is the best in town. The entire Gaslamp is sold out for New Year's eve.  Cozy room for two with window seat view of the Quarter. Celebrate New Year in style without driving. Hurry to the rooftop at midnight for the spectacular fireworks displays.  Tour the zoo and other attractions for the rest of your vacation week.   Discounts and tours available at front desk.  And don't miss breakfast daily on the roof top terrace!
space: Beautiful private room with bath and mini kitchen.  The rooftop terrace serves breakfast each morning and is also a nice place to relax, read a book or see the view.  The Gaslamp Quarter is fun and easy to explore on foot. In fact, it's at your doorstep.

host_about: Retired,  in the prime of life.  Non-smoker, occasional social drinker, easy going and friendly.   I enjoy travelling and meeting new people.  Although it's fun to travel with others, I'm not afraid to strike out on my own. As an Airbnb guest I look for a clean, quiet space with a comfy bed, kitchen access, internet/wifi availability and relatively close to public transportation.  Separate or shared bathroom is fine.

name: Waterhaven - A Pondside Oasis
summary: Located in the Hillcrest area of San Diego just blocks to Balboa Park is Waterhaven, an adults only retreat and the perfect place to enjoy your San Diego stay. A cozy 325 square foot fully private retreat that includes your own living space, bathroom, and kitchen. The guesthouse has dual paned windows, no shared walls, and  the yard is fully protected with a stone wall for privacy and security. Waterhaven is a quiet, peaceful, relaxing experience.
space: Your spacious private patio is directly outside your guesthouse door, and sits next to a large koi pond with waterfalls. The guesthouse has a new heating and air conditioning unit for your comfort. The guesthouse is sparkling clean! We change the mattress pad, and hypoallergenic pillow encasings after every guest, and you will sleep well on a fantastic bed, with 1000 thread count cotton sheets. The cottage is located on the back half of our property. Off-street, on site parking is reserved for you. San Diego isn't just about beaches! Enjoy Balboa Park and its 17 museums, Old Town, live theater, street festivals, Food festivals, the Hotel Del Coronado, Legoland, the San Diego Zoo & Safari Park - And a scenic drive to the mountains or desert is always nice.  Waterhaven is more than just a place to stay, it's an experience, and we look forward to sharing it with you! Guests have full access to the entire house, excluding the garage. Del Mar is a beautiful neighborhood with world class dining, shopping, beaches, friendly locals, and beautiful nature.  The world famous Del Mar Racing is near by, and it's only 5 minutes away from the ocean. Across the street from m
neighborhood_overview: Del Mar is a beautiful neighborhood with world class dining, shopping, beaches, friendly locals, and beautiful nature.  The world famous Del Mar Racing is near by, and it's only 5 minutes away from the ocean. Across the street from my house there is a trendy shopping mall Del Mar Highlands Town Center, where you can grab a coffee, snack, groceries, go to a fancy movie theater Cinépolis, grab a nice dinner, access a bank or get to a pharmacy. All a short walk away from my place. For other things a car is needed. Del Mar and Torrey Pines are two beaches that are the closest (and nicest in my opinion). Del Mar beach has a lovely park and great restaurants. Torrey Pines has an amazing hike trail called Torrey Pines State Reserve with gorgeous ocean views - I think it's a must if you're in San Diego.
notes: I would be happy to help you with whatever you need - just let me know by texting, and I'll be there as needed.

name: Creative North Park Back House
summary: This 100 year old creative, wood floor 1 bed craftsman in North Park is walking distance to dozens of breweries, restaurants and shops + a quick 15 min  drive from nearly all of San Diego. North Park is a very walkable and friendly neighborhood with lots of action both days and nights. Dogs are welcome but will require an extra $40 for cleaning.
space: Comfortable and minimalist 1920's 1 bedroom back house that is creatively painted with wood floors, a tile shower, a full kitchen / BBQ grill and an outside courtyard with a lemon tree. Though it's stocked, it's not fully stocked to meet ALL your standards. It's a real home, not a hotel.

notes: The private entrance is through the Alley between 30th and Ohio. Dogs are welcome and can hang in the courtyard during the day, though the front house has a small dog that can be a little barky. For pets I require an extra $40 cleaning fee. It's an old house so it has it's quirks :) It's my home (not a hotel, it's worth repeating) and I love it so much. I rent it while traveling so please treat it accordingly
transit: If you do want to leave the neighborhood the house is right on El Cajon, a major throughway that leads to downtown or directly to the 805. Getting home is super easy, too, as the exit from the 805 is less than a quarter mile from the house.

interaction: I'm usually traveling but am almost always accessible via messaging. I have local help if anything immediate and urgent comes up.
house_rules: The front house is a family with two young children so please try to keep quiet around night time. Closing the door and windows helps. Dogs are welcome but require a $70 cleaning few instead of $30. No smoking.
host_about: I grew up in Austin, Texas but then hit the road to travel before settling in San Diego. I run an idea brand that's based on spreading inspiration so I travel often to new cities, sharing stories from people, companies and communities who are making a positive impact. But it's always amazing come home to San Diego and especially North Park!

host_since: Apartment is located in the historic Sherman Heights District, which has been undergoing major renovation of many buildings throughout the district. While not all buildings in the district are historic, many are, including the famous Villa Montezuma, which is now a museum and only 1.5 blocks away. IMPORTANT: Please keep in mind that San Diego is the 2nd largest city in California and like many major U.S. cities, we have our share of homeless people. In fact, since we are a large naval city, we may have more than usual, as many homeless people are former veterans of war that are either down on their luck or suffering from mental/physical conditions. So, whether you choose to stay in our cute micro apartment or one of the major hotels (US Grant or The W @ $300-$500 a night), you need to expect to see homeless people, their shopping carts and the occasional panhandling. With this in mind, PLEASE do not give a negative review due to any experience you may have with the homeless, as we have
host_location: FAQ WHAT IS A MICRO APARTMENT? A micro apartment is a uniquely designed small apartment with the basic essentials often found in European and some major U.S. cities. All areas are compact, yet comfortable. This particular apartment boasts a very comfortable queen size bed, private bathroom and private kitchenette; many micro apartments have small beds and shared bathrooms, but not ours! Although micro apartments historically were used for long-term residents with simple needs, today they're more commonly used for short-term guests. Our apartment is modern and updated for the needs of today's travelers. While the apartment is very nice, we realize it's not for everyone. If you don't like small unique spaces, please consider other listings. We want you to be happy! AIR CONDITIONING? More than half of the homes in San Diego do NOT have Air Conditioning, which many guests from other areas of the country find mind-boggling. However, our San Diego climate is very mild and extremely pleasant
host_about: San Diego is home to many modes of transportation. Some of the newest and most popular methods are electric scooters and bicycles.  They are both simple to operate and fun to use. Electric Scooters & Bikes (download app to your smartphone) To get FREE RIDE CREDITS, use the codes below: BIRD (black labels) – Use Code: ZGVXBM LIME (lime green label) – Use Code: RDMDLE6 SPIN (orange label) – Use Code: KNUCKBOG Ride Share Services (available to/from airport too) To get FREE RIDE CREDITS, use the codes below:  UBER – Use Code: QBEZ0 LYFT – Use Code: KEVIN14245 Buses and Trolley (rail system).  Closest Bus Stop: 22nd & Market Streets Closest Trolley Stop: 25th & Commercial Streets Visit: (Website hidden by Airbnb) to plan your trip or purchase electronic tickets Sorry, but we do not currently have bicycle racks for guests.
host_response_time: Shared quiet use of front balcony with views of downtown, Coronado Island, Petco Park and more. Coin-operated laundry on first floor (no laundry after 9pm)
host_response_rate: Minimal communication with hosts, but we're here if you need us.
host_acceptance_rate: - Quiet Hours from 10:30pm - 7:30am - Smoking/vaping permitted only in backyard (never on balconies) - Guest to be considerate of other residents - No laundry after 9pm - No pets under any circumstances
street:
I am working professional in the real estate industry. I manage leased apartments and homes and I broker real estate sales transaction. In addition to managing and brokering properties, I own several of my own and have become somewhat of an expert in remodeling, especially on a budget. As a traveler, I'm pretty easy going. I don't need an overly fancy place, but can appreciate one if that's what I select. My main needs are clean and comfortable. Further, hosts should know that as a property owner myself, I am very respectful of others, their personal property and of course, diversity of living situation.

When I'm not working or traveling, I can often be found enjoying time with friends, my 9.5 year old extremely well-behaved dog named Miss Pickles, or quiet time. I also enjoy visiting Palm Springs where I also have a small home.

While I enjoy going out for drinks at a club on occasion, I tend to prefer more intimate gatherings with friends at one of our homes or a restaurant. Being around quality people interests me far more than the quantity of people. That said, when I'm out, some say I'm the life of a party as I tend to have a pretty good sense of humor.

If you host a place for me, I think you'll find me to be a good guest and one that you would extend an invitation to again. I do not smoke nor do I bring my pet on my trips, unless we've discussed such in advance.  I look forward to meeting you in the future!

neighborhood_overview: Cortex Hill is the northernmost area of downtown San Diego, particularly known for the Cortex Building. Much of this family-friendly area is pedestrianized, and there are many sidewalk cafes along Fifth and Sixth Avenues. The apartment is located at the top of the hill, away from the hustle and bustle of downtown (and a park right in front). The neighborhood is blocks away from the beautiful Balboa Park/SD Zoo, renowned restaurants in Little Italy, the waterfront and the Convention Center.
notes: We have a dog which is seen in some of the photos. He comes to work with me so is usually either with us or away from the home. He is very friendly he is also very old (15).
transit: We live so Central to many favorite hot spots in San Diego. Bankers Hill Balboa Park Little Italy downtown and Harbor area are all within walking distance less than a mile away. There is also taxi services available as well as a free transportation service in the downtown area that you can ask us about. Finally the train station is about a mile away in case you are planning on going to LA or somewhere North and the trolley station is just a few blocks away.

Common areas such as dining and living room are not included. A city parking pass is provided for your stay (loss of the pass will incur a $100 fee)
interaction: My husband and I work everyday during the week and usually come home for dinner for a quiet and mellow evening. We respect our guests privacy and space during their stay and expect the same in return. We are available for any tips or recommendations as well.
house_rules: • No rowdiness - be respectful of the shared space. • No consumption of our food or beverage unless otherwise indictaded • Clean after yourself at all times during your stay.
host_about:
My husband and I are professionals in our 30s  from San Diego and Mexico City.
 
We are friendly, responsible and clean guests and/or hosts, and look to receive the same treatment back. So far its been great!

We host two homes in San Diego, one in Eastlake which is in Chula Vista and the other in Cortez Hill which is near downtown San Diego. Chula Vista is a quiet residential area with all the essentials, including nice walks, shops, restaurants, parks, etc.  It is very peaceful and easy. Cortez Hill is centrally located to all of the fun activities San Diego has to offer, yet still quiet enough to enjoy some peace after an active day. We would love to share a bit of our San Diego during your visit.

host_id: Ocean Beach is one of the more laid back and relaxing beach towns in San Diego. Yoga studios, coffee houses, restaurants, bars and of course, the beach! The main street is only a few blocks away with shopping and night life.  The street is closed down every Wednesday afternoon to host a farmers market.   The main strip ends at the beach and the Ocean Beach pier, the longest pier on the west coast. Next to this is the beach.  Balboa Park and the world famous San Diego Zoo are a 10 minute drive. A 10 minute drive will also bring you to Hillcrest or downtown San Diego with it's historic Gaslamp Quarter and well-known night life. The beachfront amusement park, Belmont Park, is only 2 miles away if you'd like to ride the Giant Dipper roller coaster or be whirled around on some of the other rides. Sea World is 1 mile away.  Take a 2 minute drive out to Sunset Cliffs for an amazing sunset over the ocean. Go to 3rd Corner for a great glass of wine and some amazing food. Find good coffee on sev
host_url: Please note: The airport is centrally located in the city, therefore you will hear airplanes when visiting San Diego. Flights begin around 6:30am and stop around 10pm. My attic is well insulated and the house has double pane Anderson windows to limit noise during the day. However if you are sensitive to noise Ocean Beach, Point Loma and Bankers Hill may not be the spots for you. There is a very friendly cat in residence who mostly lives outside but will be happy to come in if you let her. No cat odor, not to worry. But if you have allergies my place is not a good choice.
host_name: You can walk to restaurants, breweries, beach (10 min), a great local organic market is a block away. This neighborhood is all about leaving your car, relaxing, and walking out to dinner at night. A bus stop and a convenience store are a short block away. Easy freeway access by car or a quick uber ride to downtown, other beaches, or Sea World.  Ocean Beach is the most centrally located beach in San Diego and gives the best access to downtown. The San Diego trolley system is nearby. Also, the trains are conveniently close if you'd like to take a scenic day trip up the coast to Los Angeles or even Disneyland.
host_since: You have a whole beautiful house, yard and covered deck for your use. The house shares a wall with a studio, but that entrance is separate. The covered patio and inner courtyard are lit at night and make a beautiful eating and lounging area. Locked gates make the area completely secure and 8 foot fences create your own private world.
host_location: I am available any time by phone and text. I leave you a guide book to the area, wine to start your trip and coffee to get you going in the morning! If you need different check in times please ask. Summers are a busy time and early check in may be difficult, but I can accomodate bag drop off.
host_about: - Please respect quiet residential neighborhood. No loud noise after 10. No shoes in house. - NO SMOKING inside or out please.
host_total_listings_count: Originally from the East Coast I am practical and down to earth. I am an avid surfer, love finding a great restaurant, enjoy wine tasting. Traveling the world has taught me what is important for comfort in a rental. I provide my guests with as much information and lovely surroundings as possible.

name: Find Your Zen in a Pristine Casita in South Park
summary: Wake up to fountain sounds outside the door and friendly hummingbirds, butterflies, and bees feeding off native plants in the sunny courtyard. This southwestern-style casita with all the comforts is just miles from downtown and San Diego's best beaches, but feels a world away.
space: Welcome to our immaculate get away in San Diego. This casita is tucked away in the middle of San Diego’s historic South Park neighborhood and feels a world away from the hustle and bustle of the city. South Park is the most idyllic of San Diego’s urban core neighborhoods. Beautiful single-family homes perched on canyons with 100-year-old eucalyptus trees abound. Imagine waking up your own sunny courtyard to the sound of a fountain right outside your door with friendly lizards, birds, butterflies, bees and hummingbirds feeding off of the native plants and flowers that surround the property. The only other sounds you hear in this private tucked away gem are the winds rustling through the giant eucalyptus and bamboo right outside your window. Enjoy morning coffee in the courtyard filled with the smell of jasmine as you wake up to the warm San Diego sunshine. This cozy little casita comes complete with Topochico water, granola bars and coffee to get your San Diego adventure off to a refres
description: Wake up to fountain sounds outside the door and friendly hummingbirds, butterflies, and bees feeding off native plants in the sunny courtyard. This southwestern-style casita with all the comforts is just miles from downtown and San Diego's best beaches, but feels a world away.
neighborhood_overview: Explore San Diego from the South Park neighborhood with restaurants ranging from innovative vegan food to upmarket Italian eats. Tree-lined Fern and 30th Streets are home to indie boutiques and cafes, and nearby Grape Street Dog Park has city views.
notes: As an added bonus, a licensed acupuncturist and massage therapist lives on-site. If you are interested in scheduling an appointment as part of your stay, please let me know.
transit: Your private casita is only: 3 very walkable blocks from endless dining and shopping options in South Park; 5 minutes from the dozens of craft brewers in North Park; 10 minutes from the Gaslamp Quarter in Downtown San Diego, Coronado Island, world famous San Diego Zoo, Balboa Park, Sea World, Convention Center, Petco Park and San Diego Bay/Harbor; 15 mintes from multiple beaches, La Jolla, 32nd St Naval Station, Miramar Air Base, Cowels Mountain and Mission Gorge; 20 minutes from the Mexican border and Tijuana; and 60 mintes from Rosarito Mexico, Orange County, Camp Pendleton, Julian and the Anza Borrego Desert

interaction: Owners live on-site and are available for questions throughout your stay.

name: Private room in cute Hillcrest home, close to all!
summary: Welcome to our home!  It is cute and unique but most importantly it is close to everything!  One of the things I love most is it is easy to get to by car and about a $7 Lyft ride to almost everything fun.  On the weekends I am home, I don't even move my car.  I can walk to an amazing brunch, Lyft to the Embarcadero or Lyft to a night out.  If you are coming from out of town, you are in luck!  I work in Tourism, so I know all the best places and things to do.
space: At our house, you will have your own room.  Yes, it is a shared bathroom.  However, the most I am home is for an hour or 2 to do a work out video in the living room, no joke.  I love them!  So pretty much consider the bathroom all yours.  There is a nice size dining room and kitchen so you will have plenty of space.  The bed is very comfy in my opinion.  I have had many people stay in the room and they all comment on it.  There is a tv in the bedroom, feel free to use it for Netflix or Hulu.

transit: There are many ways to explore San Diego.  Walking:  About a 15 minute walk to Adams Ave. where you'll find many of the neighborhood's favorite bars and restaurants including the Rabbit Hole, Blind Lady Ale House, Sycamore Den, Starbucks, Dao Fu (our favorite Vietnamese spot), vegan restaurants, Thai and more.   Bike/Scooter:  San Diego has many different bike/scooter share programs. Download one of the Apps, find a bike or scooter on the street, unlock with your smartphone and go. It's a great way to venture beyond Normal Heights and explore other nearby neighborhoods.  Uber/Lyft: Ride sharing Apps are a smart and convenient way to access most parts of the city at very affordable prices. We typically get to/from downtown San Diego for around $10 each way.

host_about:
My name is Amanda Wiggins and I am an Account Review Associate at Commonwealth Financial Network.  I am also a retired professional beach volleyball player, high school varsity coach and club volleyball coach, and an entrepreneur from Monument, Colorado.  During the summers, I used to travel and compete on the professional beach volleyball tour against some of the best players in the country.  Now I try to get outside as much as possible, but I coach more than I play.  Currently, I am the Varsity Indoor and Beach Volleyball coach at University City High School as well as a club coach for La Jolla Volleyball Club.  I have been living in the San Diego area for almost 8 years and remain very active in the community.   
My personality is friendly and outgoing, I love to travel, and make friends with a spontaneous and adventurous spirit.  I am always willing to try something once.  I love all types of animals, enjoy hanging out with my friends and family, I love to workout and push myself to the limits, and I especially enjoy the sunshine and beach.  A few things I can't live without are: My Hydroflask Waterbottle, a volleyball, pillow, friends, and my family.
   
I look forward to hosting my place on AirBnB.  My goal is for others to enjoy sunny San Diego as much as I do.  I am very laid back and my sense of style is bright and playful.  The sunshine and bright colors make me happy, and are reflected in my home design.  I want people to feel like they are on a relaxing vacation and able to get away from reality.  My hope is that my place feels cozy and has the characteristics of a home away from home!  People will want to tell their friends about my place and come back, I know it!!!  My style of travel is definitely reflected in my hosting.  
My life motto:  YOLO" You Only Live Once.  So live with no regrets!!"

neighborhood_overview: Hillcrest is a charming, historic neighborhood in San Diego and the heart of San Diego's LGBTQ community. You'll be in the center of a thriving business center, featuring a wide variety of restaurants from very casual to fine dining, bars and clubs, retail shopping and more.   For grocery needs, Trader Joe's, Ralph's, and Sprouts are a mere 4 minute walk away.   Balboa Park, museums, and the world famous San Diego ZOO are an easy 12 minute walk away. Hillcrest is also vibrant center of gay life in San Diego and is the perfect place to celebrate PRIDE (July 12-14)!  For further exploration the world-famous Gaslamp Quarter is less than 10 minutes away by car. Beautiful San Diego beaches and SeaWorld are less than 15 minutes from our doorstep as well. If you prefer to take public transportation multiple major bus routes have a hub at the transit center one block away at the intersection of University Ave. and Park Blvd.

house_rules: -Home needs to be treated with respect and care. -Pets not allowed. If found evidence of pet brought to property without permission for there will be a $200 fee. - Please contact with any questions you may have when staying at the property. Do not ask the neighbors for anything.  Any altercation with neighbor will also result in loss of deposit.    -Any damages or cost occurred to home by guests, i.e. damage to walls, extra cleaning by large mess, damage to items in home, will be sought after and recuperated through all available means. I will determine the amount soley based on what I believe to be reasonable compensation - No additional guests allowed than given permission for. No parties or events. Any infraction of these or noise complaints by the neighbors and you will be charged full deposit amount.  -There will be additional charge for larger mess. Examples are lots of trash left around, kitchen left very messy, lots of sand from beach on floor.  House rules not being followed.
host_about: Thank you for your interest in a Curiel Collection home.  I take pride in offering my guests some of the most luxurious and unique stays in San Diego.  Design and architecture have always been a passion of mine and I believe it shows in my properties.  Each home offers beautifully appointed accommodations that emphasize comfort and quality.  My property manager, Alexander, will help ensure you have a pleasant stay and is available to answer any questions you might have.  We both respond to messages on the Airbnb app to ensure atimely responses. It is his personal information attached to this bio and he will be the person who you will be in contact with you about my properties. All the reviews are a reflection of the dedicated team I have assembled to ensure my guests have the best stay possible.  -- David Curiel, owner

name: Private bed and bath in walkable North Park
summary: 1 bedroom available in airy 2 bedroom home, featuring gas stove, vaulted ceilings, and wood floors. Mid-century modern decor. It's a condo unit but feels more like a loft!   5 min drive from 805 and I-8, but it's quiet.  We have WiFi/Netflix/basic tv channels.
space: It's central and spacious, right near all the hip parts of North Park.
description: 1 bedroom available in airy 2 bedroom home, featuring gas stove, vaulted ceilings, and wood floors. Mid-century modern decor. It's a condo unit but feels more like a loft!   5 min drive from 805 and I-8, but it's quiet.  We have WiFi/Netflix/basic tv channels. It's central and spacious, right near all the hip parts of North Park. Guests will have a bedroom and separate bathroom, and access to all shared spaces. You would be sharing the space with my partner and I, and our two Devon Rex cats We will be staying in the house at that time, and occasionally work from home, but are often gone in the evenings. It's the best!  One of the few walking neighborhoods in San Diego.  Two blocks from the restaurant hub of Adams Avenue and walking distance to both Park Blvd and 30th St, where you'll find plenty of cafes, bars, restaurants, yoga studios, etc. There's a little store a few doors down that makes excellent sandwiches and salads. neighborhood_overview: It's the best!  One of the few walking neighborhoods in San Diego.  Two blocks from the restaurant hub of Adams Avenue and walking distance to both Park Blvd and 30th St, where you'll find plenty of cafes, bars, restaurants, yoga studios, etc. There's a little store a few doors down that makes excellent sandwiches and salads. Close to some of the best restaurants, cafes and bars in the city, like Jayne's Gastropub, Black Market Bakery, Red House Pizza, Tajima Ramen and Polite Provisions.
notes: Our cats are extremely social and will probably follow you around the house and sit on you!
transit: There are buses a few blocks away that go downtown. On street parking available.

name: The Cove - The Bed & Breakfast Inn at La Jolla
summary: LUXURY QUEEN: 1 Queen Bed,  2nd Floor. Accessible via stairs. Moderately sized.  Romantic and light with operable windows catching the coastal breezes and offering a view of the La Jolla Museum of Art and the lush foliage surrounding the Inn.  Featuring hardwood floors, a rare country pine armoire, and decorative fireplace to add to the ambiance.  NO TV in suite, but steps to Inn's public library with TV/DVD and sun deck.  European style bathroom (small but efficient) Shower - No Tub.   Adult Only Room - No exceptions! Not appropriate or able to accommodate children under 15 yrs of age. Maximum two adults per room. No Pet Room - No exceptions!
space: We are a 15 room boutique BnB located in the heart of La Jolla Village in San Diego County.  Each guest room is appointed with different amenities and in their own style and design.  Listed as Historical Site 179  on the San Diego Registry, our Inn has a rich historical past that allows guests to explore and become lost in its stories. It was originally built as a residence for George Kautz family in 1913. The original Gardens were designed by famed horticulturist Kate Sessions, also a well known San Diego figure, who was responsible for Balboa Park and the Scripps Family Gardens. Both these individuals are honored as names of our guest rooms. It also served as the home to the March King
description: John Philip Sousa's family in the 1920s. It is one of the premier romantic inns in San Diego. Celebrating over 100 years of Architectural History, the bed and breakfast Inn is considered one of the finest examples of Irving Gill’s 1913 Cubist Style" Architecture."

Burlingame Historic District, a 10-block pocket uniquely located between North Park and South Park, offers easy access to both neighborhoods and is rich in early-century Craftsman and Spanish Revival bungalows. The guesthouse is minutes from Balboa Park, San Diego Zoo, Downtown Convention Center, Petco Park, Little Italy, Old Town, and Hillcrest. San Diego beaches, Coronado and the airport are all nearby.

neighborhood_overview: The Neighborhood - if you are looking for great food and nightlife, the heart of the North Park nighberhood is about 10 minutes walk. Hillcrest and Downtown/Gaslamp are also a cheap Cab/Uber ride away. To get to the nearest beach will take about 15 minutes.
notes: Close By - the Casita is just steps away from Morley Field portion of Balboa Park. You'll enjoy easy access to hiking trails, the Balboa tennis club, the Bud Kearns Memorial Swimming Pool, the San Diego Velodrome, Morley Field Disk Golf Course, and the Balboa Park Golf Course. Less then a mile away is the world famous San Diego Zoo, the San Diego Natural History Museum, the San Diego Air & Space Museum, the Old Globe Theater, and much more.
transit: Getting Around - San Diego is best experienced with a car. We have plenty of street parking directly in front of our house and easy access to several main freeways. It takes about 10 minutes to the beach or to shopping malls. If a car is not an option you can utilize the MTS bus lines (University ave, or 30th street), bike rental stations (short term rental for jumping between nighberhoods), and the of course Lyft and Uber ($12 to the airport).

Disturbing our neighbors is not tolerated. - Please leave the Casita in the same condition as you found it and reasonably clean. We appreciate it!

host_url: Guests have their own private entrance at the rear of the property. The apartment includes a secluded patio area surrounded by tons of greenery, in addition to the common garden areas of the property.
host_name: I like to greet all my guests upon check-in to insure they are comfortable in their suite. Should circumstances prevent, it is easy to let yourselves in by following the instructions listed under 'Directions' within your Airbnb itinerary. I'm social & outgoing and happy to offer guests recommendations to make their holiday more enjoyable. Just ask.
host_since: Pets are not allowed and the apartment is not ideal for a family; two adult maximum. Due to safety concerns, toddlers (1-3 years?) are not allowed because of glass items, sharp or toxic plants. Smoking is only allowed outdoors with consideration of neighbors. As a courtesy to neighbors, please be mindful of noise levels between 10 pm and 6 am. Guests are expected to treat all areas of the property with the same respect they would give their own.
host_neighbourhood:
I love hosting! It suits my personality. And, I love being a traveling guest. Tell me what you're looking for in a San Diego experience and I'll do my best to direct you toward it. Just ask!
Born in the mid-west and raised in southern California, I've grown up appreciating our weather that allows outdoor activities year round such as the beach, volleyball, gardening, music venues, local winter skiing and occasional pubbing with friends.
I'm socially out-going and love to meet people of different cultures and points of view. I believe that travel makes us better and more balanced. My philosophy is: a city is a city; the difference is the people you meet along the way. 
One of my passions is travel: I've been fortunate to Scuba dive in the Red Sea, Palau, & Fiji, ski at Whistler, Breckenridge and Mammoth, cruise the Baltic, Mediterranean and meet friends for sun & fun in Sydney, Capetown and Thailand. 
I'm lived in and am a landscape designer in beautiful San Diego the past 24 years.

name: One-Bedroom Apartment w/ Balcony over Balboa Park
summary: My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers. A baby would be ok, but I think it's too small for people traveling with an older kid.
space: I live in Banker's Hill, a quiet residential neighborhood between downtown and Hillcrest. It faces from Balboa Park, one of the largest and perhaps nicest city parks in America. I have a one-bedroom apartment in a 1940's style of architecture with iron railings and French doors. The balcony overlooks Balboa Park. There's a shared courtyard in the back, too. It's my home, and my personality comes through in colors and artwork being described as bohemian, colorful, and comfortable. It's quiet at nighttime. Within a five minute walk are cafes and restaurants known for high quality but with a laid-back atmosphere. It's conveniently located ~ 4 miles from the airport, but you don't hear airplanes due to the hills and canyons.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in Banker's Hill, a quiet residential area between Downtown and Hillcrest. My balcony overlooks Balboa Park, one of the largest and most beautiful urban parks in America, with hiking trails, museums, playgrounds, and sports centers spread across 3,800 acres. You can explore the area on foot, and a bus route to other parts of San Diego is a few blocks away. The area is residential and quiet, just far enough away from shopping to seem secluded. There are many cafes, restaurants, shopping, and groceries stores within 5-10 minutes walking distance. It's near Downtown San Diego (1 mile), Hillcrest (1/2 mile), North Park (2 miles), SeaWorld (7 miles), etc. It's about 1/2 mile from the ocean as the crow flies" - the closest public beaches are 8 miles away. house_rules: including thr"
thumbnail_url: It's worth reiterating that I live here. It's clean and organized but definitely my home, so please manage your expectations - this is not a spotless hotel, it's like staying in a friend's home who keeps it clean but hasn't replaced every damaged floor tile and may have missed cleaning dust in some corners. Most people love the balcony, watching the museum of man or listening to lions roar from the zoo. I have coffee on the balcony in the mornings, and a beer in the evenings with friends. I love it - it's why I maintain this place while traveling. My friends and people who have sub-leted, through another website, love the balcony and views of Balboa Park. I hope you'd enjoy it, too. A balcony facing Balboa Park may not be for everyone. It's at street-level, five feet from the sidewalk, so people occasionally walk by. Most are neighbors, either in my apartment building or the two super-nice condos on either side. Occasionally a homeless person strolls by, on their way downtown or simply
host_id: The airport is ~ 4 miles away. Most people would take a cab or Lyft. The train station is ~ a mile away, with a national Amtrak station, a commuter train going to North County, and a trolley providing access to other parts of San Diego. There are a few public bus routes nearby, but San Diego is not known for public transportation.
host_url: Kitchen, washing machine, etc are for your enjoyment. Guests can use most of the apartment, realizing that I live here therefore most shelf space is utilized. I purchased a large armoire and dresser for guests to hang or store clothes. There's also guest-dedicated towels, sheets, etc. There's wifi but no cable or television. The washing machine and dryer are in a shared space. It requires quarters, $1.75 for washing and $1.50 for drying.
host_name: I won't be available throughout the stay except in rare situations. I'm just now starting to try AirBnB-ing my place when I'm traveling for work. I may expand to when I'm camping or rock climbing in Southern California, which I do often.
host_neighbourhood:
I'm a consultant for equitable healthcare and education, traveling for workshops and fundraising.

I also travel often for rock climbing and fishing trips. Locally this is in the Sierra Nevada mountains and Baja, Mexico; but I try to explore other areas nationally and internationally.

In San Diego, I brew beer, surf, ride bicycles (one for fast & far, one for leisurely exploring), practice the guitar (I'm horrible), cook, and go see live music.

Strollers, bikes and dog walking are a familiar scene as people enjoy this charming seaside community. The local Von's supermarket and Trader Joe's is a quick 6 blocks away.
notes: If you want to cook at home, the kitchen is outfitted with dishes, glassware, pots, pans, blender, toaster oven, silverware, major appliances, and an outdoor bbq, etc...  If TV,  internet, Roku, or Netflix's aren't your things then grab the beach cruisers for a fun ride along the bay. -Please note there is no parking at the rental.   Street parking is available. -This unit is on the 1st floor with a rental unit above.   Please be advised this rental is located in a family friendly area. The bars and nightlife are about 5 blocks away. Please don't bring the party home. This is not a party house. We require that you be respectful of our neighbors and minimize the noise past 9:00 PM! The is also an onsite free laundry room available.
transit: Once you arrive in Pacific Beach, the best way to enjoy the area is to walk or ride bikes. You can drive too of course, but if you don't want to hassle with parking, Uber is a quick and easy way to get anywhere you need to go… Sea World just a short jaunt away along with the World Famous San Diego Zoo, Lego land, and beautiful Balboa Park. -Please note the rental does not have parking.  Street parking is available.
access: Guests have access to the full condo as well as beach chairs, beach cruisers/bikes, Netflix, Roku, TV, full kitchen, and lots more.  The bikes are great for riding along the boardwalk, the bay, or for quick transportation.
interaction: I manage 3 other rental properties so I am always available.  If something is not working right or you need something I live close by.

If you make your way towards La Jolla Village, stop and take a look at one of the most popular beaches called Wind-n-Sea, brunch at Cody's at the Cove and say hi to the seals as well! The list can go on forever!

Walking is okay for Golden Hill restaurants and cafes. There is also a bus stop close by that leads to downtown and the trolley system.  There is a great bike rental program in San Diego that is basically a self check out. There is a station by the Starbuck's a few blocks away where you can check one out for an hourly rate, weekly, or monthly. The prices are 1hr/$7, 2hr/$12, Weekly/$35 and monthly for $50. Search online for deco bike san diego for info.

neighborhood_overview: Mission Beach is the perfect place to be based during your stay in San Diego. You will have all you need within walking distance! The peaceful and laid back bay is on one side of the peninsula, this is the ideal place for an early morning paddle board while watching the sun rise. To the other side you have the open waves of the Pacific Ocean, the perfect place to test out your surfing skills. You can easily rent out a surfboard or take lessons from one of the shops down the promenade. Other great water-sports available include  boogie boarding and kite boarding to name just a few. If you fancy a break from the waves you should head to the historic wooden roller coaster at Belmont Park, known as the Big Dipper.  If you walk all the way down the boardwalk you will arrive at Pacific Beach (PB), the lively young beach that has numerous bars and restaurants.  The other attractions of San Diego, such as Balboa Park, Downtown, Ocean Beach and La Jolla are all very accessible by car and Uber.
transit: Mission Beach is one of the most walkable beach towns around. You can use pay-as-you-go scooters or bikes like Lime, Bird, Wheels etc. Want to rent a car by the hour? Check out Getaround and use promo code AIRSORTED

neighborhood_overview: Golden Hill is the heart of the city of San Diego. From here everything is close. This culturally diverse and walkable neighborhood is home to Craftsman cottages, cafes and diners, coffee shops, several microbreweries, boutiques, farmers market (North Park Farmers Market is on Thursdays 3-8 pm). The North Park Theater and the Ray Street Arts District" are also bastions of creativity in the area. Golden Hill will surprise you!"
notes: Convention Center is 2 miles away. Balboa Park and the Zoo 1 mile away. Stores, restaurants, coffee shops and much more walking distance.
transit: The house is centrally located, between Downtown and South Park. Balboa Park is walking distance. Downtown less than 5 minutes by car or 20 minutes by foot. You can reach easily the Convention Center by car (few minutes) or electric scooters. Beaches (OB and PB) 15 minutes by car. The house is served by BUS #2. There is plenty of parking on the street (no meteor). Also it is a very bike friendly neighborhood. Liquor store in the corner (half block away). Other grocery stores, Target, Gas stations and 7/11 open 24 hrs in the area a few blocks distance.

neighborhood_overview: Hillcrest and its neighbors was the first development outside the downtown San Diego and was built in the 1920's and 1930's. There are many fine examples of Carftsman and Spanish Mission style homes.
transit: Casa Feliz is a pleasant 15 minute walk to the San Diego Zoo and Balboa Park. A 5 minute drive takes you to downtown San Diego, Seaport Village, Petco Park (home of the the San Diego Padres baseball team), The Convention Center (where ComiCon is hosted), The historic Gaslamp Quarter, Little Italy, The Embarcadero, North Park, UCSD Medical center, Scripps Mercy Hospital, Fashion Valley Mall, and Qualcomm Stadium. Just 10 minutes away you can also enjoy historic Old Town, Point Loma Lighthouse, Coronado, Ocean Beach, Pacific Beach, Mission Beach, the USS Midway Aircraft Carrier Museum, Liberty Station, San DIego's famous craft breweries, plus Sea World, and San Diego State University (SDSU). Casa Fleiz is a perfect natural retreat with convenient access to all of San Diego Adventure. It is just 500 feet to the bus stop. An amazing diversity of restaurants and cuisines are available within walking distance, and some just a short drive away. You can enjoy; Japanese, Mexican, American, Thai
interaction: We live on the premises and are usually available to assist with anything you might need.  While Hillcrest is a vibrant neighborhood with many activities within walking distance, we and our neighbors view our homes as a retreat from the energy of the city. Our immediate neighbors are quiet, and would appreciate your respectful quiet after 10 p.m. Finding a place to park your car is a real issue in Hillcrest, there are too many cars. San Diego has a very good bus and trolley system that will get you just about anywhere if you're not in a hurry. host_about: The Navy (30yrs ret) has given me the opportunity to travel many places around the world.  Traveling is always so exciting. Meeting people, cultures, experiences, traditions, but it's given me more appreciation for San Diego.  Our family lives in the front home. Your space is completely detached and private in the back, upstairs above the garage, with beautiful views of San Diego Bay, airport and more. Whether on business or pleasure, our location is literally just over a mile (as the crow flies) from the airport, downtown, Balboa Park / Zoo, Old Town and about 4 miles to the beach. Maybe you want to visit Little Italy, the Gaslamp district, or take in a Padres game, all minutes away.  Beautiful Coronado Island is a 10 minute drive across the bridge or, better yet, take the ferry or water taxi for a real experience.  For golfers, we have exceptional weather for year round golf. Many courses to choose from. The upscale community of Mission Hills is one of the oldest in San Diego, with homes dating back 100 years.  What brings people to our community is the uniqueness and the convenience to anywhere you want to go. Keep in mind it's city, so understand its planes, trains, and automobiles nearby.  Come experience San Diego. You won't be disappointed.

neighborhood_overview: Mother Nature, walkability-bikeability, Calumet Park, Beaches both north and south. Tranquility, stately trees, meditative, zen-ful, tucked away country lane ambiance yet three blocks to ocean, walking distance to restaurants, studios, shops, Pilates and amazing sunsets. Ocean breeze, friendly, ease of transportation, Bird Rock Coffee Roasters: direct trade coffee=farm to coffee cup; outdoor yoga to live music at Riff's.
notes: When staying in the La Jolla Serene, one has the feeling of sleeping in a garden if the curtains and sliding glass door remain open, the sliding screen door remains closed, the garden lights (or moon light) shine on the prolific foliage in the private patio.  It is magical and cozy as you feel you are sleeping outside while tucked under a down comforter, listening to zen-ful or romantic music.
transit: If you are debating between renting a car or 'Ubering' about, there is a lot to be said for 'Ubering'. If most of your time will be spent in and around the beach areas, a car can be frustrating due to a lack of parking and time restrictions. Uber drivers typically arrive to my door within three minutes. If, on the other hand, the larger portion of your time will be exploring the greater San Diego area, then perhaps renting a car is a better option. Other modes of transport include walking, biking, jogging, skateboarding, surfing, buses. Bus # 30, 2 blocks from my home, travels to convenient points of interest: Wind n' Sea Beach, La Jolla Shores, Mission and Pacific Beaches, the Village of La Jolla, UCSD, La Jolla Village, Del Mar, 101 North, Westfield Shopping Center, and Old Town for trolley services which provides access to downtown, Mexico, Mission and Fashion Valley. Bike and surfboard rentals are two blocks away.
access: All common areas.
interaction: As much or as little as guest prefers.
house_rules: Available for responsible, independent, educated, resident who appreciates a clean, organized, respectful ambiance in which to live a relaxed spoiled lifestyle. We welcome you to enjoy the entire home as this will be your 'home away from home'. No pets; non-smokers and non-smoking only.
host_about:
As a  La Jolla native, I have seen many changes to our sweet village by the sea.  The constant however is the horizon; it is this endless view of magic that is just three blocks from my home and a perfect place to enjoy morning coffee and evening wine.

I am the grandmother of five lovely grandchildren, a retired school teacher having taught K through adult education, and a retired concierge from two magnificent local hotels.

Are there places you have traveled where you sense that you belong.....those places beyond the borders of your birth community?   It is one of my goals that your time in my home and in our village by the sea gives you that sense of belonging.

Passionate about  hospitality and meeting guests from all over the world, I look forward to  sharing the zen that my coastal home and garden paradise provides.

name: Secluded Studio with Canyon View
summary: Perched on a secluded canyon rim in the heart of San Diego, this light and airy studio cottage is only 1.5 miles from the Zoo and Balboa Park. Perfect for one or two, it has canyon views and is dog friendly.  Optional pet sitting services offered.
space: This property is on a secluded single lane street that runs along a ridge in a quiet residential neighborhood in the heart of San Diego. This 300 sq. ft. cottage is one of two buildings on the property (the other being Aurelia's little house on the street) and is set back behind a beautiful wooden fence.  It is perched on the edge of an expansive canyon and is light and airy and comfortably furnished for one or two people.  On the back side french doors open onto a balcony with a northeastern exposure offering an exquisite canyon view.  Numerous birds, including hawks, and even a owl or two, frequent the canyon and sometimes fly by at, or below, eye level. Bird song fills the air all day.

neighborhood_overview: We think this is the best neighborhood in San Diego.  You can walk to grocery shopping at Trader Joe's, Ralph's, and the area's best Farmer's Market on Sundays, not to mention all the restaurants of the Uptown District, University Avenue, University Heights, and Hillcrest.  Hillcrest, with its cafes, shops, and movie theater, is only a 20 minute walk.  Downtown is a short walk and bus ride away.  The world famous San Diego Zoo and all the museums and attractions of Balboa Park are 1 - 2 miles away, downtown is 3 miles away and we are only 4.7 miles from the airport and 4 miles from the Amtrak Station. Fashion Valley and Mission Valley shopping malls and access to the San Diego Trolley are 3.5 miles away. Area beaches are 7 - 8 miles away.
notes: While there is not a full kitchen in the cottage, it does have a coffee-maker, small refrigerator, microwave, and a few dining and serving amenities. Breakfast will not be provided everyday, but the cottage is stocked with coffee, tea, cream, sweeteners, English muffins, butter, and jam at the beginning of your stay. Friendly and quiet small to medium-sized dogs are welcome, and dog sitting is available for an extra charge if arranged in advance.
transit: This is a great neighborhood for those who like to walk.  Hillcrest is a 20 minute walk southwest, Park Blvd. is a 20 minute walk northeast, Balboa Park is about a 30 - 40 minute walk south. Walk about half a mile to access city busses to downtown or east to San Diego State University. Ride-sharing and car-sharing services are abundant in the area.
access: Guests will have access to the Zen garden that is at the entrance to the cottage and access to the patios, terraces, and balconies on the back side of the property.
interaction: Aurelia lives in the main house on the property and will be in and out.  Cate and Barry live down the street a few blocks.  All three of us will be available if needed.  One of the beauties of the cottage is the privacy, so interaction with Aurelia is upon your mutual discretion.
house_rules: Because this is a quiet residential neighborhood, please no loud or late parties. No smoking tobacco, please. There is no parking on the street. The driveway will be yours to park in during your stay. It is on a slight incline and a bit narrow, but can accommodate 2 cars parked in tandem.
host_about: We are a family of artists.  Barry and Aurelia draw, paint, and photograph.  Cate was a choreographer and modern dancer.  As a former architect, Barry designed numerous homes in the San Diego area, including two in our neighborhood (one being our home) that you will drive past on your way to this lovely canyon hideaway.  Barry lent his artistic eye to renovating and designing the interior and exterior spaces of this sweet little property that has been in the family for almost 25 years.  Cate and Barry have lived in this neighborhood for more than 25 years and Aurelia has lived here all of her 24 years.  She now lives in the little grey house at this property, and being an aal enthusiast and magnet, is offering her services as a dog sitter for those canines who accompany their humans during their stay and don't want to be left alone all day while their humans sightsee and visit the Zoo.

host_about:
Greetings from Team Vacasa! Yes, we're a professional property management company—but we're also real people, trusted by the owners of vacation homes to take care of all the heavy lifting like housekeeping, reservations, maintenance, and guest care. (Because, to be honest, renting out a vacation home really can be a full-time job!)

We have local teams on the ground to take care of our homes and our guests. We like to think of it as the best of both worlds: you can enjoy a one-of-a-kind vacation experience in a unique property, only without compromising on service and convenience. You can trust that your home will be cleaned by professional housekeepers, and your calls will be answered (right away, around the clock!) by our dedicated Guest Services team. 

Check out our listings, and if you have any questions, get in touch! We'd love to help you plan your perfect getaway.
