name: Casita Carancho
summary: Charming guest house on a third of an acre property in a quiet central neighborhood.  Originally developed in 1958, the space has recently been renovated.  We are the third generation of family to occupy the property and we hope you enjoy it as much as we do.  You can relax and enjoy the peace and quiet that exsists from the deck out the French doors that overlook a portion of Tecolote Canyon or enjoy a hot outside shower after spending the day at the beach.
space: This is a detached studio guest house with a private entrance, queen size bed, full size working kitchen, and a deck with canyon views to relax on.    We occupy the main house and are available to help with whatever your needs may be.  There is plenty of free street parking and we are within 3 miles of most freeways (I-5, I-805, & I-163).

neighborhood_overview: We are located in the neighborhood of Clairemont, 2 miles from Mission bay and 15 minutes (by car) to La Jolla and most local beaches.  There are some great canyon hikes, an executive golf course (Tecolote Golf) and a community park with a playground all within walking distance of the guest house.
notes: We are willing to host small families (up to 3 people) but please be aware that the space is small and was not designed to be kid friendly." If that's what your looking for checkout our Casa Carancho property right next door."
transit: We recommend having a car but it's not entirely necessary.  There are grocery stores within 1 mile in either direction of the guest house (although waking through the canyon can be difficult).  San Diego has plenty of UBER and Lyft drivers if you decide not to get a car.
access: You will have access to the entire guest house and canyon deck. You can certainly use the exterior outside shower if you'd like (our teenagers use it often after a day at the beach).
interaction: We are a busy native San Diegan family and we enjoy spending our free time at the beach.  We are more than happy to offer you suggestions for your stay and we'd be happy to share what we love about San Diego.  We are always available by phone or text.
house_rules: All guests that book MUST be 21 years of age or older.  No exceptions.  No smoking.  If there are signs of smoke or smell, guests will be charged.  This is a guest house on our property with neighbors, we ask that you be respectful of the neighborhood and no excessive noise or loud music after 10 pm.
host_about:
My husband, Chris,  and I are both native San Diegans and we love our city.  We love spending time at the beach in the water and on the sand playing volleyball,  eating good food and drinking good wine.  We have two adult children and two teenagers.  Chris works in the construction industry and I am a special education teacher.

We are hoping that our newly remodeled mid-century home meets your needs.  We've stocked the garage with boogie boards, a surfboard, beach chairs, bikes and sand toys to help make your vacation the best it can be.

We live in the same neighborhood (in a different home) so we are available to help in any way necessary.  Please feel free to contact us with any questions.

space: We are a 15 room boutique BnB located in the heart of La Jolla Village in San Diego County.  Each guest room is appointed with different amenities and in their own style and design.  Listed as Historical Site 179  on the San Diego Registry, our Inn has a rich historical past that allows guests to explore and become lost in its stories. It was originally built as a residence for George Kautz family in 1913. The original Gardens were designed by famed horticulturist Kate Sessions, also a well known San Diego figure, who was responsible for Balboa Park and the Scripps Family Gardens. Both these individuals are honored as names of our guest rooms. It also served as the home to the March King

name: Hale Ama - Middle Bedroom
summary: Hale Ama, Hawaiian for House of Love, is the name of this special spot. Located on the second floor, this room has a dedicated (detached) bathroom and desk space just off the main kitchen.  You'll be just minutes from Coronado Island, Balboa Park, Downtown San Diego, North Park, and Hillcrest.  The space offers very comfortable sleeping for up to 4 guests. Your reservation will be the only Airbnb guests in the home but the space is also occupied by other adults who live upstairs full-time.
space: Hale Ama has some pretty cool features that make it special. On the ground (1st floor), is a large, tandem garage. This fits two cars parked tandem (one car pulls in and the other pulls in behind them). The garage can be accessed by a wireless keypad mounted outside the garage door. Once checked-in you will be provided with garage access if your booking requires parking. The ground floor also features a western-facing front patio with adirondack chairs for enjoying the sunset while sipping your favorite beverage.  On the second floor, the same view and sunset is visible from the large balcony. This balcony is equipped with outdoor seating for 6. On clear days, the San Diego bay is visible and the Coronado bridge always highlights the horizon. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is part of the central part of San Diego’s residential neighborhoods. Just down the street (5 minutes walking) is grocery store and shopping plaza with laundromat, some fast food, and a pizza place. Across the street from the house, there’s a big park area that’s part of a community center, continuing education center, and a branch of the San Diego library. On the other corner is Chinese buffet restaurant that’s open late and great for a quick bite when you don’t want to cook.  Just up the street is another large shopping plaza with a Costco, 24-hour fitness, Jackie Robinson’s “Y” gym, and several other restaurant chains.  The biggest attractions in San Diego are just a few minutes away. Balboa Park, the Midway Museum, the San Diego Zoo, SDSU, Seaport Village, Sea World San Diego, the San Diego Convention Center and so much more are all easily accessible by public transit, rideshare, and car.
notes: I live in the master bedroom on the third floor. I also have renters who live on the 3rd floor. My dog Bartholomew lives in the house as well. He’s a 20lb spring spaniel chihuahua. If you have any concerns about the dog, please ask before arrival. If you have any hesitation, please find another listing. But I am sure that you will enjoy his company as soon as you get to know him.
transit: There’s quite a few options for navigating San Diego from Hale Ama. Since you’ll be staying in the central part of town, the core public transit system is easily accessible. The San Diego trolley is just 1 mile from the house giving you quick access to downtown San Diego to the west and San Diego State University to the east. Multiple bus lines have stops directly in front of the house with lines that travel west out to Coronado Island, north to Fashion Valley mall, and all other major destinations in San Diego. Lyft, Uber, and other rideshare services (like bikes and scooters) are plentiful in San Diego. You can use any of the apps to quickly call a ride to anywhere in San Diego for a lot less than a taxi. A Lyft “line” ride to the San Diego airport is about $6 from Hale Ama and takes about 12 minutes.  If you’ll have your own car, Hale Ama is located along the 805 freeway corridor, just south of route 94. The 5 freeway is just a short drive down the 94 freeway. You can easily get any
access: As a guest in my home, you’ll have access to all of the space in the home - except my bedroom. I want you to feel welcome and free to utilize the space like you’re at home. If you’re renting all of the guest bedrooms in Hale Ama, you won’t be sharing the space with anyone but me. If you’ve booked either of the bedrooms (Hale Ama - Middle Room OR Hale Ama - Upper Bedroom), you might be sharing the common spaces with another Airbnb guest.  The kitchen, living room, dining room, balcony, patio and desk area are all open to all guests of Hale Ama. The community also has plenty of common space to enjoy including several grassy areas that perfect for a picnic. Other common space in the community is dedicated to dog walking areas.  If you’re stay requires it, you can also utilize the garage for parking. There is also plenty of streetside parking available if you have need for extra parking.
interaction: I’ll be available to answer any questions you have throughout your stay, provide recommendations for places to go and see, and maybe even hang out in the evenings when I get home from work. I work long hours during the work week and won't usually be at the house from 7am to 7pm. I will be available via text or phone for anything that you need. Don’t hesitate to give me a buzz if I can help with anything.

There are many great places to walk to for food and drink just two blocks north of us. And a quick uber or lyft ride to downtown, the zoo, the convention center, the harbor and the beach.
notes: It’s important to note that we are in the flight path. Luckily we are still a ways from the airport and the planes stop landing at 11pm, but you can hear them. neighborhood_overview: You will find the house to be ideally located, within 10 minute walk to the bay and 15 to the beach. There are a lot of shops and restaurants within walking distance and we will gladly share our favorite addresses. It's a great place for a healthy lifestyle and you will see a lot of people surfing, running on the beach, biking or heading to their Yoga practice. Sea World is a 10 minute drive from our place. You are also within walking distance of the Pacific Beach nightlife (Garnet avenue is a few blocks away and the beach front is 1 mile away).
notes: We would like to make sure that you have all the information you need before you make a reservation so please feel free to reach out to us with any questions you may have.
transit: There are several bus stops within a couple of blocks, including the 30, which will take you downtown or to La Jolla in about 30 minutes. By car, access to the Interstate 5 is also easy.
access: We live in a large house (2500+ sq. feet) with a large living room, dining room, laundry room, kitchen and 3 bedrooms (each with its own bathroom), including yours. This is one of the 2 bedrooms we rent in our home and this one is located upstairs. We are happy to share the living room and kitchen. You also have full access to the deck and backyard, with hot tub and BBQ grill. You are welcome to use the washer and dryer. There is a 4 seat table in the living room and another one on the deck in our backyard.  Both offer a pleasant spot to eat (or work, if you need to). There are multiple sofas (including one in your room), comfortable armchairs and outdoor lounge chairs if you want to relax or take a nap. We kindly ask you not to use the dining room, and that you keep the areas you use clean (e.g. kitchen, grill, dryer).
interaction: We both love traveling and enjoy meeting new people so we'll be there for you - we tend to be fairly busy during the week but will stay in touch by phone or instant messages and we will be glad to share our tips and tricks to make your stay memorable. On weekends; we will most likely be around the house, running errands and relaxing. We may have friends over for brunch or dinner once in a while but there is plenty of space for us to share.
house_rules: We have a few requirements for the convenience of future guests:  - No parties allowed - Please take your shoes off in the house  - We kindly ask you not to smoke on the property  - We do not accept pets - For everyone's security, no drugs and no weapons are allowed We love to accommodate early check-ins and late check-outs when we can. If you need to check-in early and/or check-out late, please make a request at least 24 hrs in advance and we will check our schedule to see if it is possible. If it is not possible, please honor the check-in time of 3:00 p.m. and the check-out time of 11:00 am. This gives us time to make the room nice, clean, and attractive for the next guest. Thank you :)
host_about: We are a young couple and enjoy mingling with people from different cultures and backgrounds. We are originally from Europe and love living in sunny Sun Diego :). We work in sales & marketing for technology companies and sometimes work long hours during the week so we enjoy going to the beach and relaxing on the weekends. We also love traveling, good wine, and good food. We appreciate the fact that our house is within walking distance to the beach & the bay so it's always nice to go for a walk, run, or bike ride and enjoy the sunset. We like having guests around, offering suggestions for local restaurants, and adding a unique & personal touch to their stay.

name: Blue Beach House l 5 blocks to Beach /Restaurants
summary: The freshly renovated Blue Beach Flat is a perfect option for a couple or family of 3. The flat includes living room, kitchen, bathroom & bedroom with partial bay & ocean views. There’s a sunset view from the wooden deck where wine & food are enjoyed. The deck overlooks the garden & fountain below. Head outside down the stairs & it's just a short stroll to Tourmaline beach & restaurants. This flat is comfortable, clean & has style!  Enjoy a free salsa class at the owner’s PB dance studio!
space: The flat is newly renovated, is sparkling clean & boasts of everything new.  The guests have ultimate privacy in the upstairs flat.  The world traveling owners live downstairs and are extremely helpful to guests in recommendations & requests.

neighborhood_overview: Welcome to Pacific Beach!  PB is one of the most coveted neighborhoods in San Diego.  This vibrant beach town has an array of restaurants, bars, clubs, coffee shops, lounges and provides an array of entertainment.  La Jolla is just a 5 minute drive away to see the seals & shops. PB is centrally located and a 10 minute drive to Downtown, Little Italy, Del Mar, North Park, Mission Valley & Balboa Park, Sea World & the Zoo. Touring San Diego - Welcome  Here’s a list of things to do while in San Diego. Stroll, run, skate, bike scooter on the world famous beach boardwalk and see the iconic PB pier.  Drink, party & be merry on Garnet Avenue in the Heart of Pacific Beach with all the bars, pubs, nightclub, restaurants & shops! You’ll find everything there!  Have breakfast in posh La Jolla at the local farmers market on Sunday between 9:00am and 1:00pm. La Jolla Cove is an amazing place to watch the sea lions. Also check out the Caves that take you away with the most amazing ocean sounds hitti
notes: We would love if guests treat our home like their own.   Please do not remove any items from the flat. If we find that items are missing, we will need to replace it from the security deposit paid. If any items becomes damaged or broken, please notify us immediately. We have a small, deaf dog that is extremely friendly, quiet and spends her time sleeping in our house.  She does not have access to the garden leading up to the flat. There are 15 steps to go upstairs to the private flat and balcony.   Our neighbors are friendly and quiet so please no parties or overly loud music.   Guests park in the back alley in front of the garage for easy access into the garden and flat.  We are also a family of artists and own two dance studios in Pacific Beach and La Jolla.  Our airbnb guests (up to 2 guests) are welcome to take a free beginner group Salsa Class that takes place on Thursdays at 7pm.  ($50 value/not redeemable for dollar amount.)
transit: Our home is located 5 blocks from PB's iconic beaches and highly rated restaurants and coffee shops. Garnet street is located 8 blocks away. Gelson's Grocery Store is very close by.   Guests can walk to many destinations, take an affordable uber/lyft, use an electric scooter, take the public bus or bike around (rental bike store is near Garnet).
access: Guests may access the garden leading up to the stairway of the private flat of the property.  Washer and Dryer services are available upon request for an extra fee.
interaction: We love hosting and are excited to welcome you into our blue beach flat.  We live in the house downstairs so we generally greet every guest.  We are  happy to socialize with guests as well as respect space.  We are happy to answer any and all questions about the visit.  We are also accessible via text or messenger.   Our family can speak English, French, Spanish & Vietnamese which allows us to communicate in 4 languages.
house_rules: Park in the back parking spot in front of garage.  Enter through the back gate entrance.  Please wash sand off below in the grass shower area before walking up staircase. Please No Smoking inside the house or on the house property.
